Key steps of the execution phase are rounding-up of the cell, retraction of pseudopodes, reduction of cellular volume (pyknosis), chromatin condensation, nuclear fragmentation (karyorrhexis), plasma membrane blebbing and fragmentation of the cell into apoptotic bodies. When the execution phase is completed, the cell has died.

nodes.label: GO:0042492
nodes.Name: gamma-delta T cell differentiation
nodes.Definition: The process in which a relatively unspecialized hemopoietic cell acquires specialized features of a gamma-delta T cell. A gamma-delta T cell is a T cell that expresses a gamma-delta T cell receptor complex.

nodes.label: GO:0045587
nodes.Name: negative regulation of gamma-delta T cell differentiation
nodes.Definition: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of gamma-delta T cell differentiation.

nodes.label: GO:0016830
nodes.Name: carbon-carbon lyase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the cleavage of C-C bonds by other means than by hydrolysis or oxidation, or conversely adding a group to a double bond.

nodes.label: GO:0034579
nodes.Name: obsolete (1-methylpentyl)succinate synthase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the reaction: fumarate + n-hexane = (1-methylpentyl)succinate.

nodes.label: GO:0035178
nodes.Name: turning behavior
nodes.Definition: Fine-tuning the spatial position of an organism in response to variability in their environment. For example, reorientation of an organism in the direction of a food source.

nodes.label: GO:0035179
nodes.Name: obsolete larval turning behavior
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Fine-tuning the spatial position of a larva in response to variability in their environment. For example, reorientation of a larva in the direction of a food source.

nodes.label: GO:0036425
nodes.Name: obsolete D-phosphoserine phosphatase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the reaction: O-phospho-D-serine + H2O = L-serine + phosphate, on a free amino acid.

nodes.label: GO:0015645
nodes.Name: fatty acid ligase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the ligation of a fatty acid to an acceptor, coupled to the hydrolysis of ATP.

nodes.label: GO:0006971
nodes.Name: hypotonic response
nodes.Definition: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of detection of, or exposure to, a hypotonic environment, i.e. an environment with a lower concentration of solutes than the organism or cell.

nodes.label: GO:0042539
nodes.Name: hypotonic salinity response
nodes.Definition: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of detection of, or exposure to, a decrease in the concentration of salt (particularly but not exclusively sodium and chloride ions) in the environment.

nodes.label: GO:0044619
nodes.Name: positive regulation of relaxation of uterine smooth muscle in another organism
nodes.Definition: The process in which an organism increases the extent of relaxation of smooth muscle in the uterus of a second organism.

nodes.label: GO:0007626
nodes.Name: locomotory behavior
nodes.Definition: The specific movement from place to place of an organism in response to external or internal stimuli. Locomotion of a whole organism in a manner dependent upon some combination of that organism's internal state and external conditions.

nodes.label: GO:0060330
nodes.Name: regulation of response to type II interferon
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of a response to type II interferon (interferon-gamma). Response to interferon gamma is a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an interferon-gamma stimulus.

nodes.label: GO:0075193
nodes.Name: regulation of haustorium mother cell formation
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of symbiont haustorium mother cell formation. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

nodes.label: GO:0075194
nodes.Name: positive regulation of haustorium mother cell formation
nodes.Definition: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of symbiont haustorium mother cell formation. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

nodes.label: GO:0008435
nodes.Name: obsolete anticoagulant activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Functions to retard or prevent coagulation. Often used in the context of blood or milk coagulation.

nodes.label: GO:0050819
nodes.Name: negative regulation of coagulation
nodes.Definition: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of coagulation.

nodes.label: GO:0044165
nodes.Name: host cell endoplasmic reticulum
nodes.Definition: The irregular network of unit membranes, visible only by electron microscopy, that occurs in the host cell cytoplasm of many eukaryotic cells. The membranes form a complex meshwork of tubular channels, which are often expanded into slitlike cavities called cisternae. The host ER takes two forms, rough (or granular), with ribosomes adhering to the outer surface, and smooth (with no ribosomes attached).

nodes.label: GO:0044170
nodes.Name: host cell smooth endoplasmic reticulum
nodes.Definition: The irregular network of unit membranes, visible only by electron microscopy, that occurs in the host cell cytoplasm of many eukaryotic cells. The membranes form a complex meshwork of tubular channels, which are often expanded into slitlike cavities called cisternae. The host smooth ER has no ribosomes adhering to the outer surface.

nodes.label: GO:0070664
nodes.Name: negative regulation of leukocyte proliferation
nodes.Definition: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of leukocyte proliferation.

nodes.label: GO:0090291
nodes.Name: negative regulation of osteoclast proliferation
nodes.Definition: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of the multiplication or reproduction of osteoclasts, resulting in the expansion of an osteoclast cell population.

nodes.label: GO:0097190
nodes.Name: apoptotic signaling pathway
nodes.Definition: The series of molecular signals which triggers the apoptotic death of a cell. The pathway starts with reception of a signal, and ends when the execution phase of apoptosis is triggered.

nodes.label: GO:0097296
nodes.Name: activation of cysteine-type endopeptidase activity involved in apoptotic signaling pathway
nodes.Definition: Any process that initiates the activity of an inactive cysteine-type endopeptidase involved in the apoptotic signaling pathway.

nodes.label: GO:0044115
nodes.Name: formation of structure involved in a symbiotic process
nodes.Definition: The progression of an organism from an initial condition to a later condition, occurring when the organism is in a symbiotic interaction.

nodes.label: GO:0044132
nodes.Name: obsolete development of symbiont on or near host
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. The progression of a symbiont from an initial condition to a later condition, within the cells or tissues of its host organism.

nodes.label: GO:0043736
nodes.Name: obsolete DNA-3-methyladenine glycosylase IV activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the hydrolysis of alkylated DNA; recognizes and removes both N-3- and N-7-methyl purines by cleaving the N-C1' glycosidic bond between the target damaged DNA base and the deoxyribose sugar. The reaction releases a free base and leaves an apurinic (AP) site.

nodes.label: GO:0043916
nodes.Name: DNA-7-methylguanine glycosylase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: DNA containing 7-methylguanine + H2O = DNA with abasic site + 7-methylguanine. This reaction is the hydrolysis of DNA by cleavage of the N-C1' glycosidic bond between the damaged DNA 7-methylguanine and the deoxyribose sugar to remove the 7-methylguanine, leaving an abasic site.

nodes.label: GO:0038146
nodes.Name: chemokine (C-X-C motif) ligand 12 signaling pathway
nodes.Definition: The series of molecular signals initiated by the binding of the chemokine CXCL12 to its receptor on the surface of a target cell, and ending with the regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. transcription.

nodes.label: GO:0038160
nodes.Name: CXCL12-activated CXCR4 signaling pathway
nodes.Definition: The series of molecular signals initiated by the binding of the C-X-C chemokine CXCL12 to a C-X-C chemokine type 4 receptor (CXCR4) on the surface of a target cell, and ending with the regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. transcription.

nodes.label: GO:0052685
nodes.Name: obsolete perillic acid-CoA ligase (ADP-forming) activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the reaction: perillic acid + CoA-SH + ATP = H2O + ADP + phosphate + perillyl-CoA.

nodes.label: GO:0015930
nodes.Name: glutamate synthase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the formation of L-glutamine and 2-oxoglutarate from L-glutamate, using NADH, NADPH or ferredoxin as hydrogen acceptors.

nodes.label: GO:0045181
nodes.Name: glutamate synthase activity, NAD(P)H as acceptor
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 2 L-glutamate + NAD(P)+ = L-glutamine + 2-oxoglutarate + NAD(P)H + H+.

nodes.label: GO:0034603
nodes.Name: pyruvate dehydrogenase [NAD(P)+] activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: pyruvate + CoA + NAD(P)+ = acetyl-CoA + CO2 + NAD(P)H.

nodes.label: GO:0050243
nodes.Name: pyruvate dehydrogenase (NADP+) activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: CoA + NADP+ + pyruvate = acetyl-CoA + CO2 + NADPH.

nodes.label: GO:0004725
nodes.Name: protein tyrosine phosphatase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: protein tyrosine phosphate + H2O = protein tyrosine + phosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0030945
nodes.Name: obsolete protein tyrosine phosphatase activity, via thiol-phosphate intermediate
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. The catalysis of phosphate removal from a phosphotyrosine using cysteine as a nucleophile and proceed by means of a thiol-phosphate intermediate.

nodes.label: GO:0050053
nodes.Name: levansucrase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: sucrose + 2,6-beta-D-fructosyl(n) = glucose + 2,6-beta-D-fructosyl(n+1).

nodes.label: GO:0004278
nodes.Name: obsolete granzyme B activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the preferential cleavage of Asp-Xaa > Asn-Xaa > Met-Xaa, Ser-Xaa.

nodes.label: GO:0060948
nodes.Name: cardiac vascular smooth muscle cell development
nodes.Definition: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a cardiac vascular smooth muscle cell over time, from its formation to the mature state.

nodes.label: GO:0060984
nodes.Name: epicardium-derived cardiac vascular smooth muscle cell development
nodes.Definition: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a cardiac vascular smooth muscle cell that was derived from the epicardium over time, from its formation to the mature state.

nodes.label: GO:0033332
nodes.Name: ent-kaurene biosynthetic process
nodes.Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of ent-kaurene. Ent-kaurene is a tetracyclic diterpenoid that is a precursor of several plant isoprenoids, including gibberellins.

nodes.label: GO:0046246
nodes.Name: terpene biosynthetic process
nodes.Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of terpenes, any of a large group of hydrocarbons made up of isoprene units.

nodes.label: GO:0050193
nodes.Name: phosphoketolase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: D-xylulose 5-phosphate + phosphate = acetyl phosphate + D-glyceraldehyde 3-phosphate + H2O.

nodes.label: GO:0002114
nodes.Name: interleukin-33 receptor activity
nodes.Definition: Combining with interleukin-33 and transmitting the signal from one side of the membrane to the other to initiate a change in cell activity.

nodes.label: GO:0038172
nodes.Name: interleukin-33-mediated signaling pathway
nodes.Definition: The series of molecular signals initiated by interleukin-33 binding to its receptor on the surface of a target cell, and ending with the regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. transcription.

nodes.label: GO:1990321
nodes.Name: collagen type XXII trimer
nodes.Definition: A collagen homotrimer of alpha1(XXII) chains; type XXII collagen triple helices acts as a cell adhesion ligand for skin epithelial cells and fibroblasts.

nodes.label: GO:0071352
nodes.Name: cellular response to interleukin-2
nodes.Definition: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an interleukin-2 stimulus.

nodes.label: GO:0018478
nodes.Name: malonate-semialdehyde dehydrogenase (acetylating) activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 3-oxopropanoate + CoA + NAD(P)+ = acetyl-CoA + CO2 + NAD(P)H.

nodes.label: GO:0050888
nodes.Name: determination of stimulus location
nodes.Definition: The determination of where on the body surface, within the body or in the environment a stimulus originates.

nodes.label: GO:0050893
nodes.Name: sensory processing
nodes.Definition: Any neural process required for an organism to sense and interpret the dimensions of a sensory experience: modality, location, intensity and affect.

nodes.label: GO:0034382
nodes.Name: chylomicron remnant clearance
nodes.Definition: The process in which a chylomicron remnant is removed from the blood via receptor-mediated endocytosis into liver cells and its constituent parts degraded.

nodes.label: GO:0071828
nodes.Name: apolipoprotein E recycling
nodes.Definition: The process in which chylomicron remnant-associated apolipoprotein E is internalized by endocytosis, localized to recycling endosomes and then secreted in association with a high-density lipoprotein particle.

nodes.label: GO:0031012
nodes.Name: extracellular matrix
nodes.Definition: A structure lying external to one or more cells, which provides structural support, biochemical or biomechanical cues for cells or tissues.

nodes.label: GO:1990377
nodes.Name: organomineral extracellular matrix
nodes.Definition: An extracellular matrix consisting of a densely packed organomineral assembly in which the mineral phase represents the majority of the material by weight.

nodes.label: GO:0032823
nodes.Name: regulation of natural killer cell differentiation
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of natural killer cell differentiation.

nodes.label: GO:0032824
nodes.Name: negative regulation of natural killer cell differentiation
nodes.Definition: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of natural killer cell differentiation.

nodes.label: GO:0090658
nodes.Name: cone matrix sheath
nodes.Definition: A biochemically and structurally distinct domain of the retinal interphotoreceptor matrix that is specifically associated with cone photoreceptor cell inner and outer segments.

nodes.label: GO:0050869
nodes.Name: negative regulation of B cell activation
nodes.Definition: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of B cell activation.

nodes.label: GO:0051250
nodes.Name: negative regulation of lymphocyte activation
nodes.Definition: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of lymphocyte activation.

nodes.label: GO:0033911
nodes.Name: mycodextranase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the endohydrolysis of 1,4-alpha-D-glucosidic linkages in alpha-D-glucans containing both 1,3- and 1,4-bonds.

nodes.label: GO:0034401
nodes.Name: obsolete chromatin organization involved in regulation of transcription
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Any cellular process that results in the specification, formation or maintenance of the physical structure of eukaryotic chromatin that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of DNA-dependent transcription.

nodes.label: GO:0097549
nodes.Name: obsolete chromatin organization involved in negative regulation of transcription
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of transcription by chromatin organization.

nodes.label: GO:0048091
nodes.Name: positive regulation of female pigmentation
nodes.Definition: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of establishment of a pattern of pigment in females.

nodes.label: GO:0071735
nodes.Name: IgG immunoglobulin complex
nodes.Definition: A protein complex composed of two identical immunoglobulin heavy chains of an IgG isotype and two identical immunoglobulin light chains, held together by disulfide bonds. An IgG immunoglobulin complex may be embedded in the plasma membrane or present in the extracellular space, in mucosal areas or other tissues, or circulating in the blood or lymph.

nodes.label: GO:0071737
nodes.Name: IgG B cell receptor complex
nodes.Definition: An IgG immunoglobulin complex that is present in the plasma membrane of B cells and is composed of two identical immunoglobulin heavy chains of an IgG isotype and two identical immunoglobulin light chains and a signaling subunit, a heterodimer of the Ig-alpha and Ig-beta proteins.

nodes.label: GO:0042118
nodes.Name: endothelial cell activation
nodes.Definition: The change in morphology and behavior of an endothelial cell resulting from exposure to a cytokine, chemokine, cellular ligand, or soluble factor.

nodes.label: GO:1904987
nodes.Name: regulation of endothelial cell activation
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of endothelial cell activation.

nodes.label: GO:0032037
nodes.Name: myosin I heavy chain binding
nodes.Definition: Binding to a heavy chain of a myosin I complex.

nodes.label: GO:0048079
nodes.Name: regulation of cuticle pigmentation
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of establishment of a pattern of pigment in the cuticle of an organism.

nodes.label: GO:0030405
nodes.Name: obsolete matrix metalloproteinase 19 activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Was not defined before being made obsolete.

nodes.label: GO:1903100
nodes.Name: 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 3,5-bisphosphate metabolic process
nodes.Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways involving 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 3,5-bisphosphate.

nodes.label: GO:1903102
nodes.Name: 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 3,5-bisphosphate biosynthetic process
nodes.Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 3,5-bisphosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0033646
nodes.Name: host intracellular part
nodes.Definition: Any constituent part of the living contents of a host cell; the matter contained within (but not including) the plasma membrane, usually taken to exclude large vacuoles and masses of secretory or ingested material. In eukaryotes it includes the nucleus and cytoplasm. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

nodes.label: GO:0008128
nodes.Name: tyrosine-ester sulfotransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 3'-phospho-5'-adenylyl sulfate + L-tyrosine methyl ester = L-tyrosine methyl ester 4-sulfate + adenosine 3',5'-diphosphate + H+.

nodes.label: GO:0017067
nodes.Name: tyrosine-ester sulfotransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 3'-phospho-5'-adenylyl sulfate + L-tyrosine methyl ester = L-tyrosine methyl ester 4-sulfate + adenosine 3',5'-diphosphate + H+.

nodes.label: GO:0061160
nodes.Name: regulation of establishment of bipolar cell polarity regulating cell shape
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of the establishment of bipolar cell polarity that contributes to the shape of a cell.

nodes.label: GO:0061161
nodes.Name: positive regulation of establishment of bipolar cell polarity regulating cell shape
nodes.Definition: Any process that increases the rate, frequency or extent of the establishment of bipolar cell polarity that regulates the shape of a cell.

nodes.label: GO:0008846
nodes.Name: obsolete endopeptidase La activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the hydrolysis of large proteins such as globin, casein and denatured serum albumin, in presence of ATP.

nodes.label: GO:0071160
nodes.Name: cyanophycin synthetase activity (L-aspartate-adding)
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + [L-Asp(4-L-Arg)]n + L-Asp = ADP + phosphate + [L-Asp(4-L-Arg)]n-L-Asp.

nodes.label: GO:0007159
nodes.Name: leukocyte cell-cell adhesion
nodes.Definition: The attachment of a leukocyte to another cell via adhesion molecules.

nodes.label: GO:0097323
nodes.Name: B cell adhesion
nodes.Definition: The attachment of a B cell to another cell via adhesion molecules.

nodes.label: GO:0050818
nodes.Name: regulation of coagulation
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of coagulation, the process in which a fluid solution, or part of it, changes into a solid or semisolid mass.

nodes.label: GO:0075314
nodes.Name: regulation of basidium development
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of basidium development, a process that leads to the formation of a basidium, a small, specialized club-shaped structure typically bearing four basidiospores at the tips of minute projections. The basidium is unique to Basidiomycetes and distinguishes them from other kinds of fungi.

nodes.label: GO:0043524
nodes.Name: negative regulation of neuron apoptotic process
nodes.Definition: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of cell death by apoptotic process in neurons.

nodes.label: GO:1901215
nodes.Name: obsolete negative regulation of neuron death
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of neuron death.

nodes.label: GO:1903193
nodes.Name: sesquarterpene biosynthetic process
nodes.Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of sesquarterpene.

nodes.label: GO:0060259
nodes.Name: regulation of feeding behavior
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of the behavior associated with the intake of food.

nodes.label: GO:2000253
nodes.Name: positive regulation of feeding behavior
nodes.Definition: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of feeding behavior.

nodes.label: GO:0065005
nodes.Name: protein-lipid complex assembly
nodes.Definition: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of proteins and lipids to form a protein-lipid complex.

nodes.label: GO:0032087
nodes.Name: regulation of type IV site-specific deoxyribonuclease activity
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a type IV restriction endodeoxyribonuclease activity.

nodes.label: GO:0032093
nodes.Name: SAM domain binding
nodes.Definition: Binding to a SAM (Sterile Alpha Motif) domain, which is a 70-amino acid protein sequence that participates in protein-protein, protein-lipid, and protein-RNA interactions and is conserved from lower to higher eukaryotes.

nodes.label: GO:0048738
nodes.Name: cardiac muscle tissue development
nodes.Definition: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of cardiac muscle over time, from its formation to the mature structure.

nodes.label: GO:0055008
nodes.Name: cardiac muscle tissue morphogenesis
nodes.Definition: The process in which the anatomical structures of cardiac muscle tissue are generated and organized.

nodes.label: GO:0043281
nodes.Name: regulation of cysteine-type endopeptidase activity involved in apoptotic process
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the activity of a cysteine-type endopeptidase involved in apoptosis.

nodes.label: GO:0097153
nodes.Name: cysteine-type endopeptidase activity involved in apoptotic process
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of internal, alpha-peptide bonds in a polypeptide chain by a mechanism in which the sulfhydryl group of a cysteine residue at the active center acts as a nucleophile, and contributing to the apoptotic process.

nodes.label: GO:0032985
nodes.Name: protein-carbohydrate complex disassembly
nodes.Definition: The disaggregation of a protein-carbohydrate complex into its constituent components.

nodes.label: GO:0071823
nodes.Name: protein-carbohydrate complex subunit organization
nodes.Definition: Any process in which macromolecules aggregate, disaggregate, or are modified, resulting in the formation, disassembly, or alteration of a protein-carbohydrate complex.

nodes.label: GO:0014805
nodes.Name: smooth muscle adaptation
nodes.Definition: Any process in which smooth muscle adapts, with consequent modifications to structural and/or functional phenotypes, in response to a stimulus. Stimuli include contractile activity, loading conditions, substrate supply, and environmental factors. These adaptive events occur in both muscle fibers and associated structures (motoneurons and capillaries), and they involve alterations in regulatory mechanisms, contractile properties and metabolic capacities.

nodes.label: GO:0014806
nodes.Name: smooth muscle hyperplasia
nodes.Definition: A process, occurring in smooth muscle, in which there is an increase in cell number by cell division, often leading to an increase in the size of an organ.

nodes.label: GO:0003944
nodes.Name: N-acetylglucosamine-1-phosphodiester alpha-N-acetylglucosaminidase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: glycoprotein N-acetyl-D-glucosaminyl-phospho-D-mannose + H2O = N-acetyl-D-glucosamine + glycoprotein phospho-D-mannose.

nodes.label: GO:0036490
nodes.Name: regulation of translation in response to endoplasmic reticulum stress
nodes.Definition: Modulation of the frequency, rate or extent of translation as a result of endoplasmic reticulum stress.

nodes.label: GO:0043555
nodes.Name: regulation of translation in response to stress
nodes.Definition: Modulation of the frequency, rate or extent of translation as a result of a stimulus indicating the organism is under stress. The stress is usually, but not necessarily, exogenous (e.g. temperature, humidity, ionizing radiation).

nodes.label: GO:0043067
nodes.Name: regulation of programmed cell death
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of programmed cell death, cell death resulting from activation of endogenous cellular processes.

nodes.label: GO:0043068
nodes.Name: positive regulation of programmed cell death
nodes.Definition: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of programmed cell death, cell death resulting from activation of endogenous cellular processes.

nodes.label: GO:0075039
nodes.Name: establishment of turgor in appressorium
nodes.Definition: The process in which hydrostatic pressure is increased within the symbiont appressorium to breach the cuticle of the host. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

nodes.label: GO:0075041
nodes.Name: obsolete positive regulation of establishment of turgor in appressorium
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of turgor formation in the symbiont appressorium.

nodes.label: GO:0075061
nodes.Name: hyphal growth
nodes.Definition: Growth of fungi as threadlike, tubular structures that may contain multiple nuclei and may or may not be divided internally by septa, or cross-walls.

nodes.label: GO:0075063
nodes.Name: obsolete positive regulation of invasive hypha growth
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Any process that activates, maintains or increases the frequency, rate or extent of symbiont invasive hypha formation within host. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

nodes.label: GO:0004253
nodes.Name: obsolete gamma-renin activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the cleavage of the Leu-Leu bond in synthetic tetradecapeptide renin substrate, producing angiotensin I, but not active on natural angiotensinogen. Also hydrolyzes BZ-Arg-para-nitroanilide.

nodes.label: GO:0047899
nodes.Name: formate dehydrogenase (NADP+) activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: formate + NADP+ = CO2 + NADPH.

nodes.label: GO:0035710
nodes.Name: CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell activation
nodes.Definition: The change in morphology and behavior of a CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell resulting from exposure to a mitogen, cytokine, chemokine, cellular ligand, or an antigen for which it is specific.

nodes.label: GO:0035711
nodes.Name: T-helper 1 cell activation
nodes.Definition: The change in morphology and behavior of a T-helper 1 cell resulting from exposure to a mitogen, cytokine, chemokine, cellular ligand, or an antigen for which it is specific.

nodes.label: GO:0015007
nodes.Name: obsolete electron carrier, chlorophyll electron transport system
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. A molecular entity that serves as an electron acceptor and electron donor in a chlorophyll electron transport system.

nodes.label: GO:0001836
nodes.Name: release of cytochrome c from mitochondria
nodes.Definition: The process that results in the movement of cytochrome c from the mitochondrial intermembrane space into the cytosol, which is part of the apoptotic signaling pathway and leads to caspase activation.

nodes.label: GO:1903039
nodes.Name: positive regulation of leukocyte cell-cell adhesion
nodes.Definition: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of leukocyte cell-cell adhesion.

nodes.label: GO:1900046
nodes.Name: regulation of hemostasis
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of hemostasis.

nodes.label: GO:0042755
nodes.Name: eating behavior
nodes.Definition: The specific behavior of an organism relating to the intake of food, any substance (usually solid) that can be metabolized by an organism to give energy and build tissue.

nodes.label: GO:1904000
nodes.Name: positive regulation of eating behavior
nodes.Definition: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of eating behavior.

nodes.label: GO:0038163
nodes.Name: thrombopoietin-mediated signaling pathway
nodes.Definition: The series of molecular signals initiated by thrombopoietin binding to its receptor on the surface of a target cell, and ending with the regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. transcription.

nodes.label: GO:0001716
nodes.Name: L-amino-acid oxidase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: an L-alpha-amino acid + H2O + O2 = a 2-oxocarboxylate + H2O2 + NH4+.

nodes.label: GO:0016641
nodes.Name: oxidoreductase activity, acting on the CH-NH2 group of donors, oxygen as acceptor
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which a CH-NH2 group acts as a hydrogen or electron donor and reduces an oxygen molecule.

nodes.label: GO:1904633
nodes.Name: regulation of podocyte apoptotic process
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of glomerular visceral epithelial cell apoptotic process.

nodes.label: GO:1904635
nodes.Name: positive regulation of podocyte apoptotic process
nodes.Definition: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of glomerular visceral epithelial cell apoptotic process.

nodes.label: GO:1990165
nodes.Name: single-strand break-containing DNA binding
nodes.Definition: Binding to damaged DNA containing single-strand breaks (SSBs).

nodes.label: GO:0061650
nodes.Name: ubiquitin-like protein conjugating enzyme activity
nodes.Definition: Isoenergetic transfer of a ubiquitin-like protein (ULP) from one protein to another molecule, usually another protein, via the reaction X-SCP + Y = Y-SCP + X, where both the X-SCP and Y-SCP linkages are thioester bonds between the C-terminal amino acid of SCP and a sulfhydryl side group of a cysteine residue.

nodes.label: GO:0005100
nodes.Name: GTPase activator activity
nodes.Definition: Binds to and increases the activity of a GTPase, an enzyme that catalyzes the hydrolysis of GTP.

nodes.label: GO:1903037
nodes.Name: regulation of leukocyte cell-cell adhesion
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of leukocyte cell-cell adhesion.

nodes.label: GO:0005027
nodes.Name: obsolete NGF/TNF (6 C-domain) receptor activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. (Was not defined before being made obsolete).

nodes.label: GO:0005031
nodes.Name: tumor necrosis factor receptor activity
nodes.Definition: Combining with tumor necrosis factor, a proinflammatory cytokine produced by monocytes and macrophages, to initiate a change in cell function.

nodes.label: GO:0003369
nodes.Name: establishment of cell polarity involved in mesendodermal cell migration
nodes.Definition: The specification and formation of anisotropic intracellular organization that contributes to the self-propelled directed movement of a mesendodermal cell.

nodes.label: GO:0003379
nodes.Name: establishment of cell polarity involved in gastrulation cell migration
nodes.Definition: The specification and formation of anisotropic intracellular organization that contributes to the self-propelled directed movement of an ameboid cell taking part in gastrulation.

nodes.label: GO:0016504
nodes.Name: peptidase activator activity
nodes.Definition: Binds to and increases the activity of a peptidase.

nodes.label: GO:0061134
nodes.Name: peptidase regulator activity
nodes.Definition: Binds to and modulates the activity of a peptidase, any enzyme that catalyzes the hydrolysis peptide bonds.

nodes.label: GO:0075313
nodes.Name: basidium development
nodes.Definition: The process that leads to the development of basidium, a small, specialized club-shaped structure typically bearing four basidiospores at the tips of minute projections. The basidium is unique to Basidiomycetes and distinguishes them from other kinds of fungi.

nodes.label: GO:0075316
nodes.Name: negative regulation of basidium development
nodes.Definition: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of basidium development, a process that leads to the formation of basidium, a small, specialized club-shaped structure typically bearing four basidiospores at the tips of minute projections. The basidium is unique to basidiomycetes and distinguishes them from other kinds of fungi.

nodes.label: GO:0043669
nodes.Name: ectexine
nodes.Definition: The outer part of the exine, which stains positively with basic fuchsin in optical microscopy and has higher electron density in conventionally prepared TEM sections.

nodes.label: GO:0043670
nodes.Name: foot layer
nodes.Definition: The inner layer of the ectexine.

nodes.label: GO:0016879
nodes.Name: ligase activity, forming carbon-nitrogen bonds
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the joining of two molecules, or two groups within a single molecule, via a carbon-nitrogen bond, with the concomitant hydrolysis of the diphosphate bond in ATP or a similar triphosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0061483
nodes.Name: sulfinylpropanyl adenylate synthase
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: cysteine sulfanate + GTP + IMP = sulfinylpropanyl adenylate + GDP + 3 H+ + phosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0052373
nodes.Name: suppression of symbiont entry into host
nodes.Definition: Any process in which an organism stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent to which it enters into a second organism, where the two organisms are in a symbiotic interaction.

nodes.label: GO:0052483
nodes.Name: symbiont-mediated perturbation of host phagocytosis
nodes.Definition: A process in which in a symbiont interferes with or inhibits host phagocytosis by targeting phagocytic signaling or the cellular phagocytic machinery. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

nodes.label: GO:0070122
nodes.Name: obsolete isopeptidase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the hydrolysis of an isopeptide bond. An isopeptide bond is an amide linkage between a carboxyl group of one amino acid and an amino group of another amino acid in which at least one of these groups is not on the a-carbon of one of the amino acids (for example, the link between an epsilon-amino group of a lysine molecule to a carboxyl group on a second amino acid is an isopeptide bond).

nodes.label: GO:0070138
nodes.Name: ubiquitin-like protein peptidase activity
nodes.Definition: An isopeptidase activity that cleaves ubiquitin or ubiquitin-like proteins (ULP; e.g. ATG8, ISG15, NEDD8, SUMO) from target proteins.

nodes.label: GO:0043766
nodes.Name: Sep-tRNA:Cys-tRNA synthase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: H+ + hydrogen sulfide + O-phospho-L-seryl-tRNA(Cys) = L-cysteinyl-tRNA(Cys) + phosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0071952
nodes.Name: conversion of O-phosphoseryl-tRNA to cysteinyl-tRNA
nodes.Definition: The modification process that results in the conversion of O-phosphoserine charged on a tRNA(Cys) to cysteinyl-tRNA.

nodes.label: GO:0009777
nodes.Name: photosynthetic phosphorylation
nodes.Definition: Any metabolic process in which photosynthetic organisms use light energy to convert ADP to ATP without the concomitant reduction of dioxygen (O2) to water that occurs in phosphorylation.

nodes.label: GO:0009778
nodes.Name: cyclic photosynthetic phosphorylation
nodes.Definition: A photosynthetic phosphorylation process in which ATP synthesis is driven by a proton gradient generated across the thylakoid membrane. Involves only photosystem I.

nodes.label: GO:0001775
nodes.Name: cell activation
nodes.Definition: A multicellular organismal process by which exposure to an activating factor such as a cellular or soluble ligand results in a change in the morphology or behavior of a cell.

nodes.label: GO:0002266
nodes.Name: follicular dendritic cell activation
nodes.Definition: A change in the morphology or behavior of a follicular dendritic cell resulting from exposure to an activating factor such as a cellular or soluble ligand.

nodes.label: GO:0006123
nodes.Name: mitochondrial electron transport, cytochrome c to oxygen
nodes.Definition: The transfer of electrons from cytochrome c to oxygen that occurs during oxidative phosphorylation, mediated by the multisubunit enzyme known as complex IV.

nodes.label: GO:0022904
nodes.Name: respiratory electron transport chain
nodes.Definition: A process in which a series of electron carriers operate together to transfer electrons from donors such as NADH and FADH2 to any of several different terminal electron acceptors to generate a transmembrane electrochemical gradient.

nodes.label: GO:0004156
nodes.Name: dihydropteroate synthase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 2-amino-4-hydroxy-6-hydroxymethyl-7,8-dihydropteridine diphosphate + 4-aminobenzoate = diphosphate + dihydropteroate.

nodes.label: GO:0046524
nodes.Name: sucrose-phosphate synthase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: UDP-glucose + D-fructose 6-phosphate = UDP + sucrose 6-phosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0097006
nodes.Name: regulation of plasma lipoprotein particle levels
nodes.Definition: Any process involved in the maintenance of internal levels of plasma lipoprotein particles within an organism.

nodes.label: GO:0030844
nodes.Name: positive regulation of intermediate filament depolymerization
nodes.Definition: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of intermediate filament depolymerization.

nodes.label: GO:1901881
nodes.Name: positive regulation of protein depolymerization
nodes.Definition: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of protein depolymerization.

nodes.label: GO:0043050
nodes.Name: nematode pharyngeal pumping
nodes.Definition: The contraction and relaxation movements of the pharyngeal muscle that mediate feeding in nematodes.

nodes.label: GO:0043051
nodes.Name: regulation of nematode pharyngeal pumping
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the contraction and relaxation movements of the pharyngeal muscle that mediates feeding in nematodes.

nodes.label: GO:0051401
nodes.Name: CH domain binding
nodes.Definition: Binding to a calponin homology protein domain, a domain of 100 residues that occurs in signaling and cytoskeletal proteins.

nodes.label: GO:0005602
nodes.Name: complement component C1 complex
nodes.Definition: A protein complex composed of six subunits of C1q, each formed of the three homologous polypeptide chains C1QA, C1QB, and C1QB, and tetramer of two C1QR and two C1QS polypeptide chains.

nodes.label: GO:0061245
nodes.Name: establishment or maintenance of bipolar cell polarity
nodes.Definition: Any cellular process that results in the specification, formation or maintenance of a bipolar intracellular organization or cell growth patterns.

nodes.label: GO:0016903
nodes.Name: oxidoreductase activity, acting on the aldehyde or oxo group of donors
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which an aldehyde or ketone (oxo) group acts as a hydrogen or electron donor and reduces a hydrogen or electron acceptor.

nodes.label: GO:0047770
nodes.Name: carboxylate reductase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: an aldehyde + acceptor + H2O = a carboxylate + reduced acceptor.

nodes.label: GO:0051763
nodes.Name: sesquiterpene catabolic process
nodes.Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of sesquiterpenes, any of a class of terpenes of the formula C15H24 or a derivative of such a terpene.

nodes.label: GO:0014898
nodes.Name: cardiac muscle hypertrophy in response to stress
nodes.Definition: The physiological enlargement or overgrowth of all or part of the heart muscle due to an increase in size (not length) of individual cardiac muscle fibers, without cell division, as a result of a disturbance in organismal or cellular homeostasis.

nodes.label: GO:0097192
nodes.Name: extrinsic apoptotic signaling pathway in absence of ligand
nodes.Definition: The series of molecular signals in which a signal is conveyed from the cell surface to trigger the apoptotic death of a cell. The pathway starts with withdrawal of a ligand from a cell surface receptor, and ends when the execution phase of apoptosis is triggered.

nodes.label: GO:2001241
nodes.Name: positive regulation of extrinsic apoptotic signaling pathway in absence of ligand
nodes.Definition: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of extrinsic apoptotic signaling pathway in absence of ligand.

nodes.label: GO:0080167
nodes.Name: response to karrikin
nodes.Definition: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a karrikin stimulus. Karrikins are signaling molecules in smoke from burning vegetation that trigger seed germination for many angiosperms (flowering plants).

nodes.label: GO:1900234
nodes.Name: regulation of Kit signaling pathway
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of Kit signaling pathway.

nodes.label: GO:1900235
nodes.Name: negative regulation of Kit signaling pathway
nodes.Definition: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of Kit signaling pathway.

nodes.label: GO:0008624
nodes.Name: apoptotic signaling pathway
nodes.Definition: The series of molecular signals which triggers the apoptotic death of a cell. The pathway starts with reception of a signal, and ends when the execution phase of apoptosis is triggered.

nodes.label: GO:2001233
nodes.Name: regulation of apoptotic signaling pathway
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of apoptotic signaling pathway.

nodes.label: GO:2001267
nodes.Name: regulation of cysteine-type endopeptidase activity involved in apoptotic signaling pathway
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cysteine-type endopeptidase activity involved in apoptotic signaling pathway.

nodes.label: GO:1901172
nodes.Name: phytoene metabolic process
nodes.Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways involving phytoene.

nodes.label: GO:1901173
nodes.Name: phytoene catabolic process
nodes.Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of phytoene.

nodes.label: GO:0042692
nodes.Name: muscle cell differentiation
nodes.Definition: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a muscle cell.

nodes.label: GO:0051145
nodes.Name: smooth muscle cell differentiation
nodes.Definition: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a smooth muscle cell; smooth muscle lacks transverse striations in its constituent fibers and are almost always involuntary.

nodes.label: GO:0034109
nodes.Name: homotypic cell-cell adhesion
nodes.Definition: The attachment of a cell to a second cell of the identical type via adhesion molecules.

nodes.label: GO:0070527
nodes.Name: platelet aggregation
nodes.Definition: The adhesion of one platelet to one or more other platelets via adhesion molecules.

nodes.label: GO:0003277
nodes.Name: apoptotic process involved in endocardial cushion morphogenesis
nodes.Definition: Any apoptotic process that contributes to the shaping of an endocardial cushion. The endocardial cushion is a specialized region of mesenchymal cells that will give rise to the heart septa and valves.

nodes.label: GO:0003278
nodes.Name: apoptotic process involved in heart morphogenesis
nodes.Definition: Any apoptotic process that contributes to the shaping of the heart.

nodes.label: GO:0032945
nodes.Name: negative regulation of mononuclear cell proliferation
nodes.Definition: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of mononuclear cell proliferation.

nodes.label: GO:0065006
nodes.Name: protein glycosylation
nodes.Definition: A protein modification process that results in the addition of a carbohydrate or carbohydrate derivative unit to a protein amino acid, e.g. the addition of glycan chains to proteins.

nodes.label: GO:0019815
nodes.Name: B cell receptor complex
nodes.Definition: An immunoglobulin complex that is present in the plasma membrane of B cells and that in its canonical form is composed of two identical immunoglobulin heavy chains and two identical immunoglobulin light chains and a signaling subunit, a heterodimer of the Ig-alpha and Ig-beta proteins.

nodes.label: GO:0046646
nodes.Name: regulation of gamma-delta T cell proliferation
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of gamma-delta T cell proliferation.

nodes.label: GO:0046647
nodes.Name: negative regulation of gamma-delta T cell proliferation
nodes.Definition: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of gamma-delta T cell proliferation.

nodes.label: GO:0070101
nodes.Name: positive regulation of chemokine-mediated signaling pathway
nodes.Definition: Any process that increases the rate, frequency or extent of a chemokine-mediated signaling pathway.

nodes.label: GO:1903082
nodes.Name: positive regulation of C-C chemokine receptor CCR7 signaling pathway
nodes.Definition: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of C-C chemokine receptor CCR7 signaling pathway.

nodes.label: GO:0006138
nodes.Name: aerobic electron transport chain
nodes.Definition: A process in which a series of electron carriers operate together to transfer electrons from donors such as NADH and FADH2 to oxygen to generate a transmembrane electrochemical gradient.

nodes.label: GO:0019646
nodes.Name: aerobic electron transport chain
nodes.Definition: A process in which a series of electron carriers operate together to transfer electrons from donors such as NADH and FADH2 to oxygen to generate a transmembrane electrochemical gradient.

nodes.label: GO:0045214
nodes.Name: sarcomere organization
nodes.Definition: The myofibril assembly process that results in the organization of muscle actomyosin into sarcomeres. The sarcomere is the repeating unit of a myofibril in a muscle cell, composed of an array of overlapping thick and thin filaments between two adjacent Z discs.

nodes.label: GO:0060299
nodes.Name: negative regulation of sarcomere organization
nodes.Definition: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of myofibril assembly by organization of muscle actomyosin into sarcomeres. The sarcomere is the repeating unit of a myofibril in a muscle cell, composed of an array of overlapping thick and thin filaments between two adjacent Z discs.

nodes.label: GO:0046640
nodes.Name: regulation of alpha-beta T cell proliferation
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of alpha-beta T cell proliferation.

nodes.label: GO:0004901
nodes.Name: granulocyte macrophage colony-stimulating factor receptor activity
nodes.Definition: Combining with granulocyte macrophage colony-stimulating factor (GM-CSF) and transmitting the signal from one side of the membrane to the other to initiate a change in cell activity.

nodes.label: GO:0038157
nodes.Name: granulocyte-macrophage colony-stimulating factor signaling pathway
nodes.Definition: The series of molecular signals initiated by the binding of the cytokine granulocyte macrophage colony-stimulating factor (GM-CSF) to its receptor on the surface of a target cell, and ending with the regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. transcription. GM-CSF binds to a heterodimer receptor (CSF2R) consisting of an alpha ligand-binding subunit, and a common beta subunit that is shared with other cytokine receptors.

nodes.label: GO:0005608
nodes.Name: laminin-3 complex
nodes.Definition: A laminin complex composed of alpha1, beta2 and gamma1 polypeptide chains.

nodes.label: GO:0050457
nodes.Name: decylcitrate synthase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: H2O + lauroyl-CoA + oxaloacetate = (2S,3S)-2-hydroxytridecane-1,2,3-tricarboxylate + CoA + H+.

nodes.label: GO:0004900
nodes.Name: erythropoietin receptor activity
nodes.Definition: Combining with erythropoietin and transmitting the signal from one side of the membrane to the other to initiate a change in cell activity.

nodes.label: GO:0050425
nodes.Name: obsolete carboxypeptidase B activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the reaction: H2O + peptidyl-L-lysine (or L-arginine) = L-lysine (or L-arginine) + peptide. Preferential release of a C-terminal lysine or arginine amino acid.

nodes.label: GO:0060336
nodes.Name: negative regulation of type II interferon-mediated signaling pathway
nodes.Definition: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of an interferon-gamma-mediated signaling pathway.

nodes.label: GO:0050958
nodes.Name: magnetoreception
nodes.Definition: The series of events required for an organism to receive a stimulus relating to a magnetic field, convert it to a molecular signal, and recognize and characterize the signal. Stimuli may be chemical, mechanical or electrical and interpreting these stimuli allows an organism to determine the orientation of a magnetic field. Magnetoreception also involves the perception of light; birds cannot orient without the presence of short wavelength (blue/green) light.

nodes.label: GO:0016759
nodes.Name: cellulose synthase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: nucleoside-disphosphate-glucose + ((1,4)-beta-D-glucosyl)(n) = nucleoside-disphosphate + ((1,4)-beta-D-glucosyl)(n+1).

nodes.label: GO:0016760
nodes.Name: cellulose synthase (UDP-forming) activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: UDP-glucose + ((1,4)-beta-D-glucosyl)(n) = UDP + ((1,4)-beta-D-glucosyl)(n+1).

nodes.label: GO:1902442
nodes.Name: regulation of ripoptosome assembly involved in necroptotic process
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of ripoptosome assembly involved in a necroptotic process.

nodes.label: GO:1902443
nodes.Name: negative regulation of ripoptosome assembly involved in necroptotic process
nodes.Definition: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of ripoptosome assembly involved in a necroptotic process.

nodes.label: GO:0075311
nodes.Name: positive regulation of sporangium development
nodes.Definition: Any process that activates, maintains or increases the frequency, rate or extent of sporangium development, a process that leads to the formation of sporangium, a single-celled or many-celled structure in which spores are produced, as in fungi, algae, mosses, and ferns, gymnosperms, angiosperms.

nodes.label: GO:0075323
nodes.Name: positive regulation of oomycete sporangium development
nodes.Definition: Any process that activates, maintains or increases the frequency, rate or extent of oomycete sporangium development, a process that leads to the formation of oomycete sporangium, a single-celled or many-celled structure that germinates directly to form an infection hypha or differentiate, through specialized cleavage vesicles, into between 10 and 30 zoospores, which is laterally flagellated.

nodes.label: GO:0030217
nodes.Name: T cell differentiation
nodes.Definition: The process in which a precursor cell type acquires characteristics of a more mature T-cell. A T cell is a type of lymphocyte whose definin characteristic is the expression of a T cell receptor complex.

nodes.label: GO:0045581
nodes.Name: negative regulation of T cell differentiation
nodes.Definition: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of T cell differentiation.

nodes.label: GO:0008548
nodes.Name: obsolete signal-recognition-particle GTPase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the reaction: GTP + H2O = GDP + phosphate. Activity is associated with the signal-recognition particle, a protein and RNA-containing structure involved in endoplasmic reticulum-associated protein synthesis.

nodes.label: GO:0033891
nodes.Name: CC-preferring endodeoxyribonuclease activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the endonucleolytic cleavage to give 5'-phosphooligonucleotide end-products, with a preference for cleavage within the sequence CC.

nodes.label: GO:0004381
nodes.Name: fucosylgalactoside 3-alpha-galactosyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: UDP-galactose + glycoprotein-alpha-L-fucosyl-(1,2)-D-galactose = UDP + glycoprotein-alpha-D-galactosyl-(1,3)-(alpha-L-fucosyl-(1,2))-D-galactose.

nodes.label: GO:0055024
nodes.Name: regulation of cardiac muscle tissue development
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cardiac muscle tissue development.

nodes.label: GO:0097200
nodes.Name: cysteine-type endopeptidase activity involved in execution phase of apoptosis
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of internal, alpha-peptide bonds in a polypeptide chain by a mechanism in which the sulfhydryl group of a cysteine residue at the active center acts as a nucleophile, and contributing to the execution phase of apoptosis.

nodes.label: GO:0030043
nodes.Name: actin filament fragmentation
nodes.Definition: The severing of actin filaments into numerous short fragments, usually mediated by actin severing proteins.

nodes.label: GO:0010279
nodes.Name: indole-3-acetic acid amido synthetase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: indole-3-acetic acid + an amino acid = an indole-3-acetic acid amide conjugate.

nodes.label: GO:2000750
nodes.Name: negative regulation of establishment or maintenance of bipolar cell polarity regulating cell shape
nodes.Definition: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of establishment or maintenance of bipolar cell polarity regulating cell shape.

nodes.label: GO:2000770
nodes.Name: negative regulation of establishment or maintenance of cell polarity regulating cell shape
nodes.Definition: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of establishment or maintenance of cell polarity regulating cell shape.

nodes.label: GO:0032537
nodes.Name: host-seeking behavior
nodes.Definition: The specific behavior of an organism that are associated with finding a host organism; may include behavioral responses to light, temperature, or chemical emanations from the prospective host.

nodes.label: GO:0032539
nodes.Name: negative regulation of host-seeking behavior
nodes.Definition: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of any behavior associated with finding a host organism.

nodes.label: GO:0050062
nodes.Name: long-chain-fatty-acyl-CoA reductase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: a long-chain fatty aldehyde + CoA + NADP+ = a long-chain fatty acyl-CoA + NADPH.

nodes.label: GO:0009774
nodes.Name: photosynthetic electron transport chain
nodes.Definition: A process, occurring as part of photosynthesis, in which light provides the energy for a series of electron carriers to operate together to transfer electrons and generate a transmembrane electrochemical gradient.

nodes.label: GO:0004295
nodes.Name: obsolete trypsin activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the preferential cleavage of Arg-Xaa, Lys-Xaa.

nodes.label: GO:0070487
nodes.Name: monocyte aggregation
nodes.Definition: The adhesion of one monocyte to one or more other monocytes via adhesion molecules.

nodes.label: GO:1900624
nodes.Name: negative regulation of monocyte aggregation
nodes.Definition: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of monocyte aggregation.

nodes.label: GO:0004485
nodes.Name: methylcrotonoyl-CoA carboxylase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 3-methylbut-2-enoyl-CoA + ATP + bicarbonate = trans-3-methylglutaconyl-CoA + ADP + 2 H+ + phosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0016421
nodes.Name: CoA carboxylase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the joining of a carboxyl group to a molecule that is attached to CoA, with the concomitant hydrolysis of the diphosphate bond in ATP or a similar triphosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0043052
nodes.Name: thermotaxis
nodes.Definition: The directed movement of a motile cell or organism in response to a temperature gradient. Movement may be towards either a higher or lower temperature.

nodes.label: GO:0043368
nodes.Name: positive T cell selection
nodes.Definition: The process of sparing immature T cells which react with self-MHC protein complexes with low affinity levels from apoptotic death.

nodes.label: GO:0045059
nodes.Name: positive thymic T cell selection
nodes.Definition: The process of sparing immature T cells in the thymus which react with self-MHC protein complexes with low affinity levels from apoptotic death.

nodes.label: GO:0004643
nodes.Name: phosphoribosylaminoimidazolecarboxamide formyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 10-formyltetrahydrofolate + 5'-phosphoribosyl-5-amino-4-imidazolecarboxamide = tetrahydrofolate + 5'-phosphoribosyl-5-formamido-4-imidazolecarboxamide.

nodes.label: GO:0016742
nodes.Name: hydroxymethyl-, formyl- and related transferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the transfer of a hydroxymethyl- or formyl group from one compound (donor) to another (acceptor).

nodes.label: GO:0016621
nodes.Name: cinnamoyl-CoA reductase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: cinnamaldehyde + CoA + NADP+ = cinnamoyl-CoA + NADPH + H+.

nodes.label: GO:0043206
nodes.Name: supramolecular fiber organization
nodes.Definition: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a supramolecular fiber, a polymer consisting of an indefinite number of protein or protein complex subunits that have polymerised to form a fiber-shaped structure.

nodes.label: GO:0004200
nodes.Name: obsolete signaling (initiator) caspase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. (Was not defined before being made obsolete).

nodes.label: GO:0008717
nodes.Name: obsolete D-alanyl-D-alanine endopeptidase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. (Was not defined before being made obsolete).

nodes.label: GO:1904606
nodes.Name: fat cell apoptotic process
nodes.Definition: Any apoptotic process in a fat cell.

nodes.label: GO:0047705
nodes.Name: bilirubin oxidase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 2 bilirubin + O2 = 2 biliverdin + 2 H2O.

nodes.label: GO:0052623
nodes.Name: obsolete ADP dimethylallyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the reaction: delta2-isopentenyl diphosphate + ADP = diphosphate + N6-(delta(2)-isopentenyl)adenosine 5'-diphosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0050487
nodes.Name: sulfoacetaldehyde acetyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: acetyl phosphate + H+ + sulfite = phosphate + sulfoacetaldehyde.

nodes.label: GO:0030239
nodes.Name: myofibril assembly
nodes.Definition: Formation of myofibrils, the repeating units of striated muscle.

nodes.label: GO:0055003
nodes.Name: cardiac myofibril assembly
nodes.Definition: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the cardiac myofibril over time, from its formation to the mature structure. A cardiac myofibril is a myofibril specific to cardiac muscle cells.

nodes.label: GO:0008345
nodes.Name: larval locomotory behavior
nodes.Definition: Locomotory behavior in a larval (immature) organism.

nodes.label: GO:0030537
nodes.Name: larval behavior
nodes.Definition: Behavior in a larval form of an organism, an immature organism that must undergo metamorphosis to assume adult characteristics.

nodes.label: GO:0043582
nodes.Name: sporangium development
nodes.Definition: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the sporangium over time, from its formation to the mature structure. A sporangium is a structure producing and containing spores.

nodes.label: GO:0075310
nodes.Name: regulation of sporangium development
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of sporangium development, a process that leads to the formation of sporangium, a single-celled or many-celled structure in which spores are produced, as in fungi, algae, mosses, and ferns, gymnosperms, angiosperms.

nodes.label: GO:1904651
nodes.Name: positive regulation of fat cell apoptotic process
nodes.Definition: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of fat cell apoptotic process.

nodes.label: GO:0031644
nodes.Name: regulation of nervous system process
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a neurophysiological process, an organ system process carried out by any of the organs or tissues of the nervous system.

nodes.label: GO:0031646
nodes.Name: positive regulation of nervous system process
nodes.Definition: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of a neurophysiological process.

nodes.label: GO:0075235
nodes.Name: obsolete modulation of zoospore movement on or near host
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of zoospore movement on or near host. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

nodes.label: GO:0075237
nodes.Name: obsolete obsolete negative regulation of zoospore movement on or near host
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. OBSOLETE. Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of zoospore movement on or near its host organism. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

nodes.label: GO:2000855
nodes.Name: regulation of mineralocorticoid secretion
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of mineralocorticoid secretion.

nodes.label: GO:2000858
nodes.Name: regulation of aldosterone secretion
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of aldosterone secretion.

nodes.label: GO:0060537
nodes.Name: muscle tissue development
nodes.Definition: The progression of muscle tissue over time, from its initial formation to its mature state. Muscle tissue is a contractile tissue made up of actin and myosin fibers.

nodes.label: GO:1901862
nodes.Name: negative regulation of muscle tissue development
nodes.Definition: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of muscle tissue development.

nodes.label: GO:0035455
nodes.Name: response to interferon-alpha
nodes.Definition: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an interferon-alpha stimulus. Interferon-alpha is a type I interferon.

nodes.label: GO:0016336
nodes.Name: establishment or maintenance of polarity of larval imaginal disc epithelium
nodes.Definition: Any cellular process that results in the specification, formation or maintenance of a polarized larval imaginal disc epithelium.

nodes.label: GO:0042251
nodes.Name: maintenance of polarity of larval imaginal disc epithelium

nodes.label: GO:0035895

nodes.Definition: Any process in which an organism modulates the frequency, rate or extent of blood mast cell degranulation in another organism. nodes.label: GO:0097343

The composition of this protein complex may depend on several factors including nature of the signal, cell type and more.

nodes.label: GO:1901026

nodes.label: GO:0034111

nodes.label: GO:0043400

nodes.label: GO:0075071

nodes.label: GO:0070663

nodes.label: GO:0034358

nodes.Definition: A spherical particle with a hydrophobic core of triglycerides and/or cholesterol esters, surrounded by an amphipathic monolayer of phospholipids, cholesterol and apolipoproteins. Plasma lipoprotein particles transport lipids, which are non-covalently associated with the particles, in the blood or lymph.

nodes.Definition: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a muscle cell over time, from its formation to the mature structure. Muscle cell development does not include the steps involved in committing an unspecified cell to the muscle cell fate.

nodes.label: GO:0014719
nodes.Name: skeletal muscle satellite cell activation
nodes.Definition: The change of a skeletal muscle satellite cell from a mitotically quiescent to a mitotically active state following exposure to some activating factor such as a cellular or soluble ligand. In adult muscle, satellite cells become activated to divide and differentiate in response to muscle damage.

nodes.label: GO:0014901
nodes.Name: satellite cell activation involved in skeletal muscle regeneration
nodes.Definition: The process that initiates skeletal muscle satellite cell division by causing it to move from quiescence to the G1 stage of the cell cycle. The cell swells and there are a number of other small changes. The cells then start to divide. Following cell division the cells will differentiate. In adult muscle, satellite cells become activated to divide and differentiate in response to muscle damage.

nodes.label: GO:0044138
nodes.Name: obsolete modulation of development of symbiont on or near host
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Any process in which the symbiont regulates its progression from an initial condition to a later condition, on or near the cells or tissues of the host organism.

nodes.label: GO:0043514
nodes.Name: interleukin-12 complex
nodes.Definition: A protein complex that is composed of an interleukin-12 alpha (p35, product of the IL12A gene) and an interleukin-12 beta subunit (p40, product of the IL12B gene) and is secreted into the extracellular space.

nodes.label: GO:0051016
nodes.Name: barbed-end actin filament capping

nodes.label: GO:2000812

nodes.label: GO:0008002

nodes.label: GO:0075058
nodes.Name: modulation of penetration peg formation
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of symbiont penetration peg formation for entry into host. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

nodes.label: GO:0075060

nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of symbiont penetration peg formation for entry into host. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

nodes.label: GO:0045938
nodes.Name: positive regulation of circadian sleep/wake cycle, sleep
nodes.Definition: Any process that activates or increases the duration or quality of sleep, a readily reversible state of reduced awareness and metabolic activity that occurs periodically in many animals.

nodes.label: GO:0050802
nodes.Name: circadian sleep/wake cycle, sleep
nodes.Definition: The part of the circadian sleep/wake cycle where the organism is asleep.

nodes.label: GO:0034916

nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the reaction: 2-methylhexanoyl-CoA = 2-methylhex-2-enoyl-CoA + 2 H+ + e-.

nodes.label: GO:0043069
nodes.Name: negative regulation of programmed cell death

nodes.label: GO:0060546
nodes.Name: negative regulation of necroptotic process
nodes.Definition: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of a necroptotic process, a necrotic cell death process that results from the activation of endogenous cellular processes, such as signaling involving death domain receptors or Toll-like receptors.

nodes.label: GO:0044521
nodes.Name: envenomation resulting in muscle damage in another organism
nodes.Definition: A process that begins with venom being forced into an organism by the bite or sting of another organism, and ends with resultant muscle damage in the bitten organism.

nodes.label: GO:0006970

nodes.label: GO:0071470
nodes.Name: cellular response to osmotic stress
nodes.Definition: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a stimulus indicating an increase or decrease in the concentration of solutes outside the organism or cell.

nodes.Definition: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of detection of, or exposure to, a hyperosmotic environment, i.e. an environment with a higher concentration of solutes than the organism or cell.

nodes.label: GO:0001959

nodes.label: GO:0033084

nodes.label: GO:0070105

nodes.label: GO:0007577
nodes.Name: obsolete autophagic death (sensu Saccharomyces)
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. This process is a type of programmed cell death pathway similar to apoptosis and necrosis observed in multicellular organisms. It is characterized by cellular enlargement (necrosis) and presence of many autophagic bodies along with degradation of cellular components (nucleus, Golgi, ER), protein, DNA and RNA.

nodes.label: GO:0048102
nodes.Name: autophagic cell death
nodes.Definition: A form of programmed cell death that is accompanied by the formation of autophagosomes. Autophagic cell death is characterized by lack of chromatin condensation and massive vacuolization of the cytoplasm, with little or no uptake by phagocytic cells.

nodes.label: GO:0005583
nodes.Name: fibrillar collagen trimer
nodes.Definition: Any triple helical collagen trimer that forms fibrils.

nodes.label: GO:0005584
nodes.Name: collagen type I trimer
nodes.Definition: A collagen trimer containing alpha(I) chains. The most common form of type I collagen is a heterotrimer containing two alpha1(I) chains and one alpha2(I) chain; homotrimers containing three alpha1(I) chains are also found. Type I collagen triple helices associate to form banded fibrils.

nodes.label: GO:0004659

nodes.label: GO:0009582

nodes.label: GO:0043944

nodes.label: GO:0075288
nodes.Name: negative regulation of sporangiospore formation
nodes.Definition: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of sporangiospore formation, a process in which sporangiospores, a type of asexual spore found in fungi, are formed. Sporangiospores are formed within sac-like structure, the sporangium, following the division of the cytoplasm.

nodes.label: GO:0042102

nodes.label: GO:0043525

nodes.label: GO:0075261

nodes.Definition: Any process that activates, maintains or increases the frequency, rate or extent of spore-bearing organ development, a process in which hyphae grow into special aggregates called fruiting bodies that produce new spores.

nodes.label: GO:0075319
nodes.Name: positive regulation of ascus development
nodes.Definition: Any process that activates, maintains or increases the frequency, rate or extent of ascus development, a saclike structure produced by fungi of the phylum Ascomycota (sac fungi) in which sexually produced spores (ascospores), usually four or eight in number, are formed.

nodes.label: GO:0043509

nodes.Definition: A nonsteroidal regulator, composed of two covalently linked inhibin beta-A subunits (sometimes known as activin beta-A or activin/inhibin beta-A).

nodes.label: GO:0048180

nodes.Definition: A nonsteroidal regulator, composed of two covalently linked inhibin beta subunits, inhibin beta-A and inhibin beta-B (sometimes known as activin beta or activin/inhibin beta). There are three forms of activin complex, activin A, which is composed of 2 inhibin beta-A subunits, activin B, which is composed of 2 inhibin beta-B subunits, and activin AB, which is composed of an inhibin beta-A and an inhibin beta-B subunit.

nodes.label: GO:0014900

nodes.label: GO:0048772

nodes.Definition: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires the specialized features of a leucophore cell. Leucophores are pigment cells derived from the neural crest. They contain uric acid or other purine crystals, deposited in stacks called leucosomes. This gives them a white appearance.

nodes.label: GO:0048776
