nodes.Definition: The directed movement of DNA from an organism to a location inside its host organism. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

nodes.label: GO:0051837
nodes.Name: translocation of DNA into host
nodes.Definition: The directed movement of DNA from an organism to a location inside its host organism. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

nodes.label: GO:0048774
nodes.Name: cyanophore differentiation
nodes.Definition: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires the specialized features of a cyanophore cell. Cyanophores are pigment cells derived from the neural crest. They contain a blue pigment of unknown chemical composition. The pigment is stored in fibrous organelles termed cyanosomes.

nodes.label: GO:0048781

nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of low-density lipoprotein particle clearance. nodes.label: GO:0010017
nodes.Name: red or far-red light signaling pathway
nodes.Definition: The series of molecular signals initiated upon sensing by photoreceptor molecules of red light or far red light. Red light is electromagnetic radiation of wavelength of 580-700nm. Far red light is electromagnetic radiation of wavelength 700-800nm. An example of this response is seen at the beginning of many plant species developmental stages. These include germination, and the point when cotyledon expansion is triggered. In certain species these processes take place in response to absorption of red light by the pigment molecule phytochrome, but the signal can be reversed by exposure to far red light. During the initial phase the phytochrome molecule is only present in the red light absorbing form, but on absorption of red light it changes to a far red light absorbing form, triggering progress through development. An immediate short period of exposure to far red light entirely returns the pigment to its initial state and prevents triggering of the developmental process. A thirty minute break between red and subsequent far red light exposure renders the red light effect irreversible, and development then occurs regardless of whether far red light exposure subsequently occurs.

nodes.label: GO:0004216

nodes.label: GO:0044542

nodes.Definition: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of ascus development, a saclike structure produced by fungi of the phylum Ascomycota (sac fungi) in which sexually produced spores (ascospores), usually four or eight in number, are formed.

nodes.label: GO:0007115

nodes.label: GO:0009612

nodes.label: GO:0009652

nodes.label: GO:0014727
nodes.Name: positive regulation of extraocular skeletal muscle development
nodes.Definition: Any process that activates, maintains or increases the frequency, rate or extent of extraocular skeletal muscle development. The extraocular muscle is derived from cranial mesoderm and controls eye movements. The muscle begins its development with the differentiation of the muscle cells and ends with the mature muscle.

nodes.label: GO:0048643

nodes.label: GO:0075028

nodes.label: GO:0075032

nodes.label: GO:0034728

nodes.label: GO:0075024

nodes.label: GO:0006972

nodes.label: GO:0042538

nodes.Definition: The physiological, developmental and morphological changes that occur in a symbiont spore during the process of its encystment. Encystment means to enter a state of essentially suspended animation in which the spore is protected by an outer coating and remains immobile and inactive until favorable conditions for growth occur again. Light reactions also generate a proton motive force across the thylakoid membrane, and the proton gradient is used to synthesize ATP. There are two chemical reactions involved in the light reactions: water oxidation in photosystem II, and NADP reduction in photosystem I.

nodes.Name: interleukin-1 receptor activity
nodes.Definition: Combining with interleukin-1 to initiate a change in cell activity. Interleukin-1 is produced mainly by activated macrophages and is involved in the inflammatory response.

nodes.label: GO:0018721
nodes.Name: obsolete trans-9R,10R-dihydrodiolphenanthrene sulfotransferase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the reaction: trans-9R,10R-dihydrodiolphenanthrene + 2 X-SO3(-) = 2 HX + phenanthrene-9,10-dihydrodiolsulfate conjugate.

nodes.label: GO:0047529
nodes.Name: 2,3-dimethylmalate lyase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: (2R,3S)-2,3-dimethylmalate = propanoate + pyruvate.

nodes.label: GO:0001410
nodes.Name: chlamydospore formation
nodes.Definition: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the chlamydospore over time, from its formation to the mature structure. A chlamydospores is a mitotic (asexual) one-celled spore, produced primarily for survival, not dispersal, originating endogenously and singly within part of a pre-existing cell and possessing an inner secondary and often thickened cell wall. An example of this is found in Candida albicans.

nodes.label: GO:0042322
nodes.Name: negative regulation of circadian sleep/wake cycle, REM sleep
nodes.Definition: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the duration or quality of rapid eye movement (REM) sleep.

nodes.label: GO:0042747
nodes.Name: circadian sleep/wake cycle, REM sleep
nodes.Definition: A stage in the circadian sleep cycle during which dreams occur and the body undergoes marked changes including rapid eye movement, loss of reflexes, and increased pulse rate and brain activity.

nodes.label: GO:0075059
nodes.Name: positive regulation of penetration peg formation
nodes.Definition: Any process that activates, maintains or increases the frequency, rate or extent of symbiont penetration peg formation for entry into host. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

nodes.label: GO:0071760
nodes.Name: IgY immunoglobulin complex
nodes.Definition: A protein complex composed of two identical immunoglobulin heavy chains of the IgY isotype and two identical immunoglobulin light chains, held together by disulfide bonds. An IgY immunoglobulin complex may be embedded in the plasma membrane or present in the extracellular space, in mucosal areas or other tissues, or circulating in the blood or lymph.

nodes.label: GO:0005582
nodes.Name: collagen type XV trimer
nodes.Definition: A collagen homotrimer of alpha1(XV) chains; a chondroitin sulfate proteoglycan often found in specialized basement membranes where it bridges between fibrils.

nodes.label: GO:0004866
nodes.Name: endopeptidase inhibitor activity
nodes.Definition: Binds to and stops, prevents or reduces the activity of an endopeptidase.

nodes.label: GO:0008539
nodes.Name: obsolete proteasome inhibitor activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Stops, prevents or reduces the activity of the proteasome complex. The proteasome complex performs regulated ubiquitin-dependent cytosolic and nuclear proteolysis.

nodes.label: GO:0004243
nodes.Name: obsolete mitochondrial intermediate peptidase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the release of an N-terminal octapeptide as second stage of processing of some proteins imported in the mitochondrion.

nodes.label: GO:0008133
nodes.Name: obsolete collagenase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Was not defined before being made obsolete.

nodes.label: GO:0047281
nodes.Name: dioxotetrahydropyrimidine phosphoribosyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: pyrophosphate + a 2,4-dioxotetrahydropyrimidine D-ribonucleotide = PRPP + a 2,4-dioxotetrahydropyrimidine.

nodes.label: GO:0075259
nodes.Name: spore-bearing structure development
nodes.Definition: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a spore-bearing structure over time, from its formation to the mature structure. A spore-bearing structure is an anatomical structure that produces new spores.

nodes.label: GO:0075279
nodes.Name: uredinium development
nodes.Definition: The process that leads to the formation of a uredinium, a reddish, pustule-like structure formed by a rust fungus and consisting of uredospores.

nodes.label: GO:0032027
nodes.Name: myosin light chain binding
nodes.Definition: Binding to a light chain of a myosin complex.

nodes.label: GO:0032033
nodes.Name: myosin II light chain binding
nodes.Definition: Binding to a light chain of a myosin II complex.

nodes.label: GO:0001116
nodes.Name: protein-DNA-RNA complex assembly
nodes.Definition: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of proteins, DNA, and RNA molecules to form a protein-DNA-RNA complex.

nodes.label: GO:0014714
nodes.Name: myoblast fate commitment in head
nodes.Definition: The process, taking place in the head, whereby the developmental fate of a cell becomes restricted such that it will develop into a myoblast. A myoblast is a mononucleate cell type that, by fusion with other myoblasts, gives rise to the myotubes that eventually develop into skeletal muscle fibers.

nodes.label: GO:1900280
nodes.Name: negative regulation of CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell costimulation
nodes.Definition: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell costimulation.

nodes.label: GO:0033087
nodes.Name: negative regulation of immature T cell proliferation
nodes.Definition: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of immature T cell proliferation.

nodes.label: GO:0008894
nodes.Name: guanosine-5'-triphosphate,3'-diphosphate diphosphatase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: guanosine 5'-triphosphate,3'-diphosphate + H2O = guanosine 5'-diphosphate,3'-diphosphate + phosphate.

nodes.label: GO:1904634
nodes.Name: negative regulation of podocyte apoptotic process
nodes.Definition: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of glomerular visceral epithelial cell apoptotic process.

nodes.label: GO:0052759
nodes.Name: obsolete coenzyme F420-dependent 2,4,6-trinitrophenol hydride reductase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the reaction: trinitrophenol hydride Meisenheimer complex + H- = trinitrophenol dihydride Meisenheimer complex (aci form). Coenzyme F420 supplies the hydride (H-) in the reaction.

nodes.label: GO:0004813
nodes.Name: alanine-tRNA ligase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + L-alanine + tRNA(Ala) = AMP + diphosphate + L-alanyl-tRNA(Ala).

nodes.label: GO:0048641
nodes.Name: regulation of skeletal muscle tissue development
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of skeletal muscle tissue development.

nodes.label: GO:0017095
nodes.Name: heparan sulfate 6-O-sulfotransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 3'-phosphoadenosine 5'-phosphosulfate + heparan sulfate = adenosine 3',5'-bisphosphate + heparan sulfate 6-O-sulfate; results in 6-O-sulfation of glucosamine residues in heparan sulfate.

nodes.label: GO:0072674
nodes.Name: multinuclear osteoclast differentiation
nodes.Definition: The process in which a relatively unspecialized monocyte acquires the specialized features of a multinuclear osteoclast. An osteoclast is a specialized phagocytic cell associated with the absorption and removal of the mineralized matrix of bone tissue.

nodes.label: GO:0072675
nodes.Name: osteoclast fusion
nodes.Definition: The plasma membrane fusion process that results in fusion of mononuclear osteoclasts to form a multinuclear osteoclast.

nodes.label: GO:0005592
nodes.Name: collagen type XI trimer
nodes.Definition: A collagen heterotrimer containing type XI alpha chains in alpha1(XI)alpha2(XI)alpha3(XI) trimers; type XI collagen triple helices associate to form fibrils.

nodes.label: GO:0008472
nodes.Name: obsolete metallocarboxypeptidase D activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the reaction: peptidyl-L-lysine (or peptidyl-L-arginine) + H2O = peptide + L-lysine (or L-arginine). Function is activated by Co2+; inhibited by guanidinoethylmercaptosuccinic acid.

nodes.label: GO:0035456
nodes.Name: response to interferon-beta
nodes.Definition: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an interferon-beta stimulus. Interferon-beta is a type I interferon.

nodes.label: GO:0035458
nodes.Name: cellular response to interferon-beta
nodes.Definition: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an interferon-beta stimulus. Interferon-beta is a type I interferon.

nodes.label: GO:0097269
nodes.Name: all-trans-decaprenyl-diphosphate synthase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 2-trans,6-trans-farnesyl diphosphate + 7 isopentenyl diphosphate = 7 diphosphate + all-trans-decaprenyl diphosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0030330
nodes.Name: DNA damage response, signal transduction by p53 class mediator
nodes.Definition: A cascade of processes induced by the cell cycle regulator phosphoprotein p53, or an equivalent protein, in response to the detection of DNA damage.

nodes.label: GO:0043516
nodes.Name: regulation of DNA damage response, signal transduction by p53 class mediator
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the cascade of processes induced by the cell cycle regulator phosphoprotein p53, or an equivalent protein, in response to the detection of DNA damage.

nodes.label: GO:0016636
nodes.Name: oxidoreductase activity, acting on the CH-CH group of donors, iron-sulfur protein as acceptor
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which a CH-CH group acts as a hydrogen or electron donor and reduces an iron-sulfur protein.

nodes.label: GO:0050617
nodes.Name: 15,16-dihydrobiliverdin:ferredoxin oxidoreductase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 15,16-dihydrobiliverdin + oxidized ferredoxin = biliverdin IXa + reduced ferredoxin.

nodes.label: GO:0014816
nodes.Name: skeletal muscle satellite cell differentiation
nodes.Definition: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a satellite cell.

nodes.label: GO:1902232
nodes.Name: regulation of positive thymic T cell selection
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of positive thymic T cell selection.

nodes.label: GO:1902233
nodes.Name: negative regulation of positive thymic T cell selection
nodes.Definition: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of positive thymic T cell selection.

nodes.label: GO:0010165
nodes.Name: response to X-ray
nodes.Definition: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of X-ray radiation. An X-ray is a form of electromagnetic radiation with a wavelength in the range of 10 nanometers to 100 picometers (corresponding to frequencies in the range 30 PHz to 3 EHz).

nodes.label: GO:0010212
nodes.Name: response to ionizing radiation
nodes.Definition: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a ionizing radiation stimulus. Ionizing radiation is radiation with sufficient energy to remove electrons from atoms and may arise from spontaneous decay of unstable isotopes, resulting in alpha and beta particles and gamma rays. Ionizing radiation also includes X-rays.

nodes.label: GO:0071965
nodes.Name: multicellular organismal locomotion
nodes.Definition: Locomotion in a multicellular organism, i.e. self-propelled movement of a multicellular organism from one location to another.

nodes.label: GO:0033073
nodes.Name: pinene metabolic process
nodes.Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways involving the monoterpenoid pinene; alpha-pinene is (1S,5S)-2,6,6-trimethylbicyclo[3.1.1]hept-2-ene, and beta-pinene is (1S,5S)-6,6-dimethyl-2-methylenebicyclo[3.1.1]heptane.

nodes.label: GO:0098756
nodes.Name: response to interleukin-21
nodes.Definition: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an interleukin-21 stimulus.

nodes.label: GO:0098757
nodes.Name: cellular response to interleukin-21
nodes.Definition: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an interleukin-21 stimulus.

nodes.label: GO:0048741
nodes.Name: skeletal muscle fiber development
nodes.Definition: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the skeletal muscle fiber over time, from its formation to the mature structure. Muscle fibers are formed by the maturation of myotubes. They can be classed as slow, intermediate/fast or fast.

nodes.label: GO:0048747
nodes.Name: muscle cell development
nodes.Definition: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a muscle cell over time, from its formation to the mature structure. Muscle cell development does not include the steps involved in committing an unspecified cell to the muscle cell fate.

nodes.label: GO:0008755
nodes.Name: O antigen polymerase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the polymerization of o-antigen chains. O-antigens are tetra- and pentasaccharide repeat units of the cell walls of Gram-negative bacteria and are a component of lipopolysaccharide.

nodes.label: GO:0016154
nodes.Name: pyrimidine-nucleoside phosphorylase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: pyrimidine nucleoside + phosphate = pyrimidine + alpha-D-ribose 1-phosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0050362
nodes.Name: L-tryptophan:2-oxoglutarate aminotransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: L-tryptophan + 2-oxoglutarate = indolepyruvate + L-glutamate.

nodes.label: GO:0010994
nodes.Name: free ubiquitin chain polymerization
nodes.Definition: The process of creating free ubiquitin chains, compounds composed of a large number of ubiquitin monomers. These chains are not conjugated to a protein.

nodes.label: GO:1904543
nodes.Name: negative regulation of free ubiquitin chain polymerization
nodes.Definition: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of free ubiquitin chain polymerization.

nodes.label: GO:0047286
nodes.Name: NAD+-diphthamide ADP-ribosyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: peptide diphthamide + NAD+ = peptide N-(ADP-D-ribosyl)diphthamide + niacinamide.

nodes.label: GO:0042576
nodes.Name: obsolete aspartyl aminopeptidase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the release of an N-terminal aspartate or glutamate from a peptide, with a preference for aspartate.

nodes.label: GO:1901216
nodes.Name: obsolete positive regulation of neuron death
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of neuron death.

nodes.label: GO:0035794
nodes.Name: positive regulation of mitochondrial membrane permeability
nodes.Definition: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of the passage or uptake of molecules by the mitochondrial membrane.

nodes.label: GO:1902686
nodes.Name: mitochondrial outer membrane permeabilization involved in programmed cell death
nodes.Definition: The process by which the mitochondrial outer membrane becomes permeable to the passing of proteins and other molecules from the intermembrane space to the cytosol as part of a programmed cell death process.

nodes.label: GO:0097081
nodes.Name: vascular associated smooth muscle cell fate commitment
nodes.Definition: The commitment of cells to a vascular smooth muscle cell fate and their capacity to differentiate into vascular smooth muscle cells. A vascular smooth muscle cell is a non-striated, elongated, spindle-shaped cell found lining the blood vessels.

nodes.label: GO:0097082
nodes.Name: vascular associated smooth muscle cell fate specification
nodes.Definition: The process in which a cell becomes capable of differentiating autonomously into a vascular smooth muscle cell in an environment that is neutral with respect to the developmental pathway. Upon specification, the cell fate can be reversed. A vascular smooth muscle cell is a non-striated, elongated, spindle-shaped cell found lining the blood vessels.

nodes.label: GO:0033734
nodes.Name: (R)-benzylsuccinyl-CoA dehydrogenase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: (R)-2-benzylsuccinyl-CoA + 2 electron-transferring flavoprotein = (E)-2-benzylidenesuccinyl-CoA + 2 reduced electron-transferring flavoprotein.

nodes.label: GO:0035177
nodes.Name: larval foraging behavior
nodes.Definition: The movement of a larva through a feeding substrate whilst feeding on food.

nodes.label: GO:2000846
nodes.Name: regulation of corticosteroid hormone secretion
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of corticosteroid hormone secretion.

nodes.label: GO:0002301
nodes.Name: CD4-positive, alpha-beta intraepithelial T cell differentiation
nodes.Definition: The process in which a precursor cell type acquires the specialized features of a CD4-positive, alpha-beta intraepithelial T cell. Intraepithelial T cells are found among epithelial cells in mucosal areas and have distinct phenotypes and developmental pathways.

nodes.label: GO:0045484
nodes.Name: L-lysine 6-transaminase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 2-oxoglutarate + L-lysine = L-glutamate + allysine.

nodes.label: GO:1904522
nodes.Name: positive regulation of myofibroblast cell apoptotic process
nodes.Definition: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of myofibroblast cell apoptotic process.

nodes.label: GO:0008415
nodes.Name: acyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the transfer of an acyl group from one compound (donor) to another (acceptor).

nodes.label: GO:0004918
nodes.Name: interleukin-8 receptor activity
nodes.Definition: Combining with interleukin-8 and transmitting the signal from one side of the membrane to the other to initiate a change in cell activity.

nodes.label: GO:0016494
nodes.Name: C-X-C chemokine receptor activity
nodes.Definition: Combining with a C-X-C chemokine and transmitting the signal from one side of the membrane to the other to initiate a change in cell activity. A C-X-C chemokine has a single amino acid between the first two cysteines of the characteristic four cysteine motif.

nodes.label: GO:0032815
nodes.Name: negative regulation of natural killer cell activation
nodes.Definition: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of natural killer cell activation.

nodes.label: GO:0047313
nodes.Name: aromatic-amino-acid-glyoxylate transaminase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: glyoxylate + an aromatic amino acid = L-glycine + an aromatic oxo acid.

nodes.label: GO:0008064
nodes.Name: regulation of actin polymerization or depolymerization
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the assembly or disassembly of actin filaments by the addition or removal of actin monomers from a filament.

nodes.label: GO:2000570
nodes.Name: positive regulation of T-helper 2 cell activation
nodes.Definition: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of T-helper 2 cell activation.

nodes.label: GO:0043775
nodes.Name: cobyrinic acid a,c-diamide synthase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the conversion of cobyrinic acid to cobyrinic acid a,c-diamide via the intermediate formation of cobyrinic acid c-monoamide.

nodes.label: GO:0050295
nodes.Name: steryl-beta-glucosidase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: cholesteryl-beta-D-glucoside + H2O = D-glucose + cholesterol.

nodes.label: GO:0003782
nodes.Name: obsolete F-actin capping activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. (Was not defined before being made obsolete).

nodes.label: GO:0004109
nodes.Name: coproporphyrinogen oxidase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: coproporphyrinogen III + 2 H+ + O2 = 2 CO2 + 2 H2O + protoporphyrinogen IX.

nodes.label: GO:0075256
nodes.Name: regulation of teliospore formation
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of teliospore formation, which is the formation of a thick-walled resting or over-wintering spore produced by the rust fungi (Uredinales) and smut fungi (Ustilaginales) in which karyogamy occurs.

nodes.label: GO:0070486
nodes.Name: leukocyte aggregation
nodes.Definition: The adhesion of one leukocyte to one or more other leukocytes via adhesion molecules.

nodes.label: GO:0003906
nodes.Name: DNA-(apurinic or apyrimidinic site) endonuclease activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the cleavage of the C-O-P bond in the AP site created when DNA glycosylase removes a damaged base, involved in the DNA base excision repair pathway (BER).

nodes.label: GO:0010659
nodes.Name: cardiac muscle cell apoptotic process
nodes.Definition: A form of programmed cell death induced by external or internal signals that trigger the activity of proteolytic caspases, whose actions dismantle a cardiac muscle cell and result in its death. Cardiac muscle cells are striated muscle cells that are responsible for heart contraction.

nodes.label: GO:0010667
nodes.Name: negative regulation of cardiac muscle cell apoptotic process
nodes.Definition: Any process that decreases the rate or extent of cardiac cell apoptotic process, a form of programmed cell death induced by external or internal signals that trigger the activity of proteolytic caspases whose actions dismantle a cardiac muscle cell and result in its death.

nodes.label: GO:0003942
nodes.Name: N-acetyl-gamma-glutamyl-phosphate reductase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: N-acetyl-L-glutamate 5-semialdehyde + NADP+ + phosphate = N-acetyl-5-glutamyl phosphate + NADPH + H+.

nodes.label: GO:0008177
nodes.Name: succinate dehydrogenase (quinone) activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: a quinone + succinate = a quinol + fumarate.

nodes.label: GO:0032038
nodes.Name: myosin II heavy chain binding
nodes.Definition: Binding to a heavy chain of a myosin II complex.

nodes.label: GO:0046563
nodes.Name: obsolete methanol oxidase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the reaction: O2 + methanol = H2O2 + formaldehyde.

nodes.label: GO:0033667
nodes.Name: obsolete negative regulation of growth or development of symbiont in host
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Any process by which the symbiont stops, prevents or reduces its increase in size or mass or its progression from an initial condition to a later condition, within the cells or tissues of the host organism. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in the symbiotic interaction.

nodes.label: GO:0099619
nodes.Name: UDP-4-amino-4-deoxy-L-arabinose formyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 10-formyltetrahydrofolate + UDP-4-amino-4-deoxy-beta-L-arabinopyranose = 5,6,7,8-tetrahydrofolate + UDP-4-deoxy-4-formamido-beta-L-arabinopyranose.

nodes.label: GO:0044501
nodes.Name: perturbation of signal transduction in another organism
nodes.Definition: The process in which an organism effects a change in a signal transduction process - a cellular process in which a signal is conveyed to trigger a change in the activity or state of a cell - in a second organism.

nodes.label: GO:0044509
nodes.Name: envenomation resulting in modulation of signal transduction in another organism
nodes.Definition: A process that begins with venom being forced into an organism by the bite or sting of another organism, and ends with the resultant modulation of signal transduction in the bitten organism.

nodes.label: GO:0043561
nodes.Name: regulation of translational initiation in response to osmotic stress
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of translation initiation, as a result of a stimulus indicating an increase or decrease in the concentration of solutes outside the organism or cell.

nodes.label: GO:0010830
nodes.Name: regulation of myotube differentiation
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of myotube differentiation. Myotube differentiation is the process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a myotube cell. Myotubes are multinucleated cells that are formed when proliferating myoblasts exit the cell cycle, differentiate and fuse.

nodes.label: GO:1901739
nodes.Name: regulation of myoblast fusion
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of myoblast fusion.

nodes.label: GO:0050196
nodes.Name: [phosphorylase] phosphatase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: [phosphorylase a] + 4 H2O = 2 [phosphorylase b] + 4 phosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0036268
nodes.Name: swimming
nodes.Definition: Self-propelled movement of an organism from one location to another through water, often by means of active fin movement.

nodes.label: GO:0042320
nodes.Name: regulation of circadian sleep/wake cycle, REM sleep
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of rapid eye movement (REM) sleep.

nodes.label: GO:0004441
nodes.Name: inositol-1,4-bisphosphate 1-phosphatase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 1D-myo-inositol 1,4-bisphosphate + H2O = 1D-myo-inositol 4-phosphate + phosphate.

nodes.label: GO:1904657
nodes.Name: negative regulation of sensory perception of sweet taste
nodes.Definition: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of sensory perception of sweet taste.

nodes.label: GO:0043714
nodes.Name: (R)-citramalate synthase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: pyruvate + acetyl-CoA + H2O = (R)-citramalate + CoA.

nodes.label: GO:0102008
nodes.Name: dipeptidase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of a dipeptide.

nodes.label: GO:0009765
nodes.Name: photosynthesis, light harvesting
nodes.Definition: Absorption and transfer of the energy absorbed from light photons between photosystem reaction centers.

nodes.label: GO:0009768
nodes.Name: photosynthesis, light harvesting in photosystem I
nodes.Definition: After a photon of light is absorbed by one of the many chlorophyll molecules, in one of the light-harvesting complexes of an antenna on photosystem I, some of the absorbed energy is transferred to the pair of chlorophyll molecules in the reaction center.

nodes.label: GO:0060923
nodes.Name: cardiac muscle cell fate commitment
nodes.Definition: The commitment of cells to specific cardiac muscle cell fates and their capacity to differentiate into cardiac muscle cells. Cardiac muscle cells are striated muscle cells that are responsible for heart contraction.

nodes.label: GO:0060924
nodes.Name: atrial cardiac muscle cell fate commitment
nodes.Definition: The commitment of cells to atrial cardiac muscle cell fates and their capacity to differentiate into cardiac muscle cells of the atrium. Cardiac muscle cells are striated muscle cells that are responsible for heart contraction.

nodes.label: GO:0047891
nodes.Name: flavone 7-O-beta-glucosyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: UDP-glucose + 5,7,3',4'-tetrahydroxyflavone = UDP + 7-O-beta-D-glucosyl-5,7,3',4'-tetrahydroxyflavone.

nodes.label: GO:0050309
nodes.Name: sugar-terminal-phosphatase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: H2O + sugar phosphorylated on the terminal carbon = a sugar + phosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0034942
nodes.Name: obsolete cis-2-methyl-5-isopropylhexa-2,5-dienoate-CoA ligase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the reaction: cis-2-methyl-5-isopropylhexa-2,5-dienoic acid + ATP + CoASH = cis-2-methyl-5-isopropylhexa-2,5-dienoyl-CoA + AMP + PPi.

nodes.label: GO:0038109
nodes.Name: Kit signaling pathway
nodes.Definition: The series of molecular signals initiated by the binding of stem cell factor to the tyrosine kinase receptor KIT on the surface of a target cell, and ending with regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. transcription. Stem cell factor (KIT ligand) binding to the receptor Kit mediates receptor dimerization, activation of its intrinsic tyrosine kinase activity and autophosphorylation. The activated receptor then phosphorylates various substrates, thereby activating distinct signaling cascades within the cell that trigger a change in state or activity of the cell.

nodes.label: GO:0008479
nodes.Name: tRNA-guanosine(34) queuine transglycosylase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: guanosine34 in tRNA + queuine = guanine + queuosine34 in tRNA.

nodes.label: GO:0034607
nodes.Name: turning behavior involved in mating
nodes.Definition: The sharp ventral turn performed by the male as he approaches either the hermaphrodite head or tail, whilst trying to locate his partner's vulva. Turning occurs via a sharp ventral coil of the male's tail.

nodes.label: GO:0061096
nodes.Name: negative regulation of turning behavior involved in mating
nodes.Definition: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of turning behavior involved in mating. Turning behavior is the sharp ventral turn performed by the male as he approaches either the hermaphrodite head or tail, whilst trying to locate his partner's vulva. Turning occurs via a sharp ventral coil of the male's tail.

nodes.label: GO:0045584
nodes.Name: negative regulation of cytotoxic T cell differentiation
nodes.Definition: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of cytotoxic T cell differentiation.

nodes.label: GO:0043027
nodes.Name: cysteine-type endopeptidase inhibitor activity involved in apoptotic process
nodes.Definition: Binds to and stops, prevents or reduces the activity of a cysteine-type endopeptidase involved in the apoptotic process.

nodes.label: GO:0044162
nodes.Name: host cell cytoplasmic vesicle membrane
nodes.Definition: The lipid bilayer surrounding a host cell cytoplasmic vesicle.

nodes.label: GO:1990174
nodes.Name: phosphodiesterase decapping endonuclease activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the removal of the cap from an unmethylated 5'-end capped RNA resulting in the release of the entire cap structure (GpppN) and a 5' monophosphorylated RNA.

nodes.label: GO:0045159
nodes.Name: myosin II binding
nodes.Definition: Binding to a class II myosin, any member of the class of 'conventional' double-headed myosins that includes muscle myosin.

nodes.label: GO:0033821
nodes.Name: DNA beta-glucosyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the transfer of a beta-D-glucosyl residue from UDP-glucose to a hydroxymethylcytosine residue in DNA.

nodes.label: GO:0045619

nodes.Definition: The series of events required for an organism to receive a sensory light stimulus, convert it to a molecular signal, and recognize and characterize the signal. This is a neurological process.

nodes.label: GO:0010161
nodes.Name: red light signaling pathway
nodes.Definition: The series of molecular signals initiated upon sensing of red light by a photoreceptor molecule. Red light is electromagnetic radiation of wavelength of 580-700nm. An example of this response is seen at the beginning of many plant species developmental stages. These include germination, and the point when cotyledon expansion is triggered. In certain species these processes take place in response to absorption of red light by the pigment molecule phytochrome, but the signal can be reversed by exposure to far red light. During the initial phase the phytochrome molecule is only present in the red light absorbing form, but on absorption of red light it changes to a far red light absorbing form, triggering progress through development. An immediate short period of exposure to far red light entirely returns the pigment to its initial state and prevents triggering of the developmental process. A thirty minute break between red and subsequent far red light exposure renders the red light effect irreversible, and development then occurs regardless of whether far red light exposure subsequently occurs.

nodes.label: GO:0031517
nodes.Name: red light photoreceptor activity

nodes.label: GO:0019737

The extraocular muscle is derived from cranial mesoderm and controls eye movements. The muscle begins its development with the differentiation of the muscle cells and ends with the mature muscle.

nodes.label: GO:0031368
nodes.Name: obsolete Pro-X metallocarboxypeptidase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the cleavage of a Pro-Xaa bond by a metallopeptidase mechanism to release a C-terminal amino acid.

nodes.label: GO:0043339
nodes.Name: establishment or maintenance of neuroblast polarity
nodes.Definition: Any cellular process that results in the specification, formation or maintenance of the apicobasal polarity of a neuroblast cell, a progenitor of the central nervous system.

nodes.label: GO:0036463
nodes.Name: TRAIL receptor activity
nodes.Definition: Combining with the ligand TRAIL (tumor necrosis factor-related apoptosis-inducing ligand) and transmitting the signal from one side of the plasma membrane to the other to initiate apoptotic cell death.

nodes.label: GO:0008933
nodes.Name: lytic transglycosylase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the specific cleavage of the beta-(1->4) glycosidic linkage between N-acetylmuramyl and N-acetylglucosaminyl residues in peptidoglycan, with the concomitant formation of 1,6-anhydro-N-acetylmuramyl residues.

nodes.label: GO:0046675
nodes.Name: positive regulation of compound eye retinal cell apoptotic process
nodes.Definition: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of compound eye retinal cell apoptotic process.

nodes.label: GO:0016966
nodes.Name: nitric oxide reductase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: H2O + 2 ferricytochrome c + nitrous oxide = 2 H+ + 2 ferrocytochrome c + 2 nitric oxide.

nodes.label: GO:0016968
nodes.Name: nitric oxide reductase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: H2O + 2 ferricytochrome c + nitrous oxide = 2 H+ + 2 ferrocytochrome c + 2 nitric oxide.

nodes.label: GO:0001663
nodes.Name: fear response
nodes.Definition: The response of an organism to a perceived external threat.

nodes.label: GO:2000837
nodes.Name: regulation of androstenedione secretion
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of androstenedione secretion.

nodes.label: GO:0043867
nodes.Name: 7-cyano-7-deazaguanine tRNA-ribosyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: tRNA guanine + 7-cyano-7-deazaguanine = tRNA 7-cyano-7-deazaguanine + guanine.

nodes.label: GO:1902436
nodes.Name: negative regulation of male mating behavior
nodes.Definition: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of male mating behavior.

nodes.label: GO:0043089
nodes.Name: positive regulation of GTPase activity
nodes.Definition: Any process that activates or increases the activity of a GTPase.

nodes.label: GO:0035180
nodes.Name: larval wandering behavior
nodes.Definition: The movement of a third instar larva through a substrate in search of a pupation site. This movement occurs without feeding and is characterized by short bursts of forward movement, separated by stops and repeated side-to-side head probes, followed normally by a change in direction.

nodes.label: GO:0016768
nodes.Name: spermine synthase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: S-adenosylmethioninamine + spermidine = 5'-methylthioadenosine + spermine.

nodes.label: GO:0008945
nodes.Name: obsolete oligopeptidase B activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the hydrolysis of Arg-Xaa and Lys-Xaa bonds in oligopeptides, even when P1' residue is proline.

nodes.label: GO:0051993
nodes.Name: abscisic acid glucose ester beta-glucosidase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: abscisic acid glucose ester + H2O = abscisic acid + beta-D-glucose.

nodes.label: GO:0043799
nodes.Name: glycine oxidase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reactions: (1) glycine + H2O + O2 = glyoxylate + NH3 + hydrogen peroxide; (2) D-alanine + H2O + O2 = pyruvate + NH3 + hydrogen peroxide; (3) sarcosine + H2O + O2 = glyoxylate + methylamine + hydrogen peroxide; (4) N-ethylglycine + H2O + O2 = glyoxylate + ethylamine + hydrogen peroxide.

nodes.label: GO:0004525
nodes.Name: ribonuclease III activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the endonucleolytic cleavage of RNA with 5'-phosphomonoesters and 3'-OH termini; makes two staggered cuts in both strands of dsRNA, leaving a 3' overhang of 2 nt.

nodes.label: GO:0032296
nodes.Name: double-stranded RNA-specific ribonuclease activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of phosphodiester bonds in double-stranded RNA molecules.

nodes.label: GO:0051405
nodes.Name: obsolete microbial collagenase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the digestion of native collagen in the triple helical region at Xaa-Gly bonds.

nodes.label: GO:0008947
nodes.Name: obsolete omptin activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the preferential cleavage of Xaa-Yaa in which both Xaa and Yaa are Arg or Lys.

nodes.label: GO:0047382
nodes.Name: methylphosphothioglycerate phosphatase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: S-methyl-3-phospho-1-thio-D-glycerate + H2O = S-methyl-1-thio-D-glycerate + phosphate.

nodes.label: GO:1990341
nodes.Name: thrombospondin complex
nodes.Definition: A homotrimeric or homopentameric glycoprotein that functions at the interface of the cell membrane and the extracellular matrix through its interactions with proteins and proteoglycans, such as collagens, integrins and fibronectin, to regulate matrix structure and cellular behaviour.

nodes.label: GO:0010662
nodes.Name: regulation of striated muscle cell apoptotic process
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the rate or extent of striated muscle cell apoptotic process, a form of programmed cell death induced by external or internal signals that trigger the activity of proteolytic caspases whose actions dismantle a striated muscle cell and result in its death.

nodes.label: GO:0010664
nodes.Name: negative regulation of striated muscle cell apoptotic process
nodes.Definition: Any process that decreases the rate or extent of striated muscle cell apoptotic process, a form of programmed cell death induced by external or internal signals that trigger the activity of proteolytic caspases whose actions dismantle a striated muscle cell and result in its death.

nodes.label: GO:0034833
nodes.Name: obsolete geranylate CoA-transferase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the reaction: geranylate + CoASH = trans-geranyl-CoA + OH-.

nodes.label: GO:0097193
nodes.Name: intrinsic apoptotic signaling pathway
nodes.Definition: The series of molecular signals in which an intracellular signal is conveyed to trigger the apoptotic death of a cell. The pathway starts with reception of an intracellular signal (e.g. DNA damage, endoplasmic reticulum stress, oxidative stress etc.), and ends when the execution phase of apoptosis is triggered. The intrinsic apoptotic signaling pathway is crucially regulated by permeabilization of the mitochondrial outer membrane (MOMP).

nodes.label: GO:2001243
nodes.Name: negative regulation of intrinsic apoptotic signaling pathway
nodes.Definition: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of intrinsic apoptotic signaling pathway.

nodes.label: GO:0090409
nodes.Name: malonyl-CoA synthetase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: malonate + ATP + coenzyme A = malonyl-CoA + AMP + diphosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0097657
nodes.Name: 3',5'-nucleotide bisphosphate phosphatase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 3',5'-nucleoside bisphosphate + H20 = 5'-nucleoside monophosphate + phosphate.

nodes.label: GO:1903080
nodes.Name: regulation of C-C chemokine receptor CCR7 signaling pathway
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of C-C chemokine receptor CCR7 signaling pathway.

nodes.label: GO:0060111
nodes.Name: alae of collagen and cuticulin-based cuticle extracellular matrix
nodes.Definition: Raised, thickened cuticular ridges that run longitudinally, and in parallel, along the left and right sides of the animal. The alae lie above the hypodermal cells known as the lateral seam cells. In C. elegans, alae are produced in L1 larvae, dauer larvae and adult stage animals, where they consist of three, five, and three ridges of distinct morphology, respectively.

nodes.label: GO:0032579
nodes.Name: apical lamina of hyaline layer
nodes.Definition: A fibrous network that is part of the hyalin layer extracellular matrix. The apical lamina is thought to be principally composed of the glycoproteins fibropellins. This matrix has been found in echinoderms.

nodes.label: GO:0033166
nodes.Name: hyaline layer
nodes.Definition: A multilayered extraembryonic matrix that functions as a substrate for cell adhesion through early development. It is thought to protect and lubricate the embryo, stabilize the blastomeres during morphogenesis, and regulate nutrient intake. The major constituent of the hyaline layer is the protein hyalin. This matrix has been found in echinoderms.

nodes.label: GO:0030036
nodes.Name: actin cytoskeleton organization
nodes.Definition: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of cytoskeletal structures comprising actin filaments and their associated proteins.

nodes.label: GO:0031032
nodes.Name: actomyosin structure organization
nodes.Definition: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of cytoskeletal structures containing both actin and myosin or paramyosin. The myosin may be organized into filaments.

nodes.label: GO:0047579
nodes.Name: 4-hydroxymandelate oxidase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: (S)-4-hydroxymandelate + H+ + O2 = 4-hydroxybenzaldehyde + CO2 + H2O2.

nodes.label: GO:0072195
nodes.Name: kidney smooth muscle cell differentiation
nodes.Definition: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a smooth muscle cell in the kidney.

nodes.label: GO:2000358
nodes.Name: positive regulation of kidney smooth muscle cell differentiation
nodes.Definition: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of kidney smooth muscle cell differentiation.

nodes.label: GO:0010207
nodes.Name: photosystem II assembly
nodes.Definition: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form a photosystem II complex on the thylakoid membrane. The photosystem II complex consists of at least 20 polypeptides and around 80 cofactors in most organisms.

nodes.label: GO:0047517
nodes.Name: 1,4-beta-D-xylan synthase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: UDP-D-xylose + [(1->4)-beta-D-xylan](n) = UDP + [(1->4)-beta-D-xylan](n+1).

nodes.label: GO:0033765
nodes.Name: steroid dehydrogenase activity, acting on the CH-CH group of donors
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which a CH-CH group acts as a hydrogen or electron donor and reduces a hydrogen or electron acceptor, and in which one substrate is a sterol derivative.

nodes.label: GO:0050976
nodes.Name: detection of mechanical stimulus involved in sensory perception of touch
nodes.Definition: The series of events involved in the perception of touch in which a mechanical stimulus is received and converted into a molecular signal.

nodes.label: GO:0050567
nodes.Name: glutaminyl-tRNA synthase (glutamine-hydrolyzing) activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: L-glutamine + glutamyl-tRNA(Gln) + ATP = L-glutamate + glutaminyl-tRNA(Gln) + phosphate + ADP.

nodes.label: GO:0008676
nodes.Name: 3-deoxy-8-phosphooctulonate synthase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: D-arabinose 5-phosphate + H2O + phosphoenolpyruvate = 8-phospho-3-deoxy-D-manno-oct-2-ulosonate + 2 H+ + phosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0038165
nodes.Name: oncostatin-M-mediated signaling pathway
nodes.Definition: The series of molecular signals initiated by oncostatin-M (OSM) binding to its receptor on the surface of a target cell, and ending with the regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. transcription. OSM can signal via at least two different receptors (a specific receptor and a LIF receptor) to activate different downstream signal transduction pathways.

nodes.label: GO:0032029
nodes.Name: myosin tail binding
nodes.Definition: Binding to the tail region of a myosin heavy chain.

nodes.label: GO:0032035
nodes.Name: myosin II tail binding
nodes.Definition: Binding to the tail region of a myosin II heavy chain.

nodes.label: GO:0010613
nodes.Name: positive regulation of cardiac muscle hypertrophy
nodes.Definition: Any process that increases the rate, frequency or extent of the enlargement or overgrowth of all or part of the heart due to an increase in size (not length) of individual cardiac muscle fibers, without cell division.

nodes.label: GO:0071690
nodes.Name: cardiac muscle myosin thick filament assembly
nodes.Definition: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of proteins to form the myosin-based thick filaments of myofibrils in cardiac muscle.

nodes.label: GO:0033201
nodes.Name: obsolete alpha-1,4-glucan synthase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the reaction: RDP-glucose + [alpha-D-glucosyl-(1,4)]n = RDP + [alpha-D-glucosyl-(1,4)]n+1, where RDP is ADP or UDP.

nodes.label: GO:0004287
nodes.Name: obsolete prolyl oligopeptidase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the hydrolysis of Pro-Xaa > Ala-Xaa in oligopeptides.

nodes.label: GO:0047024
nodes.Name: 5alpha-androstane-3beta,17beta-diol dehydrogenase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 5alpha-androstane-3beta,17beta-diol + NADP+ = 17beta-hydroxy-5alpha-androstan-3-one + H+ + NADPH.

nodes.label: GO:1990324
nodes.Name: collagen type XXVI trimer
nodes.Definition: A collagen homotrimer of alpha1(XXVI) chains.

nodes.label: GO:0042296
nodes.Name: ISG15 transferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the transfer of ISG15 from one protein to another via the reaction X-ISG15 + Y = Y-ISG15 + X, where both X-ISG15 and Y-ISG15 are covalent linkages.

nodes.label: GO:0061662
nodes.Name: ISG15 ligase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the transfer of a ISG15 to a substrate protein via the reaction X-ISG15 + S = X + S-ISG15, where X is either an E2 or E3 enzyme, the X-ISG15 linkage is a thioester bond, and the S-ISG15 linkage is an isopeptide bond between the C-terminal amino acid of ISG15 and the epsilon-amino group of lysine residues in the substrate.

nodes.label: GO:0018494
nodes.Name: carvone reductase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reactions: (1R,4R)-dihydrocarvone + A = (R)-carvone + AH2, and (1R,4S)-isodihydrocarvone + A = (S)-carvone + AH2.

nodes.label: GO:0004239
nodes.Name: initiator methionyl aminopeptidase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the release of N-terminal initiator methionine from peptides.

nodes.label: GO:0017120
nodes.Name: obsolete polyphosphatidylinositol phosphatase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the conversion of phosphatidylinositol-3-phosphate, phosphatidylinositol-4-phosphate, and phosphatidylinositol-3,5-bisphosphate, but not PI-4,5-bisphosphate, to phosphatidylinositol; PPIPase activity is a key regulator of membrane trafficking and actin cytoskeleton organization.

nodes.label: GO:0043812
nodes.Name: phosphatidylinositol-4-phosphate phosphatase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol-4-phosphate + H2O = phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol + phosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0071346
nodes.Name: cellular response to type II interferon
nodes.Definition: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an interferon-gamma stimulus. Interferon gamma is the only member of the type II interferon found so far.

nodes.label: GO:0017178
nodes.Name: diphthine-ammonia ligase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + diphthine + NH4 = ADP + diphthamide + H+ + phosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0038153
nodes.Name: CCL2-activated CCR4 signaling pathway
nodes.Definition: The series of molecular signals initiated by the binding of the C-C chemokine CCL2 to a C-C chemokine type 4 receptor (CCR4) on the surface of a target cell, and ending with the regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. transcription.

nodes.label: GO:0044358
nodes.Name: envenomation resulting in hemorrhagic damage in another organism
nodes.Definition: A process that begins with venom being forced into an organism by the bite or sting of another organism, and ends with vascular damage and hemorrhage in the bitten organism.

nodes.label: GO:0044482
nodes.Name: envenomation resulting in blood vessel extracellular matrix damage, causing hemorrhagic damage in another organism
nodes.Definition: A process that begins with venom being forced into an organism by the bite or sting of another organism which causes damage to the extracellular matrix of the blood vessels of the bitten organism, ultimately resulting in hemorrhage in the bitten organism.

nodes.label: GO:0075197
nodes.Name: haustorium neck formation
nodes.Definition: The assembly by the symbiont of a neck-like structure for the purpose of penetration into its host organism. The neck-like structure connects haustorium mother cell and haustorium. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

nodes.label: GO:0047647
nodes.Name: alkylacetylglycerophosphatase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 1-alkyl-2-acetyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate + H2O = 2-acetyl-1-alkyl-sn-glycerol + phosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0050103
nodes.Name: dextrin dextranase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 1,4-alpha-D-glucosyl(n) + 1,6-alpha-D-glucosyl(m) = 1,4-alpha-D-glucosyl(n-1) + 1,6-alpha-D-glucosyl(m+1).

nodes.label: GO:0071839
nodes.Name: apoptotic process in bone marrow cell
nodes.Definition: The apoptotic process in cells in the bone marrow.

nodes.label: GO:0071865
nodes.Name: regulation of apoptotic process in bone marrow cell
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the occurrence or rate of cell death by apoptotic process in the bone marrow.

nodes.label: GO:0033723
nodes.Name: fluoroacetaldehyde dehydrogenase (NAD+) activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: fluoroacetaldehyde + NAD+ + H2O = fluoroacetate + NADH + 2 H+.

nodes.label: GO:0055018
nodes.Name: regulation of cardiac muscle fiber development
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cardiac muscle fiber development.

nodes.label: GO:0048783
nodes.Name: positive regulation of cyanophore differentiation
nodes.Definition: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of cyanophore differentiation.

nodes.label: GO:0098642
nodes.Name: network-forming collagen trimer
nodes.Definition: A collagen trimer that forms networks.

nodes.label: GO:0070108
nodes.Name: negative regulation of interleukin-27-mediated signaling pathway
nodes.Definition: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of an interleukin-27-mediated signaling pathway.

nodes.label: GO:0016632
nodes.Name: oxidoreductase activity, acting on the CH-CH group of donors, cytochrome as acceptor
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which a CH-CH group acts as a hydrogen or electron donor and reduces a cytochrome.

nodes.label: GO:0015668
nodes.Name: type III site-specific deoxyribonuclease activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the endonucleolytic cleavage of DNA to give double-stranded fragments with terminal 5'-phosphates. ATP hydrolysis is required. Cleavage is dependent on the presence of two copies of a specific recognition sequence in an inverse orientation in the DNA. Cleavage occurs at a specific distance from one of the recognition sites.

nodes.label: GO:0033876
nodes.Name: glycochenodeoxycholate sulfotransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 3'-phospho-5'-adenylyl sulfate + glycochenodeoxycholate = adenosine 3',5'-diphosphate + glycochenodeoxycholate 7-sulfate + H+.

nodes.label: GO:1902488
nodes.Name: cholangiocyte apoptotic process
nodes.Definition: Any apoptotic process in a cholangiocyte.

nodes.label: GO:1904194
nodes.Name: positive regulation of cholangiocyte apoptotic process
nodes.Definition: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of cholangiocyte apoptotic process.

nodes.label: GO:0010203
nodes.Name: response to very low fluence red light stimulus
nodes.Definition: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a very low fluence red light stimulus. Red light is electromagnetic radiation of wavelength of 580-700nm. Very low fluence red light is defined in this case as short pulses of red light followed by darkness, providing light levels of less than 0.001 mmol/m2/sec.

nodes.label: GO:0055122
nodes.Name: response to very low light intensity stimulus
nodes.Definition: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a very low light intensity stimulus. A very low light intensity stimulus is defined as a level of electromagnetic radiation below 0.001 mmol/m2/sec.

nodes.label: GO:0032358
nodes.Name: oxidized pyrimidine DNA binding
nodes.Definition: Binding to a DNA region containing an oxidized pyrimidine residue.

nodes.label: GO:0036005
nodes.Name: response to macrophage colony-stimulating factor
nodes.Definition: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a macrophage colony-stimulating factor stimulus.

nodes.label: GO:0047531
nodes.Name: obsolete 2,5-diaminovalerate transaminase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the reaction: 2-oxoglutarate + ornithine = 5-amino-2-oxopentanoate + L-glutamate.

nodes.label: GO:0050883
nodes.Name: musculoskeletal movement, spinal reflex action
nodes.Definition: Involuntary movement caused by the application of a stimulus to an organism and a subsequent movement. The signal processing of this movement takes place in the spinal cord.

nodes.label: GO:0016920
nodes.Name: pyroglutamyl-peptidase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the release of the N-terminal pyroglutamyl group from a peptide or protein.

nodes.label: GO:0016921
nodes.Name: obsolete pyroglutamyl-peptidase II activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the release of the N-terminal pyroglutamyl group from pGlu-His-Xaa tripeptides and pGlu-His-Xaa-Gly tetrapeptides.

nodes.label: GO:0047233
nodes.Name: N-acetylneuraminylgalactosylglucosylceramide beta-1,4-N-acetylgalactosaminyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: N-acetylneuraminyl-2,3-alpha-D-galactosyl-1,4-beta-D-glucosylceramide + UDP-N-acetylgalactosamine = N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosaminyl-1,4-(N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminyl-2,3)-beta-D-galactosyl-1,4-beta-D-glucosylceramide + UDP.

nodes.label: GO:0009771
nodes.Name: obsolete primary charge separation in photosystem II
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Energized reaction-center P680 chlorophylls on photosystem II donate an electron to a loosely bound acceptor molecule, the quinone Q, on the stromal surface of the thylakoid membrane. The result is charge separation; a negative charge on the stromal side of the thylakoid membrane and a positive charge on the luminal side.

nodes.label: GO:0018475
nodes.Name: obsolete trans-2-methyl-5-isopropylhexa-2,5-dienal dehydrogenase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the reaction: trans-2-methyl-5-isopropylhexa-2,5-dienal + NAD+ + H2O = NADH + H+ + trans-2-methyl-5-isopropylhexa-2,5-dienoic acid.

nodes.label: GO:0006938
nodes.Name: sarcomere organization
nodes.Definition: The myofibril assembly process that results in the organization of muscle actomyosin into sarcomeres. The sarcomere is the repeating unit of a myofibril in a muscle cell, composed of an array of overlapping thick and thin filaments between two adjacent Z discs.

nodes.label: GO:0008026
nodes.Name: helicase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + H2O = ADP + phosphate, to drive the unwinding of a DNA or RNA helix.

nodes.label: GO:0033909
nodes.Name: fucoidanase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the endohydrolysis of 1,2-alpha-L-fucoside linkages in fucoidan without release of sulfate.

nodes.label: GO:0008766
nodes.Name: UDP-N-acetylmuramoylalanyl-D-glutamyl-2,6-diaminopimelate-D-alanyl-D-alanine ligase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + UDP-N-acetylmuramoyl-L-alanyl-D-glutamyl-meso-2,6-diaminoheptanedioate + D-alanyl-D-alanine = ADP + phosphate + UDP-N-acetylmuramoyl-L-alanyl-D-glutamyl-6-carboxy-L-lysyl-D-alanyl-D-alanine.

nodes.label: GO:0047562
nodes.Name: 3-hydroxyaspartate aldolase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: (3R)-3-hydroxy-L-aspartate = glycine + glyoxylate.

nodes.label: GO:0047723
nodes.Name: inosinate nucleosidase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: H2O + IMP = D-ribose 5-phosphate + hypoxanthine.

nodes.label: GO:0000905
nodes.Name: sporocarp development involved in asexual reproduction
nodes.Definition: The formation of a spore-bearing structure by fungus where spores will arise from asexual reproduction.

nodes.label: GO:0036475
nodes.Name: obsolete neuron death in response to oxidative stress
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Any biological process that results in permanent cessation of all vital functions of a neuron upon exposure to an oxidative stress stimulus.

nodes.label: GO:0044554
nodes.Name: modulation of heart rate in another organism
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the frequency or rate of heart contraction of another organism.

nodes.label: GO:0051921
nodes.Name: adenosylcobyric acid synthase (glutamine-hydrolyzing) activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 4 L-glutamine + adenosylcob(III)yrinate a,c-diamide + 4 ATP + 4 H2O = 4 L-glutamate + adenosylcobyrate + 4 ADP + 8 H+ + 4 phosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0014742
nodes.Name: positive regulation of muscle hypertrophy
nodes.Definition: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of muscle hypertrophy.

nodes.label: GO:0034359
nodes.Name: mature chylomicron
nodes.Definition: A chylomicron that contains apolipoprotein C2 (APOC2), a cofactor for lipoprotein lipase (LPL) activity, and has a mean diameter of 500 nm and density of 0.95g/ml. Mature chylomicron particles transport exogenous (dietary) lipids from the intestines to other body tissues, via the blood and lymph.

nodes.label: GO:0060921
nodes.Name: sinoatrial node cell differentiation
nodes.Definition: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a sinoatrial (SA) node cell. SA node cells are pacemaker cells that are found in the sinoatrial node.

nodes.label: GO:0060931
nodes.Name: sinoatrial node cell development
nodes.Definition: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a sinoatrial (SA) node cell over time, from its formation to the mature state. SA node cells are pacemaker cells that are found in the sinoatrial node.

nodes.label: GO:0039502
nodes.Name: symbiont-mediated suppression of host type I interferon-mediated signaling pathway
nodes.Definition: A process in which a symbiont interferes with, inhibits or disrupts a type I interferon-mediated signaling in the host organism. Type I interferons include the interferon-alpha, beta, delta, episilon, zeta, kappa, tau, and omega gene families.

nodes.label: GO:0004867
nodes.Name: serine-type endopeptidase inhibitor activity
nodes.Definition: Binds to and stops, prevents or reduces the activity of a serine-type endopeptidase.

nodes.label: GO:0004868
nodes.Name: obsolete serpin
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. A superfamily of proteins, many of which inhibit serine proteinases and exhibit a high degree of homology with classical serine proteinase inhibitors such as alpha1-antitrypsin or antithrombin.

nodes.label: GO:0002210
nodes.Name: behavioral response to wounding
nodes.Definition: A behavioral response resulting from wounding.

nodes.label: GO:0018493
nodes.Name: formylmethanofuran dehydrogenase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: N-formylmethanofuran + A + H2O + H+ = AH(2) + CO2 + methanofuran.

nodes.label: GO:0019142
nodes.Name: 2-hydroxyglutarate synthase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: glyoxylate + H2O + propanoyl-CoA = 2-hydroxyglutarate + CoA + H+.

nodes.label: GO:1901693
nodes.Name: negative regulation of compound eye retinal cell apoptotic process
nodes.Definition: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of compound eye retinal cell apoptotic process.

nodes.label: GO:0047294
nodes.Name: phosphoglycerol geranylgeranyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: (2E,6E,10E)-geranylgeranyl diphosphate + sn-glycerol 1-phosphate = diphosphate + sn-3-O-(geranylgeranyl)glycerol 1-phosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0030839
nodes.Name: regulation of intermediate filament polymerization
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the assembly of intermediate filaments by the addition of monomers to a filament.

nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of (1->4)-beta-D-xylans so as to remove successive D-xylose residues from the non-reducing termini.

nodes.label: GO:0097599
nodes.Name: xylanase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of xylans, homopolysaccharides composed of xylose residues.

nodes.label: GO:0043657
nodes.Name: host cell
nodes.Definition: A cell within a host organism. Includes the host plasma membrane and any external encapsulating structures such as the host cell wall and cell envelope.

nodes.label: GO:2000352
nodes.Name: negative regulation of endothelial cell apoptotic process
nodes.Definition: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of endothelial cell apoptotic process.

nodes.label: GO:0007020
nodes.Name: microtubule nucleation
nodes.Definition: The process in which tubulin alpha-beta heterodimers begin aggregation to form an oligomeric tubulin structure (a microtubule seed). Microtubule nucleation is the initiating step in the formation of a microtubule in the absence of any existing microtubules ('de novo' microtubule formation).

nodes.label: GO:0090226
nodes.Name: obsolete regulation of microtubule nucleation by Ran protein signal transduction
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. The series of molecular signals in which a Ran GTPase relays a signal resulting in the modulation of the rate, frequency or extent of microtubule nucleation.

nodes.label: GO:0018527
nodes.Name: cyclohexylamine oxidase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: cyclohexylamine + O2 + H2O = cyclohexanone + NH3 + hydrogen peroxide.

nodes.label: GO:0046651
nodes.Name: lymphocyte proliferation
nodes.Definition: The expansion of a lymphocyte population by cell division.

nodes.label: GO:0050671
nodes.Name: positive regulation of lymphocyte proliferation
nodes.Definition: Any process that activates or increases the rate or extent of lymphocyte proliferation.

nodes.label: GO:0010982
nodes.Name: regulation of high-density lipoprotein particle clearance
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of high-density lipoprotein particle clearance. High-density lipoprotein particle clearance is the process in which a high-density lipoprotein particle is removed from the blood via receptor-mediated endocytosis and its constituent parts degraded.

nodes.label: GO:0010320
nodes.Name: obsolete arginine/lysine endopeptidase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the hydrolysis of peptide linkages in oligopeptides or polypeptides by a reaction mechanism in which arginine or lysine residues act as nucleophiles.

nodes.label: GO:0042246
nodes.Name: tissue regeneration
nodes.Definition: The regrowth of lost or destroyed tissues.

nodes.label: GO:0051153
nodes.Name: regulation of striated muscle cell differentiation
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of striated muscle cell differentiation.

nodes.label: GO:0010940
nodes.Name: obsolete positive regulation of necrotic cell death
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Any process that increases the rate, frequency or extent of necrotic cell death. Necrotic cell death is a cell death process that is morphologically characterized by a gain in cell volume (oncosis), swelling of organelles, plasma membrane rupture and subsequent loss of intracellular contents.

nodes.label: GO:0047913
nodes.Name: gallate 1-beta-glucosyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: gallate + UDP-D-glucose = 1-O-galloyl-beta-D-glucose + UDP.

nodes.label: GO:1904824

nodes.Definition: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form an anaphase-promoting complex.

nodes.label: GO:0019204

nodes.label: GO:0098519
nodes.Name: obsolete nucleotide phosphatase activity, acting on free nucleotides
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the reaction: nucleotide + H2O = nucleotide + phosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0005974

nodes.label: GO:0004914

nodes.label: GO:0047228
nodes.Name: 1,2-diacylglycerol 3-glucosyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: a 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol + UDP-alpha-D-glucose = a 1,2-diacyl-3-O-(alpha-D-glucopyranosyl)-sn-glycerol + H+ + UDP.

nodes.label: GO:0080081
nodes.Name: 4-methylumbelliferyl-beta-D-glucopyranoside beta-glucosidase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of glucosidic link in 4-methylumbelliferyl-beta-D-glucopyranoside.

nodes.label: GO:0097058
nodes.Name: CRLF-CLCF1 complex
nodes.Definition: A heterodimeric protein complex that is composed of cardiotrophin-like cytokine factor 1 (product of the CLCF1 gene) and cytokine receptor-like factor 1 (product of the CRLF gene) and is secreted into the extracellular space. The CRLF-CLCF1 complex is a ligand for the ciliary neurotrophic factor (CNTF) receptor complex.

nodes.label: GO:0047514
nodes.Name: 1,3-beta-D-glucan phosphorylase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: [(1->3)-beta-D-glucosyl](n) + phosphate = [(1->3)-beta-D-glucosyl](n-1) + alpha-D-glucose 1-phosphate; substrates include laminarin.

nodes.label: GO:0052596
nodes.Name: obsolete phenethylamine:oxygen oxidoreductase (deaminating) activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the reaction: phenylethylamine + O2 + H2O = phenylacetaldehyde + NH3 + hydrogen peroxide + H+.

nodes.label: GO:0032864
nodes.Name: activation of GTPase activity
nodes.Definition: Any process that initiates the activity of an inactive GTPase through the replacement of GDP by GTP.

nodes.label: GO:0035313
nodes.Name: wound healing, spreading of epidermal cells
nodes.Definition: The migration of an epidermal cell along or through a wound gap that contributes to the reestablishment of a continuous epidermis.

nodes.label: GO:1903690
nodes.Name: negative regulation of wound healing, spreading of epidermal cells
nodes.Definition: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of wound healing, spreading of epidermal cells.

nodes.label: GO:0038116
nodes.Name: chemokine (C-C motif) ligand 21 signaling pathway
nodes.Definition: The series of molecular signals initiated by the binding of the C-C chemokine CCL21 to its receptor on the surface of a target cell, and ending with the regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. transcription.

nodes.label: GO:0030584
nodes.Name: sporocarp development
nodes.Definition: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a sporocarp over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The sporocarp is a spore bearing fruiting body organ. An example of this process is found in the Fungal species Coprinopsis cinerea.

nodes.label: GO:0032984
nodes.Name: protein-containing complex disassembly
nodes.Definition: The disaggregation of a protein-containing macromolecular complex into its constituent components.

nodes.label: GO:0047123
nodes.Name: quinoline-4-carboxylate 2-oxidoreductase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: A + H2O + quinoline-4-carboxylate = 2-oxo-1,2-dihydroquinoline-4-carboxylate + AH(2).

nodes.label: GO:0050608
nodes.Name: vanillin dehydrogenase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: H2O + NAD+ + vanillin = 2 H+ + NADH + vanillate.

nodes.label: GO:0031294
nodes.Name: lymphocyte costimulation
nodes.Definition: The process of providing, via surface-bound receptor-ligand pairs, a second, antigen-independent, signal in addition to that provided by the B- or T cell receptor to augment B- or T cell activation.

nodes.label: GO:0031296
nodes.Name: B cell costimulation
nodes.Definition: The process of providing, via surface-bound receptor-ligand pairs, a second, antigen-independent, signal in addition to that provided by the B cell receptor to augment B cell activation.

nodes.label: GO:0044184
nodes.Name: host cell late endosome
nodes.Definition: A prelysosomal endocytic organelle differentiated from host early endosomes by lower lumenal pH and different protein composition. Host late endosomes are more spherical than early endosomes and are mostly juxtanuclear, being concentrated near the microtubule organizing center.

nodes.label: GO:0047206
nodes.Name: UDP-N-acetylmuramoylpentapeptide-lysine N6-alanyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: UDP-N-acetylmuramoyl-L-alanyl-D-glutamyl-L-lysyl-D-alanyl-D-alanine + L-alanyl-tRNA(Ala) = UDP-N-acetylmuramoyl-L-alanyl-D-glutamyl-N6-(L-alanyl)-L-lysyl-D-alanyl-D-alanine + tRNA(Ala).

nodes.label: GO:0050018
nodes.Name: L-amino-acid dehydrogenase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: an L-amino acid + H2O + NAD+ = a 2-oxo acid + NH3 + NADH.

nodes.label: GO:0071263
nodes.Name: negative regulation of translational initiation in response to starvation
nodes.Definition: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the rate of translation initiation, as a result of deprivation of nourishment.

nodes.label: GO:1901817
nodes.Name: beta-zeacarotene catabolic process
nodes.Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of beta-zeacarotene.

nodes.label: GO:0046558
nodes.Name: arabinan endo-1,5-alpha-L-arabinosidase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the endohydrolysis of (1->5)-alpha-arabinofuranosidic linkages in (1->5) arabinans.

nodes.label: GO:0036399
nodes.Name: TCR signalosome assembly
nodes.Definition: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form a TCR signalosome.

nodes.label: GO:0033896
nodes.Name: ribonuclease IX activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the endonucleolytic cleavage of poly(U) or poly(C) to fragments terminated by 3'-hydroxy and 5'-phosphate groups.

nodes.label: GO:0019160

nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: H2O + nicotinamide mononucleotide = D-ribose 5-phosphate + H+ + nicotinamide.

nodes.label: GO:0044140
nodes.Name: obsolete negative regulation of growth of symbiont on or near host surface
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the increase in the symbiont's size or mass on or near the cells or tissues of the host organism.

nodes.label: GO:0044144
nodes.Name: obsolete modulation of growth of symbiont involved in interaction with host
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the increase in size or mass of an organism occurring in, on or near the exterior of its host organism.

nodes.label: GO:0047105
nodes.Name: 4-trimethylammoniobutyraldehyde dehydrogenase activity

nodes.label: GO:0004249
nodes.Name: obsolete stromelysin 3 activity

nodes.label: GO:0031395
nodes.Name: bursicon neuropeptide hormone complex
nodes.Definition: A neuropeptide hormone secreted by the central nervous system of insects that stimulates the tanning and sclerotization of the adult cuticle following eclosion. The active hormone consists of an obligate heterodimer of the alpha and beta subunits.

nodes.label: GO:0008609
nodes.Name: alkylglycerone-phosphate synthase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 1-acyl-glycerone 3-phosphate + a long-chain alcohol = 1-alkyl-glycerone 3-phosphate + a long-chain acid anion.

nodes.label: GO:0030305

nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the cleavage of heparan sulfate; can degrade both heparan sulfate and heparin glycosaminoglycan chains.

nodes.label: GO:0032516
nodes.Name: obsolete positive regulation of phosphoprotein phosphatase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Any process that activates or increases the activity of a phosphoprotein phosphatase.

nodes.label: GO:0034378

nodes.label: GO:0042013

nodes.label: GO:0042014
nodes.Name: interleukin-19 receptor activity
nodes.Definition: Combining with interleukin-19 and transmitting the signal from one side of the membrane to the other to initiate a change in cell activity.

nodes.label: GO:0008817
nodes.Name: corrinoid adenosyltransferase activity
