nodes.label: GO:0007118
nodes.Name: budding cell apical bud growth
nodes.Definition: Growth at the tip of a bud, in a cell that reproduces by budding.

nodes.label: GO:0010568
nodes.Name: regulation of budding cell apical bud growth
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of growth at the tip of a bud, in a cell that reproduces by budding.

nodes.label: GO:0019777
nodes.Name: Atg12 transferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the transfer of ATG12 from one protein to another via the reaction X-ATG12 + Y = Y-ATG12 + X, where both X-ATG12 and Y-ATG12 are covalent linkages.

nodes.label: GO:0061651
nodes.Name: Atg12 conjugating enzyme activity
nodes.Definition: Isoenergetic transfer of Atg12 from one protein to another via the reaction X-Atg12 + Y = Y-Atg12 + X, where both the X-Atg12 and Y-Atg12 linkages are thioester bonds between the C-terminal amino acid of Atg12 and a sulfhydryl side group of a cysteine residue.

nodes.label: GO:0070206
nodes.Name: protein trimerization
nodes.Definition: The formation of a protein trimer, a macromolecular structure consisting of three noncovalently associated identical or nonidentical subunits.

nodes.label: GO:0070208
nodes.Name: protein heterotrimerization
nodes.Definition: The formation of a protein heterotrimer, a macromolecular structure consisting of three noncovalently associated subunits, of which not all are identical.

nodes.label: GO:0071473
nodes.Name: cellular response to cation stress
nodes.Definition: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of cation stress, an increase or decrease in the concentration of positively charged ions in the environment.

nodes.label: GO:0016284
nodes.Name: obsolete alanine aminopeptidase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the release of an N-terminal amino acid, preferentially alanine, from an oligopeptide or polypeptide.

nodes.label: GO:0008455
nodes.Name: alpha-1,6-mannosylglycoprotein 2-beta-N-acetylglucosaminyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: UDP-N-acetyl-D-glucosamine + alpha-D-mannosyl-1,6-(N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-1,2-alpha-D-mannosyl-1,3)-beta-D-mannosyl-R = UDP + N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-1,2-alpha-D-mannosyl-1,6-(N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-1,2-alpha-D-mannosyl-1,3)-beta-D-mannosyl-R.

nodes.label: GO:0005587

nodes.Definition: A collagen heterotrimer containing type IV alpha chains; [alpha1(IV)]2alpha2(IV) trimers are commonly observed, although more type IV alpha chains exist and may be present in type IV trimers; type IV collagen triple helices associate to form 3 dimensional nets within basement membranes.

nodes.label: GO:0075317
nodes.Name: ascus development
nodes.Definition: The process that leads to the development of ascus, a sac-like structure produced by fungi of the phylum Ascomycota (sac fungi) in which sexually produced spores (ascospores), usually four or eight in number, are formed.

nodes.label: GO:0098514
nodes.Name: detection of high humidity stimulus involved in sensory perception
nodes.Definition: The series of events in which a high humidity stimulus is detected and converted into a molecular signal as a part of the sensory detection of high humidity.

nodes.label: GO:0098516
nodes.Name: detection of high humidity
nodes.Definition: The series of events in which high humidity is detected and converted into a molecular signal.

nodes.label: GO:0004184
nodes.Name: obsolete lysine carboxypeptidase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the reaction: peptidyl-L-lysine (or peptidyl-L-arginine) + H2O = peptide + L-lysine (or L-arginine). Release of a C-terminal basic amino acid, preferentially lysine; inactivates bradykinin and anaphylatoxins in blood plasma.

nodes.label: GO:0098618
nodes.Name: selenomethionine-tRNA ligase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + L-selenomethionine + tRNA(Met) => AMP + diphosphate + selenomethionyl-tRNA(Met).

nodes.label: GO:0047153
nodes.Name: deoxycytidylate 5-hydroxymethyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 5,10-methylenetetrahydrofolate + dCMP + H2O = (6S)-5,6,7,8-tetrahydrofolate + 5-hydroxymethyldeoxycytidylate.

nodes.label: GO:0002020
nodes.Name: protease binding
nodes.Definition: Binding to a protease or a peptidase.

nodes.label: GO:1990381
nodes.Name: ubiquitin-specific protease binding
nodes.Definition: Binding to a ubiquitin-specific protease.

nodes.label: GO:0051434
nodes.Name: BH3 domain binding
nodes.Definition: Binding to a BH3 protein domain, present in Bcl-2 family members. The BH3 domain is a potent death domain and has an important role in protein-protein interactions and in cell death.

nodes.label: GO:0070513
nodes.Name: death domain binding
nodes.Definition: Binding to a death domain of a protein. The death domain (DD) is a homotypic protein interaction module composed of a bundle of six alpha-helices. DD bind each other forming oligomers. Some DD-containing proteins are involved in the regulation of apoptosis and inflammation through their activation of caspases and NF-kappaB.

nodes.label: GO:0002300
nodes.Name: CD8-positive, alpha-beta intraepithelial T cell differentiation
nodes.Definition: The process in which a precursor cell type acquires the specialized features of a CD8-positive, alpha-beta intraepithelial T cell. Intraepithelial T cells are found among epithelial cells in mucosal areas and have distinct phenotypes and developmental pathways.

nodes.label: GO:0004198
nodes.Name: calcium-dependent cysteine-type endopeptidase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of nonterminal peptide bonds in a polypeptide chain by a mechanism using a cysteine residue at the enzyme active center, and requiring the presence of calcium.

nodes.label: GO:0050392
nodes.Name: vicianin beta-glucosidase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: (R)-vicianin + H2O = mandelonitrile + vicianose.

nodes.label: GO:0047246

nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: luteolin 7-O-beta-D-glucosiduronate + UDP-alpha-D-glucuronate = H+ + luteolin 7-O-[(beta-D-glucosiduronate)-(1->2)-(beta-D-glucosiduronate)] + UDP.

nodes.label: GO:0035598
nodes.Name: N6-threonylcarbomyladenosine methylthiotransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the methylthiolation (-SCH3 addition) at the C2 of the adenosine ring of N6-threonylcarbomyladenosine (t6A) in tRNA, to form 2-methylthio-N6-threonylcarbamoyladenosine (ms2t6A).

nodes.label: GO:0061655
nodes.Name: Pup conjugating enzyme activity
nodes.Definition: Isoenergetic transfer of Pup from one protein to another via the reaction X-Pup + Y = Y-Pup + X, where both the X-Pup and Y-Pup linkages are thioester bonds between the C-terminal amino acid of Pup and a sulfhydryl side group of a cysteine residue.

nodes.label: GO:0052760
nodes.Name: obsolete coenzyme F420-dependent 2,4-dinitrophenol reductase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the reaction: 2,4-dinitrophenol + H- = 2,4-dinitrophenol hydride Meisenheimer complex. Coenzyme F420 supplies the hydride (H-) in the reaction.

nodes.label: GO:0008814
nodes.Name: citrate CoA-transferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: acetyl-CoA + citrate = acetate + (3S)-citryl-CoA.

nodes.label: GO:0000909
nodes.Name: sporocarp development involved in sexual reproduction
nodes.Definition: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a fruiting body organ over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The fruiting body is a spore bearing structure. In fungi, the sporocarp (also known as fruiting body) is a multicellular structure on which spore-producing structures, such as basidia or asci, are borne. The fruiting body is part of the sexual phase of a fungal life cycle, with the rest of the life cycle being characterized by vegetative mycelial growth. The sporocarp of a basidiomycete is known as a basidiocarp, while the fruiting body of an ascomycete is known as an ascocarp. A significant range of different shapes and morphologies is found in both basidiocarps and ascocarps; these features play an important role in the identification and taxonomy of fungi.

nodes.label: GO:1902058
nodes.Name: regulation of sporocarp development involved in sexual reproduction
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of sporocarp development involved in sexual reproduction.

nodes.label: GO:0003987
nodes.Name: acetate-CoA ligase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + acetate + CoA = AMP + diphosphate + acetyl-CoA.

nodes.label: GO:0048742
nodes.Name: regulation of skeletal muscle fiber development
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of skeletal muscle fiber development. Muscle fibers are formed by the maturation of myotubes. They can be classed as slow, intermediate/fast or fast.

nodes.label: GO:0048744
nodes.Name: negative regulation of skeletal muscle fiber development
nodes.Definition: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of skeletal muscle fiber development. Muscle fibers are formed by the maturation of myotubes. They can be classed as slow, intermediate/fast or fast.

nodes.label: GO:0050512
nodes.Name: lactosylceramide 4-alpha-galactosyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: beta-D-galactosyl-(1,4)-D-glucosylceramide + UDP-galactose = alpha-D-galactosyl-(1,4)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1,4)-D-glucosylceramide + UDP.

nodes.label: GO:0043919
nodes.Name: agmatine aminopropyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: agmatine + S-adenosylmethioninamine = N1-aminopropylagmatine + 5'-methylthioadenosine.

nodes.label: GO:0016995
nodes.Name: cholesterol oxidase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: cholesterol + O2 = cholest-5-en-3-one + H2O2.

nodes.label: GO:0047444
nodes.Name: N-acylneuraminate-9-phosphate synthase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: H2O + phosphoenolpyruvate + N-acyl-D-mannosamine 6-phosphate = phosphate + N-acylneuraminate 9-phosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0009785
nodes.Name: blue light signaling pathway
nodes.Definition: The series of molecular signals initiated upon sensing of blue light by photoreceptor molecule, at a wavelength between 400nm and 470nm.

nodes.label: GO:0071483
nodes.Name: cellular response to blue light
nodes.Definition: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a blue light stimulus. Blue light is electromagnetic radiation with a wavelength of between 440 and 500nm.

nodes.label: GO:0004774
nodes.Name: succinate-CoA ligase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: succinate + CoA + nucleotide triphosphate = nucleotide diphosphate + phosphate + succinyl-CoA.

nodes.label: GO:0004775
nodes.Name: succinate-CoA ligase (ADP-forming) activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + succinate + CoA = ADP + succinyl-CoA + phosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0060555
nodes.Name: necroptotic process
nodes.Definition: A programmed necrotic cell death process which begins when a cell receives a signal (e.g. a ligand binding to a death receptor or to a Toll-like receptor), and proceeds through a series of biochemical events (signaling pathways), characterized by activation of receptor-interacting serine/threonine-protein kinase 1 and/or 3 (RIPK1/3, also called RIP1/3) and by critical dependence on mixed lineage kinase domain-like (MLKL), and which typically lead to common morphological features of necrotic cell death. The process ends when the cell has died. The process is divided into a signaling phase, and an execution phase, which is triggered by the former.

nodes.label: GO:0019976
nodes.Name: interleukin-2 binding
nodes.Definition: Binding to interleukin-2.

nodes.label: GO:0010665
nodes.Name: regulation of cardiac muscle cell apoptotic process
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the rate or extent of cardiac cell apoptotic process, a form of programmed cell death induced by external or internal signals that trigger the activity of proteolytic caspases whose actions dismantle a cardiac muscle cell and result in its death.

nodes.label: GO:0050895
nodes.Name: circadian rhythm
nodes.Definition: Any biological process in an organism that recurs with a regularity of approximately 24 hours.

nodes.label: GO:0010347
nodes.Name: L-galactose-1-phosphate phosphatase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: L-galactose-1-phosphate + H2O = L-galactose + phosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0004360
nodes.Name: glutamine-fructose-6-phosphate transaminase (isomerizing) activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: beta-D-fructose 6-phosphate + L-glutamine = D-glucosamine 6-phosphate + L-glutamate.

nodes.label: GO:0055019
nodes.Name: negative regulation of cardiac muscle fiber development
nodes.Definition: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of cardiac muscle fiber development.

nodes.label: GO:0045758
nodes.Name: obsolete positive regulation of actin polymerization and/or depolymerization
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of actin polymerization and/or depolymerization.

nodes.label: GO:0060589
nodes.Name: nucleoside-triphosphatase regulator activity
nodes.Definition: Binds to and modulates the activity of an NTPase.

nodes.label: GO:0050328
nodes.Name: tetrahydroberberine oxidase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: (S)-tetrahydroberberine + 2 O2 = berberine + 2 H2O2.

nodes.label: GO:0060760
nodes.Name: positive regulation of response to cytokine stimulus
nodes.Definition: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of a response to cytokine stimulus.

nodes.label: GO:0003854
nodes.Name: 3-beta-hydroxy-delta5-steroid dehydrogenase (NAD+) activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: a 3-beta-hydroxy-delta(5)-steroid + NAD+ = a 3-oxo-delta(5)-steroid + NADH + H+. Also acts on on 3-beta-hydroxypregn-5-en-20-one to form progesterone.

nodes.label: GO:0036117
nodes.Name: hyaluranon cable
nodes.Definition: A cable structure, surrounding some cell types (e.g. proximal or bronchial tubular epithelial cells), and composed of hyaluranon (HA), a ubiquitous connective tissue glycosaminoglycan.

nodes.label: GO:0009775

nodes.label: GO:0032081

nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Any process that stops or reduces the rate of type II restriction endodeoxyribonuclease activity.

nodes.label: GO:0004576
nodes.Name: oligosaccharyl transferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the transfer of a oligosaccharyl group to an acceptor molecule, typically another carbohydrate or a lipid.

nodes.label: GO:0004579
nodes.Name: dolichyl-diphosphooligosaccharide-protein glycotransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: dolichyl diphosphooligosaccharide + protein L-asparagine = dolichyl diphosphate + a glycoprotein with the oligosaccharide chain attached by glycosylamine linkage to protein L-asparagine.

nodes.label: GO:0071350
nodes.Name: cellular response to interleukin-15
nodes.Definition: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an interleukin-15 stimulus.

nodes.label: GO:0008978
nodes.Name: obsolete prepilin peptidase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the cleavage of a Gly-Phe bond to release an N-terminal, basic peptide of 5-8 residues from type IV prepilin, and then N-methylates the new N-terminal amino group, the methyl donor being S-adenosyl-L-methionine.

nodes.label: GO:0097707
nodes.Name: ferroptosis
nodes.Definition: A programmed cell death characterized morphologically by the presence of smaller than normal mitochondria with condensed mitochondrial membrane densities, reduction or vanishing of mitochondria crista, and outer mitochondrial membrane rupture. Activation of mitochondrial voltage-dependent anion channels and mitogen-activated protein kinases, upregulation of endoplasmic reticulum stress, and inhibition of cystine/glutamate antiporter are involved in the induction of ferroptosis. This process is characterized by the accumulation of lipid peroxidation products and lethal reactive oxygen species (ROS) derived from iron metabolism. Glutathione peroxidase 4 (GPX4), heat shock protein beta-1, and nuclear factor erythroid 2-related factor 2 function as negative regulators of ferroptosis by limiting ROS production and reducing cellular iron uptake, respectively. In contrast, NADPH oxidase and p53 act as positive regulators of ferroptosis by promotion of ROS production and inhibition of expression of SLC7A11 (a specific light-chain subunit of the cystine/glutamate antiporter), respectively. Misregulated ferroptosis has been implicated in multiple physiological and pathological processes.

The execution phase is the last step of an apoptotic process, and is typically characterized by rounding-up of the cell, retraction of pseudopodes, reduction of cellular volume (pyknosis), chromatin condensation, nuclear fragmentation (karyorrhexis), plasma membrane blebbing and fragmentation of the cell into apoptotic bodies. When the execution phase is completed, the cell has died.

nodes.label: GO:0072495
nodes.Name: host cell Cajal body
nodes.Definition: A class of nuclear body in the eukaryotic host cell, first seen after silver staining by Ramon y Cajal in 1903, enriched in small nuclear ribonucleoproteins, and certain general RNA polymerase II transcription factors; ultrastructurally, they appear as a tangle of coiled, electron-dense threads roughly 0.5 micrometers in diameter; involved in aspects of snRNP biogenesis; the protein coilin serves as a marker for Cajal bodies. Some argue that Cajal bodies are the sites for preassembly of transcriptosomes, unitary particles involved in transcription and processing of RNA. The host is the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

nodes.label: GO:0060108
nodes.Name: annular furrow extracellular matrix
nodes.Definition: The extracellular matrix part that is a regularly spaced indentation in the outer cortical layer of the cuticle. The pattern of annular furrows corresponds to sites of invaginations in hypodermal cell membranes that, in turn, correspond to submembranous regions where actin microfilament bundles assemble early in lethargus, the first phase of the molting cycle in which activity and feeding decline.

nodes.label: GO:0052736
nodes.Name: beta-glucanase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of linkages in beta-D-glucans; beta-glucans are polysaccharides of D-glucose monomers linked by beta-glycosidic bonds.

nodes.label: GO:0016041
nodes.Name: glutamate synthase (ferredoxin) activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 2 L-glutamate + 2 oxidized ferredoxin = L-glutamine + 2-oxoglutarate + 2 reduced ferredoxin + 2 H+. This is a two-step reaction: (a) L-glutamate + NH3 = L-glutamine + H2O, (b) L-glutamate + 2 oxidized ferredoxin + H2O = NH3 + 2-oxoglutarate + 2 reduced ferredoxin + 2 H+.

nodes.label: GO:0047136
nodes.Name: 4-(dimethylamino)phenylazoxybenzene reductase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 4-(dimethylamino)azobenzene + H2O + NADP+ = 4-(dimethylamino)phenylazoxybenzene + H+ + NADPH.

nodes.label: GO:1901945
nodes.Name: miltiradiene catabolic process
nodes.Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of miltiradiene.

nodes.label: GO:0097300
nodes.Name: programmed necrotic cell death
nodes.Definition: A necrotic cell death process that results from the activation of endogenous cellular processes, such as signaling involving death domain receptors or Toll-like receptors.

nodes.label: GO:0018860
nodes.Name: anthranilate-CoA ligase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + anthranilate + CoA = AMP + diphosphate + anthranilyl-CoA.

nodes.label: GO:0075249
nodes.Name: positive regulation of aeciospore formation
nodes.Definition: Any process that activates, maintains or increases the frequency, rate or extent of aeciospore formation, a process in which a dikaryotic spore of typically a rust fungus is produced in an aecium.

nodes.label: GO:0075033
nodes.Name: obsolete appressorium septum formation
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. The process in which a symbiont partition is formed to separate the appressorium from the germination tube, occurring during appressorium formation.

nodes.label: GO:0004560
nodes.Name: alpha-L-fucosidase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: an alpha-L-fucoside + H2O = an alcohol + L-fucose.

nodes.label: GO:0033932
nodes.Name: 1,3-alpha-L-fucosidase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of (1->3) linkages between alpha-L-fucose and N-acetylglucosamine residues in glycoproteins.

nodes.label: GO:0004920
nodes.Name: interleukin-10 receptor activity
nodes.Definition: Combining with interleukin-10 and transmitting the signal from one side of the membrane to the other to initiate a change in cell activity.

nodes.label: GO:0005091
nodes.Name: guanyl-nucleotide exchange factor adaptor activity
nodes.Definition: The binding activity of a molecule that brings together a guanyl-nucleotide exchange factor and one or more other proteins, permitting them to function in a coordinated way.

nodes.label: GO:0030695
nodes.Name: GTPase regulator activity
nodes.Definition: Binds to and modulates the activity of a GTPase.

nodes.label: GO:0046987
nodes.Name: N-acetyllactosamine beta-1,3-glucuronosyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the transfer, in a beta 1,3 linkage, of D-glucuronic acid (GlcUA) from UDP-D-glucuronic acid to N-acetyllactosamine (galactosyl beta-1,4-N-acetylglucosamine).

nodes.label: GO:0050541
nodes.Name: beta,beta-carotene-9',10'-dioxygenase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: beta-carotene + O2 = beta-apo-10'-carotenal + beta-ionone.

nodes.label: GO:0004556
nodes.Name: alpha-amylase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the endohydrolysis of (1->4)-alpha-D-glucosidic linkages in polysaccharides containing three or more alpha-(1->4)-linked D-glucose units.

nodes.label: GO:0010656
nodes.Name: negative regulation of muscle cell apoptotic process
nodes.Definition: Any process that decreases the rate or frequency of muscle cell apoptotic process, a form of programmed cell death induced by external or internal signals that trigger the activity of proteolytic caspases whose actions dismantle a muscle cell and result in its death.

nodes.label: GO:0034392
nodes.Name: negative regulation of smooth muscle cell apoptotic process
nodes.Definition: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of smooth muscle cell apoptotic process.

nodes.label: GO:0004865
nodes.Name: protein serine/threonine phosphatase inhibitor activity
nodes.Definition: Binds to and stops, prevents or reduces the activity of a serine/threonine protein phosphatase, an enzyme that catalyzes the reaction: protein serine/threonine phosphate + H2O = protein serine/threonine + phosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0047230
nodes.Name: flavonol-3-O-glucoside L-rhamnosyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: flavonol 3-O-D-glucoside + UDP-L-rhamnose = flavonol 3-O-L-rhamnosylglucoside + UDP.

nodes.label: GO:0008242
nodes.Name: omega peptidase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the cleavage of non-standard peptide bonds releasing substituted amino acids such as pyroglutamate or cleave isopeptide bonds, such as many deubiquitinating enzymes.

nodes.label: GO:0008464
nodes.Name: obsolete gamma-glutamyl hydrolase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the cleavage of a gamma-glutamyl bond to release an unsubstituted C-terminal amino acid.

nodes.label: GO:0018727
nodes.Name: obsolete 2-phenanthrol sulfotransferase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the reaction: 2-phenanthrol + X-SO3(-) = HX + 2-phenanthrylsulfate.

nodes.label: GO:0050102
nodes.Name: cellodextrin phosphorylase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 1,4-beta-D-glucosyl(n) + phosphate = 1,4-beta-D-glucosyl(n-1) + alpha-D-glucose 1-phosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0034390
nodes.Name: smooth muscle cell apoptotic process
nodes.Definition: Any apoptotic process in a smooth muscle cell. Smooth muscle consists of non-striated, elongated, spindle-shaped cell found lining the digestive tract, uterus, and blood vessels.

nodes.label: GO:0006978
nodes.Name: DNA damage response, signal transduction by p53 class mediator resulting in transcription of p21 class mediator
nodes.Definition: A cascade of processes induced by the cell cycle regulator phosphoprotein p53, or an equivalent protein, resulting in the induction of the transcription of p21 (also known as WAF1, CIP1 and SDI1) or any equivalent protein, in response to the detection of DNA damage.

nodes.label: GO:0034369
nodes.Name: plasma lipoprotein particle remodeling
nodes.Definition: The acquisition, loss or modification of a protein or lipid within a plasma lipoprotein particle, including the hydrolysis of triglyceride by hepatic lipase, with the subsequent loss of free fatty acid, and the esterification of cholesterol by phosphatidylcholine-sterol O-acyltransferase (lecithin cholesterol acyltransferase; LCAT).

nodes.label: GO:0034374
nodes.Name: low-density lipoprotein particle remodeling
nodes.Definition: The acquisition, loss or modification of a protein or lipid within a low-density lipoprotein particle, including the hydrolysis of triglyceride by hepatic lipase, with the subsequent loss of free fatty acid, and the transfer of cholesterol esters from LDL to a triglyceride-rich lipoprotein particle by cholesteryl ester transfer protein (CETP), with the simultaneous transfer of triglyceride to LDL.

nodes.label: GO:0071866
nodes.Name: negative regulation of apoptotic process in bone marrow cell
nodes.Definition: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the occurrence or rate of cell death by apoptotic process in the bone marrow.

nodes.label: GO:0043678
nodes.Name: intine
nodes.Definition: The innermost of the major layers of the pollen grain wall which underlies the exine and borders the cytoplasm.

nodes.label: GO:0018547
nodes.Name: obsolete nitroglycerin reductase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the removal of one or more nitrite (NO2-) groups from nitroglycerin or a derivative.

nodes.label: GO:0043057
nodes.Name: backward locomotion
nodes.Definition: Posterior movement of an organism, e.g. following the direction of the tail of an animal.

nodes.label: GO:0043058
nodes.Name: regulation of backward locomotion
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the speed, mechanical force, or rhythm of the posterior movement of an organism.

nodes.label: GO:0075250
nodes.Name: negative regulation of aeciospore formation
nodes.Definition: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of aeciospore formation, a process in which a dikaryotic spore of typically a rust fungus is produced in an aecium.

nodes.label: GO:0016625
nodes.Name: oxidoreductase activity, acting on the aldehyde or oxo group of donors, iron-sulfur protein as acceptor
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which an aldehyde or ketone (oxo) group acts as a hydrogen or electron donor and reduces an iron-sulfur protein.

nodes.label: GO:0047553
nodes.Name: 2-oxoglutarate synthase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 2-oxoglutarate + CoA + oxidized ferredoxin = succinyl-CoA + CO2 + reduced ferredoxin.

nodes.label: GO:0080083
nodes.Name: beta-gentiobiose beta-glucosidase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of glucosidic link in beta-gentiobiose.

nodes.label: GO:0017052
nodes.Name: obsolete insulin-like growth factor binding protein
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. (Was not defined before being made obsolete).

nodes.label: GO:0047557
nodes.Name: 3-aci-nitropropanoate oxidase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 3-aci-nitropropanoate + H2O + O2 = 3-oxopropanoate + H2O2 + nitrite.

nodes.label: GO:0019231
nodes.Name: perception of static position
nodes.Definition: The perception of the orientation of different parts of the body with respect to one another.

nodes.label: GO:0061514
nodes.Name: interleukin-34-mediated signaling pathway
nodes.Definition: The series of molecular signals initiated by interleukin-34 binding to its receptor on the surface of a target cell, and ending with the regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. transcription.

nodes.label: GO:0043912
nodes.Name: obsolete D-lysine oxidase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the reaction: D-lysine + H2O + O2 = 6-amino-2-oxohexanoate + H2O2 + NH4+.

nodes.label: GO:1903264
nodes.Name: obsolete nitrate reductase activity involved in anaerobic electron transport chain
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Any nitrate reductase activity that is involved in anaerobic electron transport chain.

nodes.label: GO:1990444
nodes.Name: F-box domain binding
nodes.Definition: Binding to an F-box domain of a protein.

nodes.label: GO:0018805
nodes.Name: benzylsuccinate synthase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: fumarate + toluene = 2-benzylsuccinate.

nodes.label: GO:0050413
nodes.Name: D-alanine 2-hydroxymethyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 5,10-methylenetetrahydrofolate + D-alanine + H2O = (6S)-5,6,7,8-tetrahydrofolate + 2-methylserine.

nodes.label: GO:0019164
nodes.Name: pyruvate synthase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: pyruvate + CoA + 2 oxidized ferredoxin = acetyl-CoA + CO2 + 2 reduced ferredoxin + 2 H+.

nodes.label: GO:0044813
nodes.Name: glycolytic fermentation via PFOR pathway
nodes.Definition: The glycolytic fermentation beginning with the anaerobic conversion of glucose to pyruvate by the glycolytic pathway, continuing with pyruvate:ferredoxin oxidoreductase (PFOR) activity. This pathway is found in strict anaerobes such as Clostridia species.

nodes.label: GO:1902647
nodes.Name: negative regulation of 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 4,5-bisphosphate biosynthetic process
nodes.Definition: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 4,5-bisphosphate biosynthetic process.

nodes.label: GO:0035457
nodes.Name: cellular response to interferon-alpha
nodes.Definition: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an interferon-alpha stimulus. Interferon-alpha is a type I interferon.

nodes.label: GO:0050967
nodes.Name: detection of electrical stimulus involved in sensory perception of pain
nodes.Definition: The series of events that contribute to the perception of pain in which an electrical stimulus is received and converted into a molecular signal.

nodes.label: GO:0048257
nodes.Name: 3'-flap endonuclease activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the cleavage of a 3' flap structure in DNA, but not other DNA structures; processes the 3' ends of Okazaki fragments in lagging strand DNA synthesis.

nodes.label: GO:0050463
nodes.Name: nitrate reductase [NAD(P)H] activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: nitrite + NAD(P)+ + H2O = nitrate + NAD(P)H + H+.

nodes.label: GO:0075263
nodes.Name: oogonium development
nodes.Definition: The process that leads to the development of an oogonium, a female gametangium of Oomycetes, containing one or more gametes.

nodes.label: GO:2001239
nodes.Name: regulation of extrinsic apoptotic signaling pathway in absence of ligand
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of extrinsic apoptotic signaling pathway in absence of ligand.

nodes.label: GO:0035324
nodes.Name: female germline ring canal
nodes.Definition: An intercellular bridge that connects the germline cells of a female cyst.

nodes.label: GO:0032814
nodes.Name: regulation of natural killer cell activation
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of natural killer cell activation.

nodes.label: GO:0047282
nodes.Name: dTDP-dihydrostreptose-streptidine-6-phosphate dihydrostreptosyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: dTDP-L-dihydrostreptose + streptidine 6-phosphate = O-(1->4)-alpha-L-dihydrostreptosyl-streptidine 6-phosphate + dTDP + H+.

nodes.label: GO:0014886
nodes.Name: transition between slow and fast fiber
nodes.Definition: The process of conversion of slow-contracting muscle fibers to a faster character. This may involve increasing of contractile rate, fast myosin gene induction, increase in glycolytic metabolic properties, altered electrophysiology and altered innervation. This process also regulates skeletal muscle adapatation.

nodes.label: GO:0060933
nodes.Name: His-Purkinje system cell development
nodes.Definition: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a His-Purkinje cell over time, from its formation to the mature state. These cells form the fibers that regulate cardiac muscle contraction in the ventricles.

nodes.label: GO:0050281
nodes.Name: serine-glyoxylate transaminase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: L-serine + glyoxylate = 3-hydroxypyruvate + glycine.

nodes.label: GO:0003762
nodes.Name: obsolete histone-specific chaperone activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Assists in chromatin assembly by chaperoning histones on to replicating DNA, but is not a component of the assembled nucleosome when performing its normal biological function.

nodes.label: GO:0019177
nodes.Name: dihydroneopterin triphosphate pyrophosphohydrolase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: dihydroneopterin triphosphate = dihydroneopterin phosphate + diphosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0071738
nodes.Name: IgD immunoglobulin complex
nodes.Definition: A protein complex composed of two identical immunoglobulin heavy chains of the IgD isotype and two identical immunoglobulin light chains, held together by disulfide bonds. An IgD immunoglobulin complex may be embedded in the plasma membrane or present in the extracellular space, in mucosal areas or other tissues, or circulating in the blood or lymph.

nodes.label: GO:1990144
nodes.Name: intrinsic apoptotic signaling pathway in response to hypoxia
nodes.Definition: The series of molecular signals in which an intracellular signal is conveyed to trigger the apoptotic death of a cell. The pathway is induced in response to hypoxia (lowered oxygen tension). Hypoxia, defined as a decline in O2 levels below normoxic levels of 20.8 - 20.95%, results in metabolic adaptation at both the cellular and organismal level. The pathway ends when the execution phase of apoptosis is triggered.

nodes.label: GO:0003228
nodes.Name: atrial cardiac muscle tissue development
nodes.Definition: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of cardiac muscle of the atrium over time, from its formation to the mature structure.

nodes.label: GO:0055009
nodes.Name: atrial cardiac muscle tissue morphogenesis
nodes.Definition: The process in which the anatomical structure of cardiac atrium muscle is generated and organized.

nodes.label: GO:2000727
nodes.Name: positive regulation of cardiac muscle cell differentiation
nodes.Definition: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of cardiac muscle cell differentiation.

nodes.label: GO:0060297
nodes.Name: regulation of sarcomere organization
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of myofibril assembly by organization of muscle actomyosin into sarcomeres. The sarcomere is the repeating unit of a myofibril in a muscle cell, composed of an array of overlapping thick and thin filaments between two adjacent Z discs.

nodes.label: GO:1903943
nodes.Name: regulation of hepatocyte apoptotic process
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of hepatocyte apoptotic process.

nodes.label: GO:1903945
nodes.Name: positive regulation of hepatocyte apoptotic process
nodes.Definition: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of hepatocyte apoptotic process.

nodes.label: GO:0034520
nodes.Name: obsolete 2-naphthaldehyde dehydrogenase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the reaction: 2-naphthaldehyde + NAD+ + H2O = 2-naphthoate + NADH + H+.

nodes.label: GO:0018522
nodes.Name: benzoyl-CoA reductase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 2 ADP + cyclohexa-1,5-diene-1-carbonyl-CoA + oxidized ferredoxin + 2 phosphate = 2 ATP + 2 H2O + benzoyl-CoA + reduced ferredoxin.

nodes.label: GO:0048307
nodes.Name: ferredoxin-nitrite reductase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: NH3 + 2 H2O + 6 oxidized ferredoxin = nitrite + 6 reduced ferredoxin + 7 H+.

nodes.label: GO:0052593
nodes.Name: obsolete tryptamine:oxygen oxidoreductase (deaminating) activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the reaction: tryptamine + H2O + O2 = NH3 + indole acetaldehyde + hydrogen peroxide + H+.

nodes.label: GO:2001234
nodes.Name: negative regulation of apoptotic signaling pathway
nodes.Definition: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of apoptotic signaling pathway.

nodes.label: GO:0047639
nodes.Name: alcohol oxidase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: a primary alcohol + O2 = an aldehyde + H2O2.

nodes.label: GO:0103105
nodes.Name: 2-oxo-6-methylthiohexanoate aminotransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 2-oxo-6-methylthiohexanoate + a standard alpha amino acid = dihomomethionine + a 2-oxo carboxylate.

nodes.label: GO:0019962
nodes.Name: type I interferon binding
nodes.Definition: Binding to a type I interferon. Type I interferons include the interferon-alpha, beta, delta, epsilon, zeta, kappa, tau, and omega gene families.

nodes.label: GO:0043891
nodes.Name: glyceraldehyde-3-phosphate dehydrogenase [NAD(P)+] (phosphorylating) activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: D-glyceraldehyde 3-phosphate + phosphate + NAD(P)+ = 3-phospho-D-glyceroyl phosphate + NAD(P)H + H+.

nodes.label: GO:0070999
nodes.Name: detection of mechanical stimulus involved in sensory perception of gravity
nodes.Definition: The series of events involved in the perception of gravity in which a sensory mechanical stimulus is received and converted into a molecular signal.

nodes.label: GO:1900625
nodes.Name: positive regulation of monocyte aggregation
nodes.Definition: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of monocyte aggregation.

nodes.label: GO:0044231
nodes.Name: host cell presynaptic membrane
nodes.Definition: A specialized area of membrane of the host axon terminal that faces the plasma membrane of the host neuron or muscle fiber with which the axon terminal establishes a synaptic junction; many host synaptic junctions exhibit structural presynaptic characteristics, such as conical, electron-dense internal protrusions, that distinguish it from the remainder of the axon plasma membrane.

nodes.label: GO:0047405
nodes.Name: pyrimidine-5'-nucleotide nucleosidase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: H2O + a pyrimidine 5'-nucleotide = ribose-5-phosphate + a pyrimidine.

nodes.label: GO:0043512
nodes.Name: inhibin A complex
nodes.Definition: Heterodimeric hormone composed of an inhibin alpha subunit complexed with an inhibin beta-A subunit.

nodes.label: GO:0047785
nodes.Name: cortisol sulfotransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 3'-phospho-5'-adenylyl sulfate + cortisol = adenosine 3',5'-diphosphate + cortisol 21-sulfate + H+.

nodes.label: GO:0061743
nodes.Name: motor learning
nodes.Definition: Any process in which an organism acquires a novel neuromuscular action or movement as the result of experience.

nodes.label: GO:0038156
nodes.Name: interleukin-3-mediated signaling pathway
nodes.Definition: The series of molecular signals initiated by interleukin-3 binding to its receptor on the surface of a target cell, and ending with the regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. transcription.

nodes.label: GO:0001844
nodes.Name: obsolete protein insertion into mitochondrial membrane involved in apoptotic signaling pathway
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. The process in which a protein is incorporated into a mitochondrial membrane as the initial phase of the mitochondrial membrane permeabilization that takes place in the apoptotic signaling pathway.

nodes.label: GO:0075234
nodes.Name: obsolete zoospore movement on or near host
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Any process involved in the directed movement of a zoospore on or near its host organism. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

nodes.label: GO:0075236
nodes.Name: obsolete positive regulation of zoospore movement on or near host
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Any process that activates, maintains or increases the frequency, rate or extent of zoospore movement on or near its host organism. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

nodes.label: GO:0004234
nodes.Name: obsolete macrophage elastase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the hydrolysis of soluble and insoluble elastin. Specific cleavages are also produced at Ala14-Leu15 and Tyr16-Leu17 in the B chain of insulin.

nodes.label: GO:0090161
nodes.Name: Golgi ribbon formation
nodes.Definition: The formation of a continuous ribbon of interconnected Golgi stacks of flat cisternae.

nodes.label: GO:1904156
nodes.Name: DN3 thymocyte differentiation
nodes.Definition: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires the specialized features of a DN3 thymocyte. A DN3 thymocyte is a CD4-,CD8- thymocyte that is also CD44+,CD25+.

nodes.label: GO:0001779
nodes.Name: natural killer cell differentiation
nodes.Definition: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires the specialized features of a natural killer cell.

nodes.label: GO:0047124
nodes.Name: L-erythro-3,5-diaminohexanoate dehydrogenase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: (3S,5S)-3,5-diaminohexanoate + H2O + NAD+ = (S)-5-amino-3-oxo-hexanoate + H+ + NADH + NH4.

nodes.label: GO:0070555
nodes.Name: response to interleukin-1
nodes.Definition: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an interleukin-1 stimulus.

nodes.label: GO:0000704
nodes.Name: pyrimidine dimer DNA N-glycosylase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the removal of pyrimidine dimers by removing the 5' pyrimidine of the dimer by cleaving the N-C1' glycosidic bond between the 5' pyrimidine of the dimer and the deoxyribose sugar. The reaction releases the 5' pyrimidine of the dimer and leaves an apurinic (AP) site. The reaction involves the formation of a covalent enzyme substrate intermediate. Release of the enzyme and free base by a beta-elimination or a beta, gamma-elimination mechanism results in the cleavage of the DNA backbone 3' of the apyrimidinic (AP) site.

nodes.label: GO:0014711
nodes.Name: regulation of branchiomeric skeletal muscle development
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of branchiomeric skeletal muscle development. Branchiomeric skeletal muscle development is the process whose specific outcome is the progression of the branchiomeric skeletal muscle over time, from its formation to the mature structure.

nodes.label: GO:0035248
nodes.Name: alpha-1,4-N-acetylgalactosaminyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the transfer of an N-acetylgalactosaminyl residue from UDP-N-acetyl-galactosamine to an acceptor molecule, forming an alpha-1,4 linkage.

nodes.label: GO:0047624
nodes.Name: adenosine-tetraphosphatase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: adenosine 5'-tetraphosphate + H2O = ATP + phosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0039630
nodes.Name: RNA translocase activity
nodes.Definition: Generating a movement along a single- or double-stranded RNA molecule, driven by ATP hydrolysis.

nodes.label: GO:1904326
nodes.Name: negative regulation of circadian sleep/wake cycle, wakefulness
nodes.Definition: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of circadian sleep/wake cycle, wakefulness.

nodes.label: GO:1904359
nodes.Name: regulation of spore germination
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of spore germination.

nodes.label: GO:0098627
nodes.Name: protein arginine phosphatase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: phospho-L-arginyl-[protein] +H2O = L-arginyl-[protein] + phosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0098628
nodes.Name: peptidyl-N-phospho-arginine dephosphorylation
nodes.Definition: The removal of phosphate residues from peptidyl-N-phospho-arginine to form peptidyl-arginine.

nodes.label: GO:0047925
nodes.Name: geranoyl-CoA carboxylase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + bicarbonate + geranoyl-CoA = 3-(4-methylpent-3-en-1-yl)pent-2-enedioyl-CoA + ADP + 2 H+ + phosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0047208
nodes.Name: o-dihydroxycoumarin 7-O-glucosyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 7,8-dihydroxycoumarin + UDP-D-glucose = daphnin + H+ + UDP.

nodes.label: GO:0070139
nodes.Name: SUMO-specific endopeptidase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of peptide bonds between an alpha-carboxyl group and an alpha-amino group within the small conjugating protein SUMO.

nodes.label: GO:0070102
nodes.Name: interleukin-6-mediated signaling pathway
nodes.Definition: The series of molecular signals initiated by interleukin-6 binding to a receptor on the surface of a target cell, and ending with the regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. transcription.

nodes.label: GO:0050972
nodes.Name: detection of mechanical stimulus involved in echolocation
nodes.Definition: The series of events involved in echolocation in which a mechanical stimulus is received and converted into a molecular signal. The stimulus is in the form of a reflected sound wave (an echo), which the organism uses to determine the distance to the object that reflected the sound wave.

nodes.label: GO:0051922
nodes.Name: cholesterol sulfotransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 3'-phosphoadenylyl sulfate + cholesterol = adenosine 3',5'-bisphosphate + cholesterol sulfate + H+.

nodes.label: GO:1900720
nodes.Name: negative regulation of uterine smooth muscle relaxation
nodes.Definition: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of uterine smooth muscle relaxation.

nodes.label: GO:0033653
nodes.Name: host cell chloroplast part
nodes.Definition: Any constituent part of a chloroplast as it is found in host cells and which are a chlorophyll-containing plastid with thylakoids organized into grana and frets, or stroma thylakoids, and embedded in a stroma. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

nodes.label: GO:0033654
nodes.Name: host cell chloroplast thylakoid membrane
nodes.Definition: Any sac-like membranous structures (cisternae) in a chloroplast found in host cells, combined into stacks (grana) and present singly in the stroma (stroma thylakoids or frets) as interconnections between grana. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

nodes.label: GO:0007121
nodes.Name: bipolar cellular bud site selection
nodes.Definition: The process of defining subsequent sites of bud emergence such that budding takes place at alternating poles of a budding cell.

nodes.label: GO:0051675

nodes.label: GO:0010114
nodes.Name: response to red light
nodes.Definition: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a red light stimulus. Red light is electromagnetic radiation of wavelength of 580-700nm. An example of this response is seen at the beginning of many plant species developmental stages. These include germination, and the point when cotyledon expansion is triggered. In certain species these processes take place in response to absorption of red light by the pigment molecule phytochrome, but the signal can be reversed by exposure to far red light. During the initial phase the phytochrome molecule is only present in the red light absorbing form, but on absorption of red light it changes to a far red light absorbing form, triggering progress through development. An immediate short period of exposure to far red light entirely returns the pigment to its initial state and prevents triggering of the developmental process. A thirty minute break between red and subsequent far red light exposure renders the red light effect irreversible, and development then occurs regardless of whether far red light exposure subsequently occurs.

nodes.label: GO:0019234
nodes.Name: sensory perception of fast pain
nodes.Definition: The series of events required for an organism to receive a fast pain stimulus, convert it to a molecular signal, and recognize and characterize the signal. This is a neurological process. Fast pain is often subjectively described as a sharp or stabbing pain; in humans, the signals from a fast pain stimulus are perceived and relayed along myelinated A-delta fibers to the central nervous system, reaching their target in about 0.1 seconds.

nodes.label: GO:0019235
nodes.Name: sensory perception of slow pain
nodes.Definition: The series of events required for an organism to receive a slow pain stimulus, convert it to a molecular signal, and recognize and characterize the signal. This is a neurological process. Slow pain is often subjectively described as an aching or throbbing pain; in humans, the signals from a slow pain stimulus are perceived and relayed along unmyelinated C fibers to the central nervous system, reaching their target in about 1 second. Slow pain is often associated with tissue destruction.

nodes.label: GO:0019956

nodes.Definition: Binding to a chemokine. Chemokines are a family of small chemotactic cytokines; their name is derived from their ability to induce directed chemotaxis in nearby responsive cells. All chemokines possess a number of conserved cysteine residues involved in intramolecular disulfide bond formation. Some chemokines are considered pro-inflammatory and can be induced during an immune response to recruit cells of the immune system to a site of infection, while others are considered homeostatic and are involved in controlling the migration of cells during normal processes of tissue maintenance or development. Chemokines are found in all vertebrates, some viruses and some bacteria.

nodes.Definition: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a gamma radiation stimulus. Gamma radiation is a form of electromagnetic radiation (EMR) or light emission of a specific frequency produced from sub-atomic particle interaction, such as electron-positron annihilation and radioactive decay. Gamma rays are generally characterized as EMR having the highest frequency and energy, and also the shortest wavelength, within the electromagnetic radiation spectrum.

IDL particles are found in blood and are formed by the delipidation of very-low-density lipoprotein particles (VLDL). IDL particles are removed from blood by the liver, following binding to the APOE receptor, or are converted to low-density lipoprotein (LDL).

nodes.label: GO:0034932
nodes.Name: obsolete 1-methoxypyrene 6,7-monooxygenase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the reaction: 1-methoxypyrene + O2 + 2 H+ + 2 e- = 1-methoxypyrene-6,7-oxide + H2O.

nodes.label: GO:0008782
nodes.Name: adenosylhomocysteine nucleosidase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + H2O = adenine + S-D-ribosyl-L-homocysteine.

nodes.label: GO:0047292
nodes.Name: trihydroxypterocarpan dimethylallyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: (6AS,11AS)-3,6A,9-trihydroxypterocarpan + dimethylallyl-pyrophosphate = glyceollin + diphosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0018127
nodes.Name: obsolete NAD(P)-serine ADP-ribosyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the reaction: NAD(P)+ + L-serine = nicotinamide + N2-(ADP-D-ribosyl)-L-serine.

nodes.label: GO:0047442
nodes.Name: obsolete 17-alpha-hydroxyprogesterone aldolase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the reaction: 17alpha-hydroxyprogesterone + O2 + reduced NADPH--hemoprotein reductase = acetate + androst-4-ene-3,17-dione + 2 H+ + H2O + oxidized NADPH--hemoprotein reductase.

nodes.label: GO:0033074
nodes.Name: pinene catabolic process
nodes.Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways leading to the breakdown of the monoterpenoid pinene; alpha-pinene is (1S,5S)-2,6,6-trimethylbicyclo[3.1.1]hept-2-ene, and beta-pinene is (1S,5S)-6,6-dimethyl-2-methylenebicyclo[3.1.1]heptane.

nodes.label: GO:0048630
nodes.Name: skeletal muscle tissue growth
nodes.Definition: The increase in size or mass of a skeletal muscle. This may be due to a change in the fiber number or size.

nodes.label: GO:0033914
nodes.Name: xylan 1,3-beta-xylosidase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of successive xylose residues from the non-reducing termini of (1->3)-beta-D-xylans.

nodes.label: GO:1904763
nodes.Name: chaperone-mediated autophagy translocation complex assembly
nodes.Definition: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form a chaperone-mediated autophagy translocation complex.

nodes.label: GO:0014863
nodes.Name: detection of inactivity
nodes.Definition: The series of events in which a inactivity stimulus is received by a cell or organism and converted into a molecular signal.

nodes.label: GO:0042129
nodes.Name: regulation of T cell proliferation
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of T cell proliferation.

nodes.label: GO:0075308
nodes.Name: negative regulation of conidium formation
nodes.Definition: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of conidium formation, a process of producing non-motile spores, called conidia, via mitotic asexual reproduction in higher fungi. Conidia are haploid cells genetically identical to their haploid parent. They are produced by conversion of hyphal elements, or are borne on sporogenous cells on or within specialized structures termed conidiophores, and participate in dispersal of the fungus.

nodes.label: GO:0019232
nodes.Name: perception of rate of movement
nodes.Definition: The series of events by which an organism senses the speed and direction of movement of the body and its parts.

nodes.label: GO:0035981
nodes.Name: tongue muscle cell differentiation
nodes.Definition: The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a tongue muscle cell.

nodes.label: GO:0036494
nodes.Name: positive regulation of translation initiation in response to endoplasmic reticulum stress
nodes.Definition: Any process that activates, or increases the frequency, rate or extent of translation initiation as a result of endoplasmic reticulum stress.

nodes.label: GO:1901081
nodes.Name: negative regulation of relaxation of smooth muscle
nodes.Definition: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of relaxation of smooth muscle.

nodes.label: GO:0004079
nodes.Name: obsolete biotin-[methylmalonyl-CoA-carboxytransferase] ligase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + biotin + apo-(methylmalonyl-CoA:pyruvate carboxytransferase) = AMP + diphosphate + (methylmalonyl-CoA:pyruvate carboxytransferase).

nodes.label: GO:0008160
nodes.Name: protein tyrosine phosphatase activator activity
nodes.Definition: Binds to and increases the activity of a phosphotyrosine phosphatase, an enzyme which catalyzes of the removal of a phosphate group from a tyrosyl phenolic group of a protein.

nodes.label: GO:0051602
nodes.Name: response to electrical stimulus
nodes.Definition: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an electrical stimulus.

nodes.label: GO:0018497
nodes.Name: obsolete 1-chloro-2,2-bis(4-chlorophenyl)ethane dehydrogenase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the reaction: 1-chloro-2,2-bis(4-chlorophenyl)ethene + 2 H+ + 2 e- = 1-chloro-2,2-bis(4-chlorophenyl)ethane. 1-chloro-2,2-bis(4-chlorophenyl)ethene is also known as DDMU; 1-chloro-2,2-bis(4-chlorophenyl)ethane is also known as DDMS.

nodes.label: GO:0075020
nodes.Name: obsolete calcium or calmodulin-mediated activation of appressorium formation
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of symbiont calcium or calmodulin-mediated signal transduction during appressorium formation on or near its host organism. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

nodes.label: GO:0044535
nodes.Name: very-long-chain fatty acyl-CoA oxidase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: very-long-chain fatty acyl-CoA (C22 - C24) + O2 = trans-2,3-dehydroacyl-CoA + hydrogen peroxide.

nodes.label: GO:1990053
nodes.Name: DNA-5-methylcytosine glycosylase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: DNA containing 5-methylcytosine + H2O = DNA with abasic site + 5-methylcytosine. This reaction is the hydrolysis of DNA by cleavage of the N-C1' glycosidic bond between the DNA 5-methylcytosine and the deoxyribose sugar to remove the 5-methylcytosine, leaving an abasic site.

nodes.label: GO:2000841
nodes.Name: negative regulation of dehydroepiandrosterone secretion
nodes.Definition: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of dehydroepiandrosterone secretion.

nodes.label: GO:0047219
nodes.Name: monoterpenol beta-glucosyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: (-)-menthol + UDP-D-glucose = (-)-menthyl beta-D-glucoside + H+ + UDP.

nodes.label: GO:0061641
nodes.Name: CENP-A containing chromatin assembly
nodes.Definition: The formation of chromatin containing the histone H3 variant CENP-A to form centromeric chromatin. This specialised chromatin occurs at centromeric region in point centromeres, and the central core in modular centromeres.

nodes.label: GO:0001770
nodes.Name: establishment of natural killer cell polarity
nodes.Definition: The directed orientation of natural killer cell signaling molecules and associated membrane rafts towards a chemokine gradient or a contact point with a cell displaying natural killer cell activating ligands.

nodes.label: GO:0007014
nodes.Name: actin ubiquitination
nodes.Definition: The modification of actin by addition of ubiquitin groups.

nodes.label: GO:0033933
nodes.Name: branched-dextran exo-1,2-alpha-glucosidase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of (1->2)-alpha-D-glucosidic linkages at the branch points of dextrans and related polysaccharides, producing free D-glucose.

nodes.label: GO:0097083
nodes.Name: vascular associated smooth muscle cell fate determination
nodes.Definition: The process in which a cell becomes capable of differentiating autonomously into a vascular smooth muscle cell regardless of its environment; upon determination, the cell fate cannot be reversed. A vascular smooth muscle cell is a non-striated, elongated, spindle-shaped cell found lining the blood vessels.

nodes.label: GO:0097382
nodes.Name: obsolete deoxynucleoside-diphosphatase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the reaction: a deoxynucleoside diphosphate + H2O = a deoxynucleotide + phosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0004835
nodes.Name: tubulin-tyrosine ligase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + detyrosinated alpha-tubulin + L-tyrosine = alpha-tubulin + ADP + phosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0047253
nodes.Name: alpha-1,6-mannosylglycoprotein 4-beta-N-acetylglucosaminyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-1,6-beta-D-(N-acetyl-B-glucosaminyl-1,2)-beta-D-mannosyl-R + UDP-N-acetyl-D-glucosamine = N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-1,6-beta-D-(N-acetyl-D-glucosaminyl-1,2-beta)-(N-acetyl-D-glucosaminyl-1,4-beta)-D-mannosyl-R + UDP.

nodes.label: GO:0035446
nodes.Name: cysteine-glucosaminylinositol ligase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 1-(2-amino-2-deoxy-alpha-D-glucopyranoside)-1D-myo-inositol + L-cysteine + ATP = 1-D-myo-inosityl-2-L-cysteinylamido-2-deoxy-alpha-D-glucopyranoside + AMP + diphosphate + 2 H+. 1-(2-amino-2-deoxy-alpha-D-glucopyranoside)-1D-myo-inositol is also known as glucosaminyl-inositol or GlcN-Ins, and 1-D-myo-inosityl-2-L-cysteinylamido-2-deoxy-alpha-D-glucopyranoside as desacetylmycothiol or Cys-GlcN-Ins.

nodes.label: GO:0008992
nodes.Name: obsolete repressor LexA activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the hydrolysis of Ala-Gly bond in repressor lexA.

nodes.label: GO:0047569
nodes.Name: 3-oxoadipate CoA-transferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: succinyl-CoA + 3-oxoadipate = succinate + 3-oxoadipyl-CoA.

nodes.label: GO:2001265
nodes.Name: positive regulation of C-C chemokine binding
nodes.Definition: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of C-C chemokine binding.

nodes.label: GO:0042392
nodes.Name: sphingosine-1-phosphate phosphatase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: sphingosine 1-phosphate + H2O = sphingosine + phosphate.

nodes.label: GO:1902633
nodes.Name: 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 4,5-bisphosphate metabolic process
nodes.Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways involving 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 4,5-bisphosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0038115
nodes.Name: chemokine (C-C motif) ligand 19 signaling pathway
nodes.Definition: The series of molecular signals initiated by the binding of the C-C chemokine CCL19 to its receptor on the surface of a target cell, and ending with the regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. transcription.

nodes.label: GO:0038119
nodes.Name: CCL19-activated CCR7 signaling pathway
nodes.Definition: The series of molecular signals initiated by the binding of the C-C chemokine CCL19 to a C-C chemokine type 7 receptor (CCR7) on the surface of a target cell, and ending with the regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. transcription.

nodes.label: GO:0061712
nodes.Name: tRNA (N(6)-L-threonylcarbamoyladenosine(37)-C(2))-methylthiotransferase
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: N(6)-L-threonylcarbamoyladenine(37) in tRNA + sulfur-(sulfur carrier) + 2 S-adenosyl-L-methionine = 2-methylthio-N(6)-L-threonylcarbamoyladenine(37) in tRNA + S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + (sulfur carrier) + L-methionine + 5'-deoxyadenosine.

nodes.label: GO:0047480
nodes.Name: UDP-N-acetylmuramoyl-tripeptide-D-alanyl-D-alanine ligase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: UDP-N-acetylmuramoyl-L-alanyl-D-glutamyl-L-lysine + ATP + D-alanyl-D-alanine = phosphate + UDP-N-acetylmuramoyl-L-alanyl-D-glutamyl-L-lysyl-D-alanyl-D-alanine + ADP.

nodes.label: GO:0018859
nodes.Name: 4-hydroxybenzoate-CoA ligase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + 4-hydroxybenzoate + CoA = AMP + diphosphate + 4-hydroxybenzoyl-CoA.

nodes.label: GO:1902043
nodes.Name: positive regulation of extrinsic apoptotic signaling pathway via death domain receptors
nodes.Definition: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of extrinsic apoptotic signaling pathway via death domain receptors.

nodes.label: GO:0047283
nodes.Name: dolichyl-phosphate D-xylosyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: dolichol-phosphate + UDP-D-xylose = dolichyl D-xylosyl phosphate + UDP.

nodes.label: GO:0033935
nodes.Name: oligoxyloglucan beta-glycosidase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of (1->4)-beta-D-glucosidic links in oligoxyloglucans so as to remove successive isoprimeverose (i.e. alpha-xylo-1,6-beta-D-glucosyl-) residues from the non-reducing chain ends.

nodes.label: GO:0035851
nodes.Name: Krueppel-associated box domain binding
nodes.Definition: Binding to a Krueppel-associated box (KRAB) domain of a protein. The approximately 75 amino acid KRAB domain is enriched in charged amino acids, and is found in the N-terminal regions of many zinc finger-containing transcription factors.

nodes.label: GO:0052096
nodes.Name: formation of syncytium involving giant cell for nutrient acquisition
nodes.Definition: The assembly of a syncytium, a multi-nucleate and physiologically active aggregation of fused root cells induced by a symbiotic nematode in a plant host. The syncytium exclusively provides the nematode with nourishment during its sedentary life, for the purpose of obtaining nutrients from its host organism. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

nodes.label: GO:0034849
nodes.Name: obsolete 2-naphthoate CoA-transferase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the reaction: 2-naphthoyl-CoA + OH- = 2-naphthoate + CoASH.

nodes.label: GO:0003830
nodes.Name: beta-1,4-mannosylglycoprotein 4-beta-N-acetylglucosaminyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: UDP-N-acetyl-D-glucosamine + beta-D-mannosyl-R = UDP + 4-(N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl)-beta-D-mannosyl-R.

nodes.label: GO:0061666
nodes.Name: UFM1 ligase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the transfer of UFM1 to a substrate protein via the reaction X-UFM1 + S = X + S-UFM1, where X is either an E2 or E3 enzyme, the X-UFM1 linkage is a thioester bond, and the S-UFM1 linkage is an isopeptide bond between the C-terminal amino acid of UFM1 and the epsilon-amino group of lysine residues in the substrate.

nodes.label: GO:0006336
nodes.Name: chromatin organization
nodes.Definition: The assembly or remodeling of chromatin composed of DNA complexed with histones, other associated proteins, and sometimes RNA.

nodes.label: GO:0008672
nodes.Name: 2-dehydro-3-deoxyglucarate aldolase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 2-dehydro-3-deoxy-D-glucarate = pyruvate + tartronate semialdehyde.

nodes.label: GO:0004231
nodes.Name: obsolete insulysin activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the degradation of insulin, glucagon and other polypeptides. No action on proteins.

nodes.label: GO:0030568
nodes.Name: obsolete plasmin inhibitor activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Stops, prevents or reduces the activity of the serine endopeptidase plasmin.

nodes.label: GO:0061631
nodes.Name: ubiquitin conjugating enzyme activity
nodes.Definition: Isoenergetic transfer of ubiquitin from one protein to another via the reaction X-ubiquitin + Y = Y-ubiquitin + X, where both the X-ubiquitin and Y-ubiquitin linkages are thioester bonds between the C-terminal glycine of ubiquitin and a sulfhydryl side group of a cysteine residue.

nodes.label: GO:0016495
nodes.Name: C-X3-C chemokine receptor activity
nodes.Definition: Combining with a C-X3-C chemokine and transmitting the signal from one side of the membrane to the other to initiate a change in cell activity. A C-X3-C chemokine has three amino acids between the first two cysteines of the characteristic four-cysteine motif.

nodes.label: GO:0080071
nodes.Name: indol-3-yl-methyl-desulfoglucosinolate sulfotransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: indol-3-yl-methyl-desulfoglucosinolate + 3'-phosphoadenosine 5'-phosphosulfate = indol-3-yl-methyl-glucosinolate + adenosine 3',5'-bisphosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0090201
nodes.Name: negative regulation of release of cytochrome c from mitochondria
nodes.Definition: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of release of cytochrome c from mitochondria, the process in which cytochrome c is enabled to move from the mitochondrial intermembrane space into the cytosol, which is an early step in apoptosis and leads to caspase activation.

nodes.label: GO:0004182
nodes.Name: obsolete carboxypeptidase A activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the reaction: peptidyl-L-amino acid + H2O = peptide + L-amino acid. Little or no action with -Asp, -Glu, -Arg, -Lys or -Pro.

nodes.label: GO:0052108
nodes.Name: obsolete growth or development of symbiont during interaction with host
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. The increase in size or mass of an organism, or the progression of an organism from an initial condition to a later condition, occurring in, on or near the exterior of its host organism. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

nodes.label: GO:0032861
nodes.Name: activation of GTPase activity
nodes.Definition: Any process that initiates the activity of an inactive GTPase through the replacement of GDP by GTP.

nodes.label: GO:0033899
nodes.Name: ribonuclease U2 activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the two-stage endonucleolytic cleavage to nucleoside 3'-phosphates and 3'-phosphooligonucleotides ending in Ap or Gp with 2',3'-cyclic phosphate intermediates.

nodes.label: GO:0008125
nodes.Name: obsolete pancreatic elastase I activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the hydrolysis of proteins, including elastin. Preferential cleavage: Ala-Xaa.

nodes.label: GO:0035689
nodes.Name: chemokine (C-C motif) ligand 5 signaling pathway
nodes.Definition: The series of molecular signals initiated by chemokine CCL5 binding to its receptor on the surface of a target cell, and ending with the regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. transcription.

nodes.label: GO:1903973
nodes.Name: negative regulation of cellular response to macrophage colony-stimulating factor stimulus
nodes.Definition: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of cellular response to macrophage colony-stimulating factor stimulus.

nodes.label: GO:0061162
nodes.Name: establishment of monopolar cell polarity
nodes.Definition: The specification and formation of monopolar intracellular organization or cell growth patterns. Monopolar cell organization is directional organization along an axis.

nodes.label: GO:0004350
nodes.Name: glutamate-5-semialdehyde dehydrogenase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: L-glutamate 5-semialdehyde + NADP+ + phosphate = L-glutamyl 5-phosphate + H+ + NADPH.

nodes.label: GO:0050510
nodes.Name: N-acetylgalactosaminyl-proteoglycan 3-beta-glucuronosyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosaminyl-(1,4)-beta-D-glucuronosyl-proteoglycan + UDP-alpha-D-glucuronate = beta-D-glucuronosyl-(1,3)-N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosaminyl-(1,4)-beta-D-glucuronosyl-proteoglycan + UDP.

nodes.label: GO:1901174
nodes.Name: phytoene biosynthetic process
nodes.Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of phytoene.

nodes.label: GO:1901936
nodes.Name: beta-caryophyllene catabolic process
nodes.Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of beta-caryophyllene.

nodes.label: GO:0010611
nodes.Name: regulation of cardiac muscle hypertrophy
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of the enlargement or overgrowth of all or part of the heart due to an increase in size (not length) of individual cardiac muscle fibers, without cell division.

nodes.label: GO:0010293
nodes.Name: abscisic aldehyde oxidase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: a 2-cis-(+)-abscisic aldehyde + H2O + O2 = 2-cis-(+)-abscisate + H+ + H2O2.

nodes.label: GO:0018488
nodes.Name: aryl-aldehyde oxidase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: an aromatic aldehyde + O2 + H2O = an aromatic acid + hydrogen peroxide.

nodes.label: GO:0047627
nodes.Name: adenylylsulfatase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 5'-adenylyl sulfate + H2O = AMP + 2 H+ + sulfate.

nodes.label: GO:0097395
nodes.Name: response to interleukin-32
nodes.Definition: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an interleukin-32 stimulus.

nodes.label: GO:0035314
nodes.Name: scab formation
nodes.Definition: Formation of hardened covering (a scab) at a wound site. The scab has multiple functions including limiting blood loss, providing structural stability to the wound and guarding against infection.

nodes.label: GO:0061661
nodes.Name: FAT10 ligase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the transfer of FAT10 to a substrate protein via the reaction X-FAT10 + S = X + S-FAT10, where X is either an E2 or E3 enzyme, the X-FAT10 linkage is a thioester bond, and the S-FAT10 linkage is an isopeptide bond between the C-terminal glycine of FAT10 and the epsilon-amino group of lysine residues in the substrate.

nodes.label: GO:0004214
nodes.Name: obsolete dipeptidyl-peptidase I activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the release of an N-terminal dipeptide, Xaa-Xbb from Xaa-Xbb-Xcc, except when Xaa is Arg or Lys, or Xbb or Xcc is Pro.

nodes.label: GO:0048081
nodes.Name: positive regulation of cuticle pigmentation
nodes.Definition: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of establishment of a pattern of pigment in the cuticle of an organism.

nodes.label: GO:0035501
nodes.Name: MH1 domain binding
nodes.Definition: Binding to a MH1 (MAD homology 1) protein domain. The MH1 domain is found at the amino terminus of MAD related proteins such as Smads and can mediate DNA binding in some proteins. Smads also use the MH1 domain to interact with some transcription factors.

nodes.label: GO:0042972
nodes.Name: licheninase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of (1->4)-beta-D-glucosidic linkages in beta-D-glucans containing (1->3) and (1->4) bonds.

nodes.label: GO:0036424
nodes.Name: L-phosphoserine phosphatase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: O-phospho-L-serine + H2O = L-serine + phosphate, on a free amino acid.

nodes.label: GO:0080116
nodes.Name: glucuronoxylan glucuronosyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the transfer of glucuronate to the xylan backbone of glucuronoxylan molecule.

nodes.label: GO:0050071
nodes.Name: phosphatidylglycerol lysyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1'-sn-glycerol) + L-lysyl-tRNA(Lys) = 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-1'-(3'-O-L-lysyl)-sn-glycerol + tRNA(Lys).

nodes.label: GO:1990643
nodes.Name: cellular response to granulocyte colony-stimulating factor
nodes.Definition: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a granulocyte colony-stimulating factor stimulus.

nodes.label: GO:0032851
nodes.Name: positive regulation of GTPase activity
nodes.Definition: Any process that activates or increases the activity of a GTPase.

nodes.label: GO:1902794
nodes.Name: siRNA-independent facultative heterochromatin formation
nodes.Definition: The formation of facultative heterochromatin into a heterochromatin domain, enriched in histone H3 methylated on lysine 9 (H3K9me), by a process independent of small interfering RNAs.

nodes.label: GO:0090541
nodes.Name: MIT domain binding
nodes.Definition: Binding to a MIT protein domain. The MIT domain is found in vacuolar sorting proteins, spastin (probable ATPase involved in the assembly or function of nuclear protein complexes), and a sorting nexin, which may play a role in intracellular trafficking.

nodes.label: GO:0034852
nodes.Name: obsolete 4,4-dimethyl-3-oxopentanal dehydrogenase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the reaction: 4,4-dimethyl-3-oxopentanal + H2O = 4,4-dimethyl-3-oxopentanoate + 3 H+ + 2 e-.

nodes.label: GO:0090326
nodes.Name: positive regulation of locomotion involved in locomotory behavior
nodes.Definition: Any process that increases the frequency, rate, or extent of the self-propelled movement of a cell or organism from one location to another in a behavioral context; the aspect of locomotory behavior having to do with movement.

nodes.label: GO:0038121
nodes.Name: C-C motif chemokine 21 receptor activity
nodes.Definition: Combining with the C-C motif chemokine 21 (CCL21) and transmitting the signal from one side of the membrane to the other to initiate a change in cell activity.

nodes.label: GO:0052657
nodes.Name: guanine phosphoribosyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: GMP + diphosphate = guanine + 5-phospho-alpha-D-ribose 1-diphosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0000310
nodes.Name: xanthine phosphoribosyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 5-phospho-alpha-D-ribose 1-diphosphate + xanthine = (9-D-ribosylxanthine)-5'-phosphate + diphosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0009043
nodes.Name: xanthine phosphoribosyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 5-phospho-alpha-D-ribose 1-diphosphate + xanthine = (9-D-ribosylxanthine)-5'-phosphate + diphosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0050408
nodes.Name: [pyruvate kinase]-phosphatase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: [pyruvate kinase] phosphate + H2O = [pyruvate kinase] + phosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0009646
nodes.Name: response to absence of light
nodes.Definition: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an absence of light stimuli.

nodes.label: GO:0009647
nodes.Name: skotomorphogenesis
nodes.Definition: The control of plant growth, development, and differentiation in response to growth in darkness.

nodes.label: GO:0047022
nodes.Name: 7-beta-hydroxysteroid dehydrogenase (NADP+) activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: NADP+ + a 7-beta-hydroxysteroid = NADPH + H+ + a 7-oxosteroid.

nodes.label: GO:0050144
nodes.Name: nucleoside deoxyribosyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 2-deoxy-D-ribosyl-base1 + base2 = 2-deoxy-D-ribosyl-base2 + base1.

nodes.label: GO:0015068
nodes.Name: glycine amidinotransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: L-arginine + glycine = L-ornithine + guanidinoacetate.

nodes.label: GO:0085040
nodes.Name: obsolete extra-invasive hyphal space
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. The space between the symbiont plasma membrane and the extra-invasive hyphal membrane.

nodes.label: GO:0016637
nodes.Name: obsolete oxidoreductase activity, acting on the CH-CH group of donors, other acceptors
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which a CH-CH group acts as a hydrogen or electron donor and reduces an acceptor other than quinone or related compound, a cytochrome, an iron-sulfur protein, NAD, NADP or oxygen.

nodes.label: GO:0019969
nodes.Name: interleukin-10 binding
nodes.Definition: Binding to interleukin-10.
