nodes.label: GO:0005786
nodes.Name: signal recognition particle, endoplasmic reticulum targeting
nodes.Definition: A ribonucleoprotein particle of 325 kDa composed of a 7S (300 nucleotide) RNA molecule and a complex of six different polypeptides. This binds both to the N-terminal signal peptide for proteins destined for the endoplasmic reticulum as they emerge from the large ribosomal subunit and also to the ribosome. This binding arrests further translation thereby preventing the proteins from being released into the cytosol. The SRP-ribosome complex then diffuses to the endoplasmic reticulum where it is bound to the signal recognition particle receptor, which allows resumption of protein synthesis and facilitates the passage of the growing polypeptide chain through the translocon. Through a process involving GTP hydrolysis, the SRP-SRP receptor complex dissociates and SRP returns to the cytosol. Of the six polypeptides of SRP the 54 kDa subunit (SRP54) is the central player. It contains an N-terminal GTPase domain and a C-terminal domain that binds directly to the signal peptide and the SRP RNA. Examples of this component are found in Mus musculus, Saccharomyces cerevisiae and Arabidopsis thaliana.

The incision serves as a starting point for subsequent excision repair by DNA polymerase I, which excises thymidine and reinserts cytidine.

nodes.label: GO:0071491
nodes.Name: cellular response to red light
nodes.Definition: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a red light stimulus. Red light is electromagnetic radiation of wavelength of 580-700nm. An example of this response is seen at the beginning of many plant species developmental stages. These include germination, and the point when cotyledon expansion is triggered. In certain species these processes take place in response to absorption of red light by the pigment molecule phytochrome, but the signal can be reversed by exposure to far red light. During the initial phase the phytochrome molecule is only present in the red light absorbing form, but on absorption of red light it changes to a far red light absorbing form, triggering progress through development. An immediate short period of exposure to far red light entirely returns the pigment to its initial state and prevents triggering of the developmental process. A thirty minute break between red and subsequent far red light exposure renders the red light effect irreversible, and development then occurs regardless of whether far red light exposure subsequently occurs.

nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: UDP-apiose + 7-O-beta-D-glucosyl-5,7,4'-trihydroxyflavone = UDP + 7-O-(beta-D-apiofuranosyl-1,2-beta-D-glucosyl)-5,7,4'-trihydroxyflavone.

nodes.label: GO:0032314
nodes.Name: regulation of GTPase activity
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the rate of GTP hydrolysis by a GTPase.

nodes.label: GO:0018548
nodes.Name: obsolete pentaerythritol trinitrate reductase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the reaction: pentaerythritol trinitrate + NADPH = NADP+ + nitrate + pentaerythritol dinitrate.

nodes.label: GO:0090434
nodes.Name: oleoyl-CoA ligase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + oleic acid + CoA = AMP + diphosphate + oleoyl-CoA.

nodes.label: GO:0004526
nodes.Name: ribonuclease P activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the endonucleolytic cleavage of RNA, removing 5' extra nucleotides from tRNA precursor.

nodes.label: GO:0046556
nodes.Name: alpha-L-arabinofuranosidase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of terminal non-reducing alpha-L-arabinofuranoside residues in alpha-L-arabinosides.

nodes.label: GO:0050372
nodes.Name: obsolete ubiquitin-calmodulin ligase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the reaction: n ATP + calmodulin + n ubiquitin = n AMP + n diphosphate + ubiquitin(n)-calmodulin.

nodes.label: GO:0043518
nodes.Name: negative regulation of DNA damage response, signal transduction by p53 class mediator
nodes.Definition: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the cascade of processes induced by the cell cycle regulator phosphoprotein p53, or an equivalent protein, in response to the detection of DNA damage.

nodes.label: GO:0046582
nodes.Name: GTPase activator activity
nodes.Definition: Binds to and increases the activity of a GTPase, an enzyme that catalyzes the hydrolysis of GTP.

nodes.label: GO:0008803
nodes.Name: bis(5'-nucleosyl)-tetraphosphatase (symmetrical) activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: P(1),P(4)-bis(5'-adenosyl) tetraphosphate + H2O = 2 ADP + 2 H+.

nodes.label: GO:0004817
nodes.Name: cysteine-tRNA ligase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + L-cysteine + tRNA(Cys) = AMP + diphosphate + L-cysteinyl-tRNA(Cys).

nodes.label: GO:0034342
nodes.Name: response to type III interferon
nodes.Definition: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a type III interferon stimulus. Interferon lambda is the only member of the type III interferon found so far.

nodes.label: GO:0008962
nodes.Name: phosphatidylglycerophosphatase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: phosphatidylglycerophosphate + H2O = phosphatidylglycerol + phosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0016642
nodes.Name: oxidoreductase activity, acting on the CH-NH2 group of donors, disulfide as acceptor
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which a CH-NH2 group acts as a hydrogen or electron donor and reduces a disulfide group.

nodes.label: GO:0031161
nodes.Name: phosphatidylinositol catabolic process
nodes.Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of phosphatidylinositol, any glycophospholipid with its sn-glycerol 3-phosphate residue is esterified to the 1-hydroxyl group of 1D-myo-inositol.

nodes.label: GO:0034386
nodes.Name: 4-aminobutyrate:2-oxoglutarate transaminase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 4-aminobutanoate + 2-oxoglutarate = succinate semialdehyde + L-glutamate.

nodes.label: GO:0005090
nodes.Name: guanyl-nucleotide exchange factor activity
nodes.Definition: Stimulates the exchange of GDP to GTP on a signaling GTPase, changing its conformation to its active form. Guanine nucleotide exchange factors (GEFs) act by stimulating the release of guanosine diphosphate (GDP) to allow binding of guanosine triphosphate (GTP), which is more abundant in the cell under normal cellular physiological conditions.

nodes.label: GO:0019785
nodes.Name: ISG15-specific peptidase activity
nodes.Definition: A thiol-dependent isopeptidase activity that cleaves ISG15 from a target protein to which it is conjugated.

nodes.label: GO:0018525
nodes.Name: 4-hydroxybenzoyl-CoA reductase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: benzoyl-CoA + oxidized ferredoxin + H2O = 4-hydroxybenzoyl-CoA + reduced ferredoxin.

nodes.label: GO:0034841
nodes.Name: obsolete mentha-1,3-dione-CoA ligase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the reaction: mentha-1,3-dione + CoASH = 3,7-dimethyl-5-oxo-octyl-CoA.

nodes.label: GO:0007518
nodes.Name: myoblast fate determination
nodes.Definition: The cell fate determination process in which a cell becomes capable of differentiating autonomously into a myoblast regardless of its environment; upon determination, the cell fate cannot be reversed. A myoblast is a mononucleate cell type that, by fusion with other myoblasts, gives rise to the myotubes that eventually develop into skeletal muscle fibers.

nodes.label: GO:0042292
nodes.Name: URM1 activating enzyme activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the activation of the small ubiquitin-related modifier URM1, through the formation of an ATP-dependent high-energy thiolester bond.

nodes.label: GO:0071502
nodes.Name: cellular response to temperature stimulus
nodes.Definition: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a temperature stimulus.

nodes.label: GO:0035183
nodes.Name: female germline ring canal inner rim
nodes.Definition: A proteinaceous actin-rich layer of the insect ovarian ring canal that forms subcortically to the outer rim. The electron dense inner rim accumulates after the final mitotic division of each germline syncytia, and contains actin, a phosphotyrosine protein, and a number of cytoskeletal proteins.

nodes.label: GO:0061203
nodes.Name: striated muscle paramyosin thick filament assembly
nodes.Definition: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of proteins to form the paramyosin-based thick filaments of myofibrils in striated muscle.

nodes.label: GO:0061204
nodes.Name: paramyosin filament assembly or disassembly
nodes.Definition: The formation or disassembly of a filament composed of paramyosin molecules.

nodes.label: GO:0000810
nodes.Name: diacylglycerol diphosphate phosphatase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: a 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol 3-diphosphate + H2O = a 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate + phosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0044638
nodes.Name: obsolete envenomation resulting in positive regulation of complement activation, classical pathway in another organism
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. A process that begins with venom being forced into an organism by the bite or sting of another organism, and ends with the positive regulation of complement activation via the classical pathway of the bitten/stung organism.

nodes.label: GO:0044522
nodes.Name: envenomation resulting in myocyte killing in another organism
nodes.Definition: A process that begins with venom being forced into an organism by the bite or sting of another organism, killing heart myocytes and ultimately resulting in muscle damage in the bitten organism.

nodes.label: GO:0032853
nodes.Name: positive regulation of GTPase activity
nodes.Definition: Any process that activates or increases the activity of a GTPase.

nodes.label: GO:0004524
nodes.Name: RNA-DNA hybrid ribonuclease activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the endonucleolytic cleavage of RNA in RNA-DNA hybrids to 5'-phosphomonoesters.

nodes.label: GO:0047280
nodes.Name: nicotinamide phosphoribosyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: diphosphate + nicotinamide mononucleotide = 5-phospho-alpha-D-ribose 1-diphosphate + H+ + nicotinamide.

nodes.label: GO:0032031
nodes.Name: myosin I head/neck binding
nodes.Definition: Binding to the head/neck region of a myosin I heavy chain.

nodes.label: GO:0030972
nodes.Name: obsolete cleavage of cytosolic proteins involved in execution phase of apoptosis
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. The proteolytic degradation of proteins in the cytosol that contributes to apoptosis.

nodes.label: GO:1901920
nodes.Name: obsolete peptidyl-tyrosine dephosphorylation involved in activation of protein kinase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Any peptidyl-tyrosine dephosphorylation that is involved in activation of protein kinase activity.

nodes.label: GO:0050084
nodes.Name: mannitol-1-phosphatase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: D-mannitol 1-phosphate + H2O = D-mannitol + 2 H+ + phosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0047110
nodes.Name: phenylglyoxylate dehydrogenase (acylating) activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: CoA + NAD+ + phenylglyoxylate = benzoyl-CoA + CO2 + NADH.

nodes.label: GO:0050139
nodes.Name: nicotinate-N-glucosyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: nicotinate + UDP-D-glucose = N-(beta-D-glucosyl)nicotinate + UDP.

nodes.label: GO:0031516
nodes.Name: far-red light photoreceptor activity
nodes.Definition: The function of absorbing and responding to electromagnetic radiation with a wavelength of approximately 730nm. The response may involve a change in conformation.

nodes.label: GO:0070009
nodes.Name: serine-type aminopeptidase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of a single N-terminal amino acid residue from a polypeptide chain by a catalytic mechanism that involves a catalytic triad consisting of a serine nucleophile that is activated by a proton relay involving an acidic residue (e.g. aspartate or glutamate) and a basic residue (usually histidine).

nodes.label: GO:0004763
nodes.Name: serine-pyruvate transaminase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: L-serine + pyruvate = 3-hydroxypyruvate + L-alanine.

nodes.label: GO:0035758
nodes.Name: chemokine (C-C motif) ligand 21 binding
nodes.Definition: Binding to chemokine (C-C motif) ligand 21.

nodes.label: GO:0075064
nodes.Name: obsolete negative regulation invasive hypha growth
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of symbiont invasive hypha formation within host. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

nodes.label: GO:0050971
nodes.Name: detection of mechanical stimulus involved in magnetoreception
nodes.Definition: The series of events involved in magnetoception in which a mechanical stimulus is received and converted into a molecular signal. The stimulus is in the form of torque on particles such as magnetite which respond to a magnetic field.

nodes.label: GO:0008911
nodes.Name: lactaldehyde dehydrogenase (NAD+) activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: (S)-lactaldehyde + NAD+ + H2O = (S)-lactate + NADH + H+.

nodes.label: GO:0051435
nodes.Name: BH4 domain binding
nodes.Definition: Binding to a BH4 protein domain, present in Bcl-2 family members. All anti-apoptotic proteins contain BH1 and BH2 domains; some also contain an additional N-terminal BH4 domain, which is almost never seen in pro-apoptotic proteins. Loss of the BH4 domain can diminish or abrogate anti-apoptotic function or even impart outright death-promoting properties to the protein.

nodes.label: GO:0016644
nodes.Name: obsolete oxidoreductase activity, acting on the CH-NH2 group of donors, other acceptors
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which a CH-NH2 group acts as a hydrogen or electron donor and reduces an acceptor other than a cytochrome, disulfide, an iron-sulfur protein, NAD, NADP or oxygen.

nodes.label: GO:0034302
nodes.Name: akinete formation
nodes.Definition: The process in which an akinete, a thick-walled (encysted) dormant cell derived from the enlargement of a vegetative cell, is formed. Akinetes typically have granular cytoplasm, are more resistant to environmental extremes than vegetative cells, and are characteristic of several groups of Cyanobacteria.

nodes.label: GO:0008715
nodes.Name: CDP-diacylglycerol diphosphatase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: CDP-diacylglycerol + H2O = a phosphatidate + CMP + 2 H+.

nodes.label: GO:0032856
nodes.Name: activation of GTPase activity
nodes.Definition: Any process that initiates the activity of an inactive GTPase through the replacement of GDP by GTP.

nodes.label: GO:0036509
nodes.Name: obsolete trimming of terminal mannose on B branch
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. The removal of an alpha-1,2-linked mannose from the B-chain of a glycoprotein oligosaccharide in the endoplasmic reticulum.

nodes.label: GO:0103102
nodes.Name: obsolete UDP-glucose:8-methylthiooctylhydroximate S-glucosyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the reaction: UDP-alpha-D-glucose + 8-methylthiooctylhydroximate = H+ + 7-methylthioheptyldesulfoglucosinolate + UDP.

nodes.label: GO:0052922
nodes.Name: hexaprenyl diphosphate synthase (geranylgeranyl-diphosphate specific) activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: geranylgeranyl diphosphate + 2 isopentenyl diphosphate = 2 diphosphate + all-trans-hexaprenyl diphosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0047578
nodes.Name: 4-hydroxyglutamate transaminase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 4-hydroxy-L-glutamate + 2-oxoglutarate = 4-hydroxy-2-oxoglutarate + L-glutamate.

nodes.label: GO:0008330
nodes.Name: protein tyrosine/threonine phosphatase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reactions: protein threonine phosphate + H2O = protein threonine + phosphate; and protein tyrosine phosphate + H2O = protein tyrosine + phosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0047102
nodes.Name: aminomuconate-semialdehyde dehydrogenase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: H2O + NAD+ + 2-aminomuconate semialdehyde = NADH + 2-amino-muconate.

nodes.label: GO:0001758
nodes.Name: retinal dehydrogenase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: retinal + NAD+ + H2O = retinoate + NADH. Acts on both 11-trans and 13-cis forms of retinal.

nodes.label: GO:0061696
nodes.Name: pituitary gonadotropin complex
nodes.Definition: A protein complex that is a protein hormone secreted by gonadotrope cells of the anterior pituitary of vertebrates. capable of regulating normal growth, sexual development, and reproductive function.

nodes.label: GO:0043245
nodes.Name: extraorganismal space
nodes.Definition: The environmental space outside of an organism; this may be a host organism in the case of parasitic and symbiotic organisms.

nodes.label: GO:0050211
nodes.Name: procollagen galactosyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: UDP-galactose + procollagen 5-hydroxy-L-lysine = UDP + procollagen 5-(D-galactosyloxy)-L-lysine.

nodes.label: GO:0036004
nodes.Name: GAF domain binding
nodes.Definition: Binding to a GAF protein domain.

nodes.label: GO:0004229
nodes.Name: obsolete gelatinase B activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the cleavage of gelatin types I and V and collagen types IV and V.

nodes.label: GO:0033855
nodes.Name: nicotianamine aminotransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 2-oxoglutarate + nicotianamine = 3''-deamino-3''-oxonicotianamine + L-glutamate.

nodes.label: GO:0050879
nodes.Name: multicellular organismal movement
nodes.Definition: Any physiological process involved in changing the position of a multicellular organism or an anatomical part of a multicellular organism.

nodes.label: GO:0008467
nodes.Name: [heparan sulfate]-glucosamine 3-sulfotransferase 1 activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 3'-phosphoadenylyl sulfate + [heparan sulfate]-glucosamine = adenosine 3',5'-bisphosphate + [heparan sulfate]-glucosamine 3-sulfate. The [heparan sulfate]-glucosamine 3-sulfate has a substrate consensus sequence of Glc(N2S>NAc)+/-6S GlcA GlcN2S*+/-6S GlcA>IdoA+/-2S Glc(N2S/NAc)+/-6S.

nodes.label: GO:0004232
nodes.Name: obsolete interstitial collagenase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the preferential cleavage of one bond in native collagen. Cleavage of the triple helix of collagen at about three-quarters of the length of the molecule from the N-terminus, at Gly775-Ile776 in the alpha-1(I) chain. Cleaves synthetic substrates and alpha-macroglobulins at bonds where P1' is a hydrophobic residue.

nodes.label: GO:0051694
nodes.Name: pointed-end actin filament capping
nodes.Definition: The binding of a protein or protein complex to the pointed (or minus) end of an actin filament, thus preventing the addition, exchange or removal of further actin subunits.

nodes.label: GO:0043716
nodes.Name: 2-hydroxy-3-keto-5-methylthiopentenyl-1-phosphate phosphatase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 2-hydroxy-3-keto-5-methylthiopentenyl-1-phosphate + H2O = 1,2-dihydroxy-5-(methylthio)pent-1-en-3-one + phosphate. 2-hydroxy-3-keto-5-methylthiopentenyl-1-phosphate is also known as HK-MTPenyl-P, and 1,2-dihydroxy-3-keto-5-methylthiopentene as DHK-MTPene.

nodes.label: GO:0016542
nodes.Name: male courtship behavior
nodes.Definition: The behavior of a male, for the purpose of attracting a sexual partner. An example of this process is found in Drosophila melanogaster.

nodes.label: GO:0042550
nodes.Name: photosystem I stabilization
nodes.Definition: The stabilization of the photosystem I protein complex, resulting from the phosphorylation of its structural protein subunits, in a cell actively involved in photosynthesis.

nodes.label: GO:0031278
nodes.Name: alpha-1,2-galactosyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the transfer of a galactose residue from a donor molecule, such as GDP-galactose or UDP-galactose, to an oligosaccharide, forming an alpha-1,2-linkage.

nodes.label: GO:0043876
nodes.Name: D-threonine aldolase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: D-threonine (or D-allo-threonine) = glycine + acetaldehyde.

nodes.label: GO:0036512
nodes.Name: obsolete trimming of second mannose on A branch
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. The removal of the second alpha-1,2-linked mannose from the A-chain of a glycoprotein oligosaccharide in the endoplasmic reticulum.

nodes.label: GO:0044198
nodes.Name: zf-TRAF domain binding
nodes.Definition: Binding to a TRAF-type zinc finger domain of a protein.

nodes.label: GO:0006121
nodes.Name: mitochondrial electron transport, succinate to ubiquinone
nodes.Definition: The transfer of electrons from succinate to ubiquinone that occurs during oxidative phosphorylation, mediated by the multisubunit enzyme known as complex II.

nodes.label: GO:0051862
nodes.Name: translocation of molecules into symbiont
nodes.Definition: The directed movement of molecule(s) produced by an organism to a location inside the symbiont organism. The symbiont is defined as the smaller of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

nodes.label: GO:0016982
nodes.Name: alpha-1,4-glucosidase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of terminal, non-reducing alpha-(1->4)-linked alpha-D-glucose residues with release of alpha-D-glucose.

nodes.label: GO:0010363
nodes.Name: regulation of plant-type hypersensitive response
nodes.Definition: Any endogenous process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the plant hypersensitive response.

nodes.label: GO:0047847
nodes.Name: deoxyuridine phosphorylase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 2'-deoxyuridine + phosphate = 2-deoxy-alpha-D-ribose 1-phosphate + uracil.

nodes.label: GO:0045352
nodes.Name: interleukin-1 type I receptor antagonist activity
nodes.Definition: Blocks the binding of interleukin-1 to interleukin-1 type I receptors.

nodes.label: GO:0016026
nodes.Name: obsolete proteasome endopeptidase core
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. (Was not defined before being made obsolete).

nodes.label: GO:2000844
nodes.Name: negative regulation of testosterone secretion
nodes.Definition: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of testosterone secretion.

nodes.label: GO:0050502
nodes.Name: cis-zeatin O-beta-D-glucosyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: cis-zeatin + UDP-D-glucose = O-beta-D-glucosyl-cis-zeatin + H+ + UDP.

nodes.label: GO:0007123
nodes.Name: obsolete bud scar accumulation
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. (Was not defined before being made obsolete).

nodes.label: GO:0017114
nodes.Name: obsolete wide-spectrum protease inhibitor activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Stops, prevents or reduces the activity of a protease by a wide-spectrum protease inhibitor. A wide-spectrum protease inhibitor is a protein having a peptide stretch which contains specific cleavage sites for different proteinases enabling inhibition of all four classes of proteinases by formation of a covalent bond between the inhibitor and the protease.

nodes.label: GO:0008847
nodes.Name: Enterobacter ribonuclease activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the endonucleolytic cleavage to 3'-phosphomononucleotides and 3'-phosphooligonucleotides with 2',3'-cyclic phosphate intermediates.

nodes.label: GO:0008707
nodes.Name: 4-phytase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: myo-inositol hexakisphosphate + H2O = 1-myo-inositol 1,2,3,4,5-pentakisphosphate + phosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0075266
nodes.Name: negative regulation of oogonium development
nodes.Definition: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of oogonium development, a process that leads to the formation of a female gametangium of oomycetes, containing one or more gametes.

nodes.label: GO:0018696
nodes.Name: pyruvate synthase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: pyruvate + CoA + 2 oxidized ferredoxin = acetyl-CoA + CO2 + 2 reduced ferredoxin + 2 H+.

nodes.label: GO:0050507
nodes.Name: indoxyl-UDPG glucosyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: indoxyl + UDP-D-glucose = H+ + indican + UDP.

nodes.label: GO:0033825
nodes.Name: oligosaccharide 4-alpha-D-glucosyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the transfer of the non-reducing terminal alpha-D-glucose residue from a 1,4-alpha-D-glucan to the 4-position of an alpha-D-glucan, thus bringing about the hydrolysis of oligosaccharides.

nodes.label: GO:0019034
nodes.Name: viral replication complex
nodes.Definition: Specific locations and structures in the virus infected cell involved in replicating the viral genome.

nodes.label: GO:0050192
nodes.Name: phosphoglycerate phosphatase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 2-phospho-D-glycerate + H2O = D-glycerate + phosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0070738
nodes.Name: tubulin-glycine ligase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the posttranslational transfer of one or more glycine residues to a specific glutamate residue on a target tubulin molecule; acts on alpha or beta tubulin.

nodes.label: GO:1990323
nodes.Name: collagen type XXIV trimer
nodes.Definition: A collagen homotrimer of alpha1(XXIV) chains; type XXIV collagen triple helices may participate in regulating type I collagen fibrillogenesis at specific anatomical locations during fetal development.

nodes.label: GO:0034842
nodes.Name: obsolete thiophene-2-carboxylate-CoA ligase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the reaction: thiophene-2-carboxylate + ATP + CoASH = thiophene-2-carboxyl-CoA + AMP + PPi.

nodes.label: GO:1990700
nodes.Name: nucleolar chromatin organization
nodes.Definition: Any process that results in the specification, formation or maintenance of the physical structure of nucleolar chromatin.

nodes.label: GO:0070797
nodes.Name: negative regulation of cleistothecium development
nodes.Definition: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of cleistothecium development, a process that leads to the formation of a cleistothecium. The cleistothecium is a closed sexual fruiting body that contains ascospores in linear asci, characteristic of some filamentous Ascomycete fungi such as members of the genera Aspergillus and Emericella.

nodes.label: GO:0052599
nodes.Name: obsolete methylputrescine oxidase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the reaction: N-methylputrescine + H2O + O2 = N-methylaminobutanal + NH3 + hydrogen peroxide + H+.

nodes.label: GO:0071968
nodes.Name: lipid A-core heptosyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: galactosyl-glucosyl3-heptosyl3-KDO2-lipid A-bisphosphate + ADP-L-glycero-beta-D-manno-heptose = lipid A-core + ADP + H+.

nodes.label: GO:2000691
nodes.Name: negative regulation of cardiac muscle cell myoblast differentiation
nodes.Definition: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of cardiac muscle cell myoblast differentiation.

nodes.label: GO:0070036
nodes.Name: obsolete GTP-dependent helicase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the reaction: GTP + H2O = GDP + phosphate, to drive the unwinding of a DNA or RNA helix.

nodes.label: GO:0034884
nodes.Name: obsolete gamma-N-formylaminovinylacetaldehyde dehydrogenase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the reaction: gamma-N-formylaminovinylacetaldehyde + H2O = gamma-N-formylaminovinylacetate + 2 H+ + 2 e-.

nodes.label: GO:0043745
nodes.Name: obsolete N2-acetyl-L-aminoadipate semialdehyde dehydrogenase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the reaction: N2-acetyl-L-aminoadipyl-delta-phosphate + NADPH + H+ = N2-acetyl-L-aminoadipate semialdehyde + NADP+ + orthophosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0044192
nodes.Name: host cell mitochondrial inner membrane
nodes.Definition: The inner, i.e. lumen-facing, lipid bilayer of the host cell mitochondrial envelope. It is highly folded to form cristae.

nodes.label: GO:0016976
nodes.Name: NEDD8 transferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the transfer of NEDD8 from one protein to another via the reaction X-NEDD8 + Y = Y-NEDD8 + X, where both X-NEDD8 and Y-NEDD8 are covalent linkages.

nodes.label: GO:0052658
nodes.Name: inositol-1,4,5-trisphosphate 5-phosphatase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 1D-myo-inositol 1,4,5-trisphosphate + H2O = 1D-myo-inositol 1,4-bisphosphate + phosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0044717
nodes.Name: 8-hydroxy-dADP phosphatase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 8-hydroxy-dADP + H2O = 8-hydroxy-dAMP + phosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0047571
nodes.Name: 3-oxosteroid 1-dehydrogenase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: a 3-oxosteroid + acceptor = a 3-oxo-D1-steroid + reduced acceptor.

nodes.label: GO:0004569
nodes.Name: glycoprotein endo-alpha-1,2-mannosidase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of the terminal alpha-glucosyl-(1,3)-mannosyl unit from Glc-Man(9)-(GlcNAc)(2) oligosaccharide component of the glycoprotein produced in the Golgi membrane.

nodes.label: GO:0047669
nodes.Name: amylosucrase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: sucrose + 1,4-alpha-D-glucosyl(n) = D-fructose + 1,4-alpha-D-glucosyl(n+1).

nodes.label: GO:0043261
nodes.Name: laminin-12 complex
nodes.Definition: A laminin complex composed of alpha2, beta1 and gamma3 polypeptide chains.

nodes.label: GO:0008841
nodes.Name: dihydrofolate synthase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + dihydropterate + L-glutamate = ADP + phosphate + dihydrofolate.

nodes.label: GO:0050352
nodes.Name: trimethylamine-oxide aldolase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: H+ + trimethylamine N-oxide = dimethylamine + formaldehyde.

nodes.label: GO:0055043
nodes.Name: 5-oxovalerate dehydrogenase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 5-oxovalerate + NADP+ + H2O = glutarate + NADPH + H+.

nodes.label: GO:0014865
nodes.Name: detection of activity
nodes.Definition: The series of events in which an activity stimulus is received by a cell and converted into a molecular signal.

nodes.label: GO:0052789
nodes.Name: obsolete mannan 1,3-beta-mannosidase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the hydrolysis of (1->3)-beta-D-mannosidic linkages in mannans, releasing mannose.

nodes.label: GO:0004285
nodes.Name: obsolete proprotein convertase 1 activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the release of protein hormones, neuropeptides and renin from their precursors, generally by cleavage of -Lys-Arg-Xaa at the Arg-Xaa bond.

nodes.label: GO:2000518
nodes.Name: negative regulation of T-helper 1 cell activation
nodes.Definition: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of T-helper 1 cell activation.

nodes.label: GO:0080079
nodes.Name: cellobiose glucosidase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: D-cellobiose + H2O = 2 D-glucose.

nodes.label: GO:0009769
nodes.Name: photosynthesis, light harvesting in photosystem II
nodes.Definition: After a photon of light is absorbed by one of the many chlorophyll molecules, in one of the light-harvesting complexes of an antenna on photosystem II, some of the absorbed energy is transferred to the pair of chlorophyll molecules in the reaction center.

nodes.label: GO:0050465
nodes.Name: nitroquinoline-N-oxide reductase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 4-(hydroxyamino)quinoline N-oxide + 2 NAD(P)+ + H2O = 4-nitroquinoline N-oxide + 2 NAD(P)H + 2 H+.

nodes.label: GO:0047268
nodes.Name: galactinol-raffinose galactosyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: raffinose + 1-alpha-D-galactosyl-myo-inositol = stachyose + myo-inositol.

nodes.label: GO:0009981
nodes.Name: 1,3-beta-D-glucan synthase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: UDP-glucose + [(1->3)-beta-D-glucosyl](n) = UDP + [(1->3)-beta-D-glucosyl](n+1).

nodes.label: GO:0010294
nodes.Name: abscisic acid glucosyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: (+)-abscisate + UDP-D-glucose = abscisic acid glucose ester + UDP.

nodes.label: GO:0047242
nodes.Name: hydroxyanthraquinone glucosyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: a hydroxyanthraquinone + UDP-D-glucose = a glucosyloxyanthraquinone + UDP.

nodes.label: GO:0072537
nodes.Name: fibroblast activation
nodes.Definition: A change in the morphology or behavior of a fibroblast resulting from exposure to an activating factor such as a cellular or soluble ligand.

nodes.label: GO:0007119
nodes.Name: budding cell isotropic bud growth
nodes.Definition: Unlocalized bud growth such that the entire surface of the bud expands evenly, in a cell that reproduces by budding.

nodes.label: GO:0070774
nodes.Name: obsolete phytoceramidase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the reaction: a phytoceramide + H2O = a fatty acid + phytosphingosine.

nodes.label: GO:0019964
nodes.Name: type II interferon binding
nodes.Definition: Binding to type II interferon, also known as interferon-gamma.

nodes.label: GO:0060055
nodes.Name: angiogenesis involved in wound healing
nodes.Definition: Blood vessel formation when new vessels emerge from the proliferation of pre-existing blood vessels and contribute to the series of events that restore integrity to a damaged tissue, following an injury.

nodes.label: GO:0019982
nodes.Name: interleukin-7 binding
nodes.Definition: Binding to interleukin-7.

nodes.label: GO:0051127
nodes.Name: positive regulation of actin nucleation
nodes.Definition: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of actin nucleation, the initial step in the formation of an actin filament in which actin monomers combine to form a new filament.

nodes.label: GO:0008709
nodes.Name: cholate 7-alpha-dehydrogenase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: cholate + NAD+ = 3alpha,12alpha-dihydroxy-7-oxo-5beta-cholanate + H+ + NADH.

nodes.label: GO:0035986
nodes.Name: obsolete senescence-associated heterochromatin focus assembly
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. The assembly of chromatin into senescence-associated heterochromatin foci (SAHF), transcriptionally-silent heterochromatin structures present in senescent cells, containing the condensed chromatin of one chromosome, and enriched for histone modifications. Formation of these chromatin structures is thought to repress expression of proliferation-promoting genes.

nodes.label: GO:0004592
nodes.Name: pantoate-beta-alanine ligase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + (R)-pantoate + beta-alanine = AMP + diphosphate + (R)-pantothenate.

nodes.label: GO:0072517
nodes.Name: host cell viral assembly compartment
nodes.Definition: A membrane-bounded compartment that forms in the cytoplasm of the host cell, in which virus assembly takes place.

nodes.label: GO:0008921
nodes.Name: lipopolysaccharide-1,6-galactosyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: UDP-galactose + lipopolysaccharide = UDP + 1,6 alpha-D-galactosyl-lipopolysaccharide.

nodes.label: GO:0050303
nodes.Name: lysine 6-dehydrogenase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: H2O + NAD+ + L-lysine = NH3 + NADH + allysine.

nodes.label: GO:0009824
nodes.Name: AMP dimethylallyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: AMP + dimethylallyl diphosphate = N(6)-(dimethylallyl)adenosine 5'-phosphate + diphosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0000163
nodes.Name: protein serine/threonine phosphatase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: protein serine phosphate + H2O = protein serine + phosphate, and protein threonine phosphate + H2O = protein threonine + phosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0003818
nodes.Name: obsolete complement factor I activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the inactivation of complement subcomponents C3b, iC3b and C4b by proteolytic cleavage.

nodes.label: GO:0008765
nodes.Name: UDP-N-acetylmuramoylalanyl-D-glutamate-2,6-diaminopimelate ligase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: meso-2,6-diaminopimelate + ATP + UDP-N-acetylmuramoyl-L-alanyl-D-glutamate = ADP + 2 H+ + phosphate + UDP-N-acetylmuramoyl-L-alanyl-D-gamma-glutamyl-meso-2,6-diaminoheptanedioate.

nodes.label: GO:0018855
nodes.Name: 2-oxo-delta3-4,5,5-trimethylcyclopentenylacetyl-CoA synthetase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 2-oxo-delta3-4,5,5-trimethylcyclopentenylacetate + ATP + CoA = AMP + diphosphate + 2-oxo-delta3-4,5,5-trimethylcyclopentenylacetyl-CoA.

nodes.label: GO:0034200
nodes.Name: D-glycero-beta-D-manno-heptose 1,7-bisphosphate 7-phosphatase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: D-glycero-beta-D-manno-heptose 1,7-bisphosphate + H2O = D-glycero-beta-D-manno-heptose 1-phosphate + phosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0050692
nodes.Name: DNA binding domain binding
nodes.Definition: Binding to a protein's DNA binding domain (DBD).

nodes.label: GO:0043824
nodes.Name: succinylglutamate-semialdehyde dehydrogenase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: N-succinyl-L-glutamate 5-semialdehyde + H2O + NAD+ = N-succinyl-L-glutamate + 2 H+ + NADH.

nodes.label: GO:0033837
nodes.Name: anthocyanin 3'-O-beta-glucosyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: UDP-glucose + an anthocyanin = UDP + an anthocyanin 3'-O-beta-D-glucoside.

nodes.label: GO:0003925
nodes.Name: G protein activity
nodes.Definition: A molecular function regulator that cycles between active GTP-bound and inactive GDP-bound states. In its active state, binds to a variety of effector proteins to regulate cellular processes. Intrinsic GTPase activity returns the G protein to its GDP-bound state. The return to the GDP-bound state can be accelerated by the action of a GTPase-activating protein (GAP).

nodes.label: GO:0016506
nodes.Name: obsolete apoptosis activator activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. The function held by products which directly activate any step in the process of apoptosis.

nodes.label: GO:0034029
nodes.Name: 2-oxoglutarate carboxylase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 2-oxoglutarate + ATP + bicarbonate = ADP + 2 H+ + oxalosuccinate + phosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0061677
nodes.Name: 2-dehydro-3-deoxy-D-gluconate aldolase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 2-dehydro-3-deoxy-D-gluconate = pyruvate + D-glyceraldehyde.

nodes.label: GO:0007521
nodes.Name: muscle cell fate determination
nodes.Definition: The cell fate determination process in which a cell becomes capable of differentiating autonomously into a muscle cell regardless of its environment; upon determination, the cell fate cannot be reversed.

nodes.label: GO:0042283
nodes.Name: dolichyl pyrophosphate Glc1Man9GlcNAc2 alpha-1,3-glucosyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the addition of the second glucose residue to the lipid-linked oligosaccharide precursor for N-linked glycosylation; the transfer of glucose from dolichyl phosphate glucose (Dol-P-Glc) on to the lipid-linked oligosaccharide Glc(1)Man(9)GlcNAc(2)-PP-Dol.

nodes.label: GO:0033149
nodes.Name: FFAT motif binding
nodes.Definition: Binding to a FFAT motif, a short motif containing diphenylalanine in an acidic tract that targets proteins to the cytosolic surface of the ER and to the nuclear membrane by binding directly to members of the VAP (VAMP-associated protein) protein family.

nodes.label: GO:0098750
nodes.Name: FYXD domain binding
nodes.Definition: Binding to a FXYD domain.

nodes.label: GO:0003961
nodes.Name: O-acetylhomoserine aminocarboxypropyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: O-acetyl-L-homoserine + methanethiol = L-methionine + acetate. Also reacts with other thiols and H2S, producing homocysteine or thioethers.

nodes.label: GO:0016665
nodes.Name: obsolete oxidoreductase activity, acting on other nitrogenous compounds as donors, other acceptors
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction in which a nitrogenous group, excluding NH and NH2 groups, acts as a hydrogen or electron donor and reduces an acceptor other than a cytochrome, an iron-sulfur protein, oxygen, NAD or NADP.

nodes.label: GO:0047221
nodes.Name: sn-glycerol-3-phosphate 2-alpha-galactosyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: sn-glycerol 3-phosphate + UDP-D-galactose = 2-(alpha-D-galactosyl)-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate + H+ + UDP.

nodes.label: GO:0075338
nodes.Name: obsolete modulation of growth or development of symbiont during interaction with host
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the increase in size or mass of an organism, or the progression of an organism from an initial condition to a later condition, occurring in, on or near the exterior of its host organism.

nodes.label: GO:0004202
nodes.Name: obsolete caspase-2 activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. (Was not defined before being made obsolete).

nodes.label: GO:0043343
nodes.Name: establishment of neuroblast polarity
nodes.Definition: The specification and formation of the apicobasal polarity of a neuroblast cell, a progenitor of the central nervous system.

nodes.label: GO:0047622
nodes.Name: adenosine nucleosidase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: adenosine + H2O = D-ribose + adenine.

nodes.label: GO:0072577
nodes.Name: endothelial cell apoptotic process
nodes.Definition: Any apoptotic process in an endothelial cell. An endothelial cell comprises the outermost layer or lining of anatomical structures and can be squamous or cuboidal.

nodes.label: GO:0030911
nodes.Name: TPR domain binding
nodes.Definition: Binding to a tetratricopeptide repeat (TPR) domain of a protein, the consensus sequence of which is defined by a pattern of small and large hydrophobic amino acids and a structure composed of helices.

nodes.label: GO:0016889
nodes.Name: DNA endonuclease activity, producing 3'-phosphomonoesters
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of ester linkages within deoxyribonucleic acids by creating internal breaks to yield 3'-phosphomonoesters.

nodes.label: GO:0004401
nodes.Name: histidinol-phosphatase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: L-histidinol phosphate + H2O = L-histidinol + phosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0031079
nodes.Name: obsolete picornain 3C activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the selective cleavage of GlnGly bond in the poliovirus polyprotein. In other picornavirus reactions Glu may be substituted for Gln, and Ser or Thr for Gly.

nodes.label: GO:0016432
nodes.Name: tRNA-uridine aminocarboxypropyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: S-adenosyl-L-methionine + tRNA uridine = 5'-methylthioadenosine + tRNA 3-(3-amino-3-carboxypropyl)-uridine.

nodes.label: GO:0050094
nodes.Name: methionine-glyoxylate transaminase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: L-methionine + glyoxylate = 4-methylthio-2-oxobutanoate + glycine.

nodes.label: GO:0075227
nodes.Name: regulation of encysted zoospore germination
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of an encysted zoospore germination.

nodes.label: GO:0033948
nodes.Name: fructan beta-(2,1)-fructosidase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of terminal, non-reducing (2->1) linked beta-D-fructofuranose residues in fructans.

nodes.label: GO:0042290
nodes.Name: obsolete URM1 hydrolase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. (Was not defined before being made obsolete).

nodes.label: GO:0055027
nodes.Name: chlamydospore formation
nodes.Definition: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the chlamydospore over time, from its formation to the mature structure. A chlamydospores is a mitotic (asexual) one-celled spore, produced primarily for survival, not dispersal, originating endogenously and singly within part of a pre-existing cell and possessing an inner secondary and often thickened cell wall. An example of this is found in Candida albicans.

nodes.label: GO:0047747
nodes.Name: cholate-CoA ligase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reactions: (1) ATP + cholate + CoA = AMP + diphosphate + choloyl-CoA and (2) ATP + (25R)-3alpha,7alpha,12alpha-trihydroxy-5beta-cholestan-26-oate + CoA = AMP + diphosphate + (25R)-3alpha,7alpha,12alpha-trihydroxy-5beta-cholestanoyl-CoA. This reaction is the first step in the conjugation of bile acids with amino acids, converting bile acids into their acyl-CoA thioesters. Chenodeoxycholate, deoxycholate, lithocholate and trihydroxycoprostanoate can also act as substrates.

nodes.label: GO:0043135
nodes.Name: 5-phosphoribosyl 1-pyrophosphate pyrophosphatase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 5-phospho-alpha-D-ribose 1-diphosphate + H2O = ribose 1,5 bisphosphate + phosphate + H+.

nodes.label: GO:0034042
nodes.Name: 5-formyluracil DNA N-glycosylase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the removal of 5-formyluracil bases by cleaving the N-C1' glycosidic bond between the oxidized pyrimidine and the deoxyribose sugar.

nodes.label: GO:0101007
nodes.Name: obsolete negative regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter in response to salt stress
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Any process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter as a result of a stimulus indicating the organism is under salt stress. The stress is usually an increase or decrease in the concentration of salt (particularly but not exclusively sodium and chloride ions) in the environment.

nodes.label: GO:0101008
nodes.Name: obsolete negative regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter in response to increased salt
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Any process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of transcription from an RNA polymerase II promoter as a result of detection of, or exposure to, an increase in the concentration of salt (particularly but not exclusively sodium and chloride ions) in the environment.

nodes.label: GO:0047013
nodes.Name: cholate 12-alpha dehydrogenase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: cholate + NADP+ = 3alpha,7alpha-dihydroxy-12-oxo-5beta-cholanate + H+ + NADPH.

nodes.label: GO:0044685
nodes.Name: obsolete tetrahydromethanopterin-dependent serine hydroxymethyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the reaction: tetrahydromethanopterin + L-serine = 5,10-methylenetetrahydromethanopterin + glycine + H2O.

nodes.label: GO:0050955
nodes.Name: thermoception
nodes.Definition: The series of events required for an organism to receive a temperature stimulus, convert it to a molecular signal, and recognize and characterize the signal. Thermoception in larger animals is mainly done in the skin; mammals have at least two types of sensor, for detecting heat (temperatures above body temperature) and cold (temperatures below body temperature).

nodes.label: GO:0008914
nodes.Name: leucyl-tRNA--protein transferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: L-leucyl-tRNA(Leu) + N-terminal L-arginyl-[protein] = H+ + N-terminal L-leucyl-L-arginyl-[protein] + tRNA(Leu). Can also transfer the leucyl residue on an N-terminal L-lysyl residue.

nodes.label: GO:0060361
nodes.Name: flight
nodes.Definition: Self-propelled movement of an organism from one location to another through the air, usually by means of active wing movement.

nodes.label: GO:0004354
nodes.Name: glutamate dehydrogenase (NADP+) activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: L-glutamate + H2O + NADP+ = 2-oxoglutarate + NH3 + NADPH + H+.

nodes.label: GO:0030019
nodes.Name: obsolete tryptase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the preferential cleavage of Arg-Xaa, Lys-Xaa, but with more restricted specificity than trypsin.

nodes.label: GO:0044095
nodes.Name: host cell nucleoplasm
nodes.Definition: That part of a host cell's nuclear content other than the chromosomes or the nucleolus. The host is the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

nodes.label: GO:0004030
nodes.Name: aldehyde dehydrogenase [NAD(P)+] activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: an aldehyde + NAD(P)+ + H2O = an acid + NAD(P)H + H+.

nodes.label: GO:0050269
nodes.Name: coniferyl-aldehyde dehydrogenase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: coniferyl aldehyde + H2O + NAD(P)+ = ferulate + NAD(P)H + H+.

nodes.label: GO:0008756
nodes.Name: o-succinylbenzoate-CoA ligase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 2-succinylbenzoate + ATP + CoA = 2-succinylbenzoyl-CoA + AMP + diphosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0003294
nodes.Name: atrial ventricular junction remodeling
nodes.Definition: The reorganization or renovation of heart tissue that contributes to the maturation of the connection between an atrium and a ventricle.

nodes.label: GO:0004158
nodes.Name: obsolete dihydroorotate oxidase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the reaction: (S)-dihydroorotate + O2 = H2O2 + orotate.

nodes.label: GO:0042722
nodes.Name: alpha-beta T cell activation by superantigen
nodes.Definition: The change in morphology and behavior of alpha-beta T cells resulting from exposure to a superantigen, a microbial antigen with an extremely potent activating effect on T cells that bear a specific variable region.

nodes.label: GO:0050441
nodes.Name: 3-ethylmalate synthase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: butanoyl-CoA + glyoxylate + H2O = 3-ethylmalate + CoA + H+.

nodes.label: GO:0009815
nodes.Name: 1-aminocyclopropane-1-carboxylate oxidase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 1-aminocyclopropane-1-carboxylate + L-ascorbate + O2 = CO2 + dehydroascorbate + ethylene + 2 H2O + hydrogen cyanide. Ethene is also known as ethylene.

nodes.label: GO:0008934
nodes.Name: inositol monophosphate 1-phosphatase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: myo-inositol 1-phosphate + H2O = myo-inositol + phosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0085001
nodes.Name: formation of stylet for nutrient acquisition
nodes.Definition: The assembly of a stylet, a hollow protrusible spear-like symbiont structure projected into the host cell for the purpose of obtaining nutrients. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

nodes.label: GO:0051134
nodes.Name: negative regulation of NK T cell activation
nodes.Definition: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of natural killer T cell activation.

nodes.label: GO:0097167
nodes.Name: circadian regulation of translation
nodes.Definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of mRNA translation with a regularity of approximately 24 hours.

nodes.label: GO:0071967
nodes.Name: lipopolysaccharide core heptosyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: glucosyl-heptosyl2-KDO2-lipid A-phosphate + ADP-L-glycero-beta-D-manno-heptose = glucosyl-heptosyl3-KDO2-lipid A-phosphate + ADP + H+.

nodes.label: GO:0097385
nodes.Name: programmed necrotic cell death in response to starvation
nodes.Definition: A programmed necrotic cell death occurring as a result of a starvation stimulus (deprivation of nourishment).

nodes.label: GO:2000536
nodes.Name: negative regulation of entry of bacterium into host cell
nodes.Definition: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of entry of bacterium into host cell.

nodes.label: GO:0043802
nodes.Name: hydrogenobyrinic acid a,c-diamide synthase (glutamine-hydrolysing) activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 2 L-glutamine + 2 ATP + 2 H2O + hydrogenobyrinate = 2 L-glutamate + 2 ADP + 4 H+ + hydrogenobyrinate a,c-diamide + 2 phosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0051669
nodes.Name: fructan beta-fructosidase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of terminal, non-reducing 2,1- and 2,6-linked beta-D-fructofuranose residues in fructans.

nodes.label: GO:1990808
nodes.Name: F-bar domain binding
nodes.Definition: Binding to an F-BAR domain of a protein, a domain of about 60 residues that occurs in a wide range of cytoskeletal proteins.

nodes.label: GO:0009770
nodes.Name: obsolete primary charge separation in photosystem I
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Energized reaction-center P700 chlorophylls on photosystem I donate an electron to a loosely bound Quinone acceptor molecule X, on the stromal surface of the thylakoid membrane. The result is charge separation; a negative charge on the stromal side of the thylakoid membrane and a positive charge on the luminal side.

nodes.label: GO:0018552
nodes.Name: coenzyme-B sulfoethylthiotransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: coenzyme B + methyl-coenzyme M = coenzyme M-coenzyme B heterodisulfide + methane. Methyl-CoM is also known as 2-(methylthio)ethanesulfonate, coenzyme B as N-(7-mercaptoheptanoyl)threonine 3-O-phosphate, and coenzyme M-coenzyme B heterodisulfide as CoM-S-S-CoB.

nodes.label: GO:0050524
nodes.Name: coenzyme-B sulfoethylthiotransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: coenzyme B + methyl-coenzyme M = coenzyme M-coenzyme B heterodisulfide + methane. Methyl-CoM is also known as 2-(methylthio)ethanesulfonate, coenzyme B as N-(7-mercaptoheptanoyl)threonine 3-O-phosphate, and coenzyme M-coenzyme B heterodisulfide as CoM-S-S-CoB.

nodes.label: GO:0047222
nodes.Name: mannotetraose 2-alpha-N-acetylglucosaminyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 1,3-alpha-D-mannosyl-1,2-alpha-D-mannosyl-1,2-alpha-D-mannosyl-D-mannose + UDP-N-acetyl-D-glucosamine = 1,3-alpha-D-mannosyl-1,2-(N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosaminyl-alpha-D-mannosyl)-1,2-alpha-D-mannosyl-D-mannose + UDP.

nodes.label: GO:0097340
nodes.Name: inhibition of cysteine-type endopeptidase activity
nodes.Definition: Any process that prevents the activation of an inactive cysteine-type endopeptidase.

nodes.label: GO:0097341
nodes.Name: zymogen inhibition
nodes.Definition: Any process that prevents the proteolytic processing of an inactive enzyme to an active form.

nodes.label: GO:0052618
nodes.Name: coenzyme F420-0:L-glutamate ligase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: GTP + L-glutamate + factor F420-0 = GDP + H+ + factor gamma-F420-1 + phosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0008665
nodes.Name: tRNA 2'-phosphotransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 2'-phospho-[ligated tRNA] + NAD+ = mature tRNA + ADP ribose 1'',2''-phosphate + nicotinamide + H2O. This reaction is the transfer of the splice junction 2-phosphate from ligated tRNA to NAD+ to produce ADP-ribose 1'-2' cyclic phosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0047121
nodes.Name: isoquinoline 1-oxidoreductase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: A + H2O + isoquinoline = AH(2) + isoquinolin-1(2H)-one.

nodes.label: GO:0044631
nodes.Name: obsolete positive regulation of complement activation, lectin pathway in another organism
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of complement activation by the lectin pathway, in a different organism.

nodes.label: GO:0034564
nodes.Name: obsolete 4,4'-dihydroxy-alpha-methylstilbene dioxygenase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the reaction: 4,4'-dihydroxy-alpha-methylstilbene + O2 = 4-hydroxybenzaldehyde + 4-hydroxyacetophenone + 2 H+ + 2 e-.

nodes.label: GO:0033126
nodes.Name: obsolete positive regulation of GTP catabolic process
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the breakdown of GTP, guanosine triphosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0046509
nodes.Name: 1,2-diacylglycerol 3-beta-galactosyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol + UDP-D-galactose = 1,2-diacyl-3-beta-D-galactosyl-sn-glycerol + H+ + UDP.

nodes.label: GO:0047239
nodes.Name: hydroxymandelonitrile glucosyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 4-hydroxymandelonitrile + UDP-D-glucose = H+ + taxiphyllin + UDP.

nodes.label: GO:0008994
nodes.Name: rhamnulose-1-phosphate aldolase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: L-rhamnulose 1-phosphate = glycerone phosphate + (S)-lactaldehyde.

nodes.label: GO:0018121
nodes.Name: obsolete NAD(P)-asparagine ADP-ribosyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the reaction: NAD(P)+ + L-asparagine = nicotinamide + N2-(ADP-D-ribosyl)-L-asparagine.

nodes.label: GO:0098601
nodes.Name: selenomethionine adenosyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + L-Selenomethionine + H2O => Orthophosphate + Diphosphate + Se-Adenosylselenomethionine.

nodes.label: GO:0047861
nodes.Name: diiodotyrosine transaminase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 2-oxoglutarate + 3,5-diiodo-L-tyrosine = 3-(3,5-diiodo-4-hydroxyphenyl)pyruvate + L-glutamate.

nodes.label: GO:2000210
nodes.Name: positive regulation of anoikis
nodes.Definition: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of anoikis.

nodes.label: GO:0004044
nodes.Name: amidophosphoribosyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 5-phospho-beta-D-ribosylamine + L-glutamate + diphosphate = 5-phospho-alpha-D-ribose 1-diphosphate + L-glutamine + H2O.

nodes.label: GO:0033829
nodes.Name: O-fucosylpeptide 3-beta-N-acetylglucosaminyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the transfer of a beta-D-GlcNAc residue from UDP-D-GlcNAc to the fucose residue of a fucosylated protein acceptor.

nodes.label: GO:0019137
nodes.Name: thioglucosidase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: a thioglucoside + H2O = a thiol + a sugar.

nodes.label: GO:0003852
nodes.Name: 2-isopropylmalate synthase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 3-methyl-2-oxobutanoate + acetyl-CoA + H2O = (2S)-2-isopropylmalate + CoA + H+.

nodes.label: GO:0044543
nodes.Name: obsolete envenomation resulting in zymogen activation in another organism
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. The process which begins with venom being forced into an organism by the bite or sting of another organism, and ends with the proteolytic processing of an inactive enzyme to an active form.

nodes.label: GO:0070128
nodes.Name: methionyl-tRNA formyltransferase activity

nodes.label: GO:0070702

nodes.label: GO:1990478

nodes.label: GO:0075341

nodes.label: GO:0004637

nodes.label: GO:0001509

nodes.label: GO:0003792

nodes.label: GO:0044486

nodes.label: GO:0042731

nodes.label: GO:0052792

nodes.label: GO:0004215

nodes.label: GO:0071552

nodes.label: GO:0016544

nodes.label: GO:0090223

nodes.label: GO:0008821

nodes.label: GO:0003907

Release of the enzyme and free base by a beta-elimination or a beta, gamma-elimination mechanism results in the cleavage of the DNA backbone 3' of the apurinic (AP) site.

nodes.label: GO:0033361

nodes.Definition: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of lysine, via the intermediate diaminopimelate; in this pathway tetrahydrodipicolinate is converted to meso-diaminopimelate in a single enzymatic step.

nodes.Name: activation of microtubule nucleation
nodes.Definition: Any process that starts the inactive process of microtubule nucleation. Microtubule nucleation is the 'de novo' formation of a microtubule, in which tubulin heterodimers form metastable oligomeric aggregates, some of which go on to support formation of a complete microtubule. Microtubule nucleation usually occurs from a specific site within a cell.

nodes.label: GO:2000721

nodes.label: GO:0047477

This reaction is the first step in the conjugation of bile acids with amino acids, converting bile acids into their acyl-CoA thioesters. Chenodeoxycholate, deoxycholate, lithocholate and trihydroxycoprostanoate can also act as substrates.

nodes.label: GO:0004192

nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the hydrolysis of peptide bonds. Specificity similar to, but narrower than, that of pepsin A. Does not cleave the Gln4-His5 bond in the B chain of insulin.

nodes.label: GO:0075340

nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the increase in size or mass of an organism, or the progression of an organism from an initial condition to a later condition, occurring in, on or near the exterior of its host organism.

nodes.label: GO:0044398
nodes.Name: envenomation resulting in induction of edema in another organism
nodes.Definition: A process that begins with venom being forced into an organism by the bite or sting of another organism, and ends with the swelling of soft tissues of the bitten organism as a result of excess water accumulation.

nodes.label: GO:0030487

nodes.label: GO:0047695

nodes.label: GO:0048063

nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosaminyl-(1,4)-beta-D-glucuronosyl-proteoglycan + UDP-alpha-D-glucuronate = beta-D-glucuronosyl-(1,4)-N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosaminyl-(1,4)-beta-D-glucuronosyl-proteoglycan + UDP.

nodes.label: GO:1902445

nodes.Definition: Any regulation of mitochondrial membrane permeability that is involved in programmed necrotic cell death.

nodes.label: GO:0033943

nodes.label: GO:0030402

nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Was not defined before being made obsolete.

nodes.label: GO:0016039

nodes.label: GO:0043044

nodes.Definition: A dynamic process of chromatin reorganization resulting in changes to chromatin structure. These changes allow DNA metabolic processes such as transcriptional regulation, DNA recombination, DNA repair, and DNA replication.

nodes.label: GO:0044164
nodes.Name: host cell cytosol
nodes.Definition: The part of the host cell cytoplasm that does not contain organelles but which does contain other particulate matter, such as protein complexes.

nodes.label: GO:0005020
nodes.Name: stem cell factor receptor activity
nodes.Definition: Combining with stem cell factor (SCF) receptor ligand and transmitting the signal from one side of the membrane to the other to initiate a change in cell activity by catalysis of the reaction: ATP + a protein-L-tyrosine = ADP + a protein-L-tyrosine phosphate. Stem cell factor is a cytokine that stimulates mast cell growth and differentiation.

nodes.label: GO:0014883
nodes.Name: transition between fast and slow fiber
nodes.Definition: The process of conversion of fast-contracting muscle fibers to a slower character. This may involve slowing of contractile rate, slow myosin gene induction, increase in oxidative metabolic properties, altered electrophysiology and altered innervation. This process also regulates skeletal muscle adapatation.

nodes.label: GO:0009772
nodes.Name: photosynthetic electron transport in photosystem II
nodes.Definition: A photosynthetic electron transport chain in which electrons move from the primary electron acceptor (Quinone, Q) through a chain of electron transport molecules in the thylakoid membrane until they reach the ultimate electron acceptor of Photosystem II, which is plastocyanin (PC). The electron is then passed to the P700 chlorophyll a molecules of the reaction centre of photosystem I.

nodes.label: GO:0032317

nodes.Definition: Binding to a NACHT (NAIP, CIITA, HET-E and TP1) domain. The NACHT domain consists of seven distinct conserved motifs, including an ATP/GTPase specific P-loop, a Mg2+-binding site and five more specific motifs.

nodes.label: GO:0004451

nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: isocitrate = glyoxylate + succinate.

nodes.label: GO:0016511

nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. (Was not defined before being made obsolete).

nodes.label: GO:0004281

nodes.label: GO:0000043
nodes.Name: 4-hydroxybenzoate polyprenyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 4-hydroxybenzoate + an all-trans-polyprenyl diphosphate = a 4-hydroxy-3-all-trans-polyprenylbenzoate + diphosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0050244
nodes.Name: pyruvate oxidase (CoA-acetylating) activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: CoA + H+ + O2 + pyruvate = acetyl-CoA + CO2 + H2O2.

nodes.label: GO:0001769
nodes.Name: establishment of B cell polarity
nodes.Definition: The directed orientation of B cell signaling molecules and associated membrane rafts towards a chemokine gradient of a contact point with an antigen displaying cell.

nodes.label: GO:0003947

nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: UDP-N-acetyl-D-galactosamine + (N-acetylneuraminyl)-D-galactosyl-D-glucosylceramide = UDP + N-acetyl-D-galactosaminyl-(N-acetylneuraminyl)-D-galactosyl-D-glucosylceramide.

nodes.label: GO:0044158
nodes.Name: host cell wall
nodes.Definition: The rigid or semi-rigid envelope lying outside the host cell membrane of plant, fungal, and most prokaryotic cells, maintaining their shape and protecting them from osmotic lysis. In plants it is made of cellulose and, often, lignin; in fungi it is composed largely of polysaccharides; in bacteria it is composed of peptidoglycan.

nodes.label: GO:0018797

nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. Catalysis of the reaction: acetophenone + CO2 = H+ + benzoyl acetate.

nodes.label: GO:0051060

nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of (1,6)-alpha-D-glucosidic linkages in pullulan (a linear polymer of alpha-(1,6)-linked maltotriose units) and in amylopectin and glycogen, and the a- and b-limit dextrins of amylopectin and glycogen.

nodes.label: GO:0050340

nodes.label: GO:1901200

nodes.Definition: Any negative regulation of calcium ion transport into cytosol that is involved in cellular response to salt stress.

nodes.label: GO:0047403

nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: H2O + beta-D-Gal-(1,3)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1,3)-beta-D-Gal-(1,4)-D-Glc = beta-D-Gal-(1,4)-D-Glc + beta-D-Gal-(1,3)-D-GlcNAc.

nodes.label: GO:0001966
nodes.Name: thigmotaxis
nodes.Definition: The directed movement of an animal in response to touch.

nodes.label: GO:0042169
nodes.Name: SH2 domain binding
nodes.Definition: Binding to a SH2 domain (Src homology 2) of a protein, a protein domain of about 100 amino-acid residues and belonging to the alpha + beta domain class.

nodes.label: GO:0071536
nodes.Name: obsolete RING-like zinc finger domain-mediated complex assembly
nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. A process of protein complex assembly in which the arrangement and bonding together of the set of components that form the protein complex is mediated by a RING-like zinc finger domain interaction.

nodes.label: GO:0002295
nodes.Name: T-helper cell lineage commitment
nodes.Definition: The process in which a CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell becomes committed to becoming a T-helper cell, a CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell specialized to promote various immunological processes.

nodes.label: GO:0002297
nodes.Name: T-helper 2 cell lineage commitment
nodes.Definition: The process in which a CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell becomes committed to becoming a T-helper 2 cell, a CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell specialized to promote immunological processes often associated with resistance to extracellular organisms such as helminths, enhanced production of particular antibody isotypes, and pathological conditions such as allergy.

nodes.label: GO:0052639

nodes.label: GO:0044045

nodes.Definition: OBSOLETE. An interaction with the host organism mediated by a substance in the symbiont cell outer membrane - a lipid bilayer that forms the outermost layer of the symbiont cell envelope. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

nodes.label: GO:0003827

nodes.label: GO:0033885

nodes.label: GO:0008578

nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the removal of damaged bases by cleaving the N-C1' glycosidic bond between the target damaged DNA base and the deoxyribose sugar. The reaction releases a free base and leaves an apurinic/apyrimidinic (AP) site.

nodes.label: GO:0070251

nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: ATP + pristanate + CoA = AMP + diphosphate + pristanoyl-CoA.

nodes.label: GO:0033901
nodes.Name: ribonuclease V activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of poly(A), forming oligoribonucleotides and ultimately 3'-AMP.

nodes.label: GO:0050395
nodes.Name: vitexin beta-glucosyltransferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: UDP-D-glucose + vitexin = H+ + UDP + vitexin 2''-O-beta-D-glucoside.

nodes.label: GO:0047308

nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: L-alanine + oxomalonate = aminomalonate + pyruvate.

nodes.label: GO:1990311

nodes.Name: ubiquitin protein ligase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the transfer of ubiquitin to a substrate protein via the reaction X-ubiquitin + S = X + S-ubiquitin, where X is either an E2 or E3 enzyme, the X-ubiquitin linkage is a thioester bond, and the S-ubiquitin linkage is an amide bond: an isopeptide bond between the C-terminal glycine of ubiquitin and the epsilon-amino group of lysine residues in the substrate or, in the linear extension of ubiquitin chains, a peptide bond the between the C-terminal glycine and N-terminal methionine of ubiquitin residues.

nodes.label: GO:0042295
nodes.Name: NEDD8 transferase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the transfer of NEDD8 from one protein to another via the reaction X-NEDD8 + Y = Y-NEDD8 + X, where both X-NEDD8 and Y-NEDD8 are covalent linkages.

nodes.label: GO:0050035

nodes.label: GO:0002307
nodes.Name: CD8-positive, alpha-beta regulatory T cell differentiation
nodes.Definition: The process in which a precursor cell type acquires the specialized features of a CD8-positive, alpha-beta regulatory T cell.

nodes.label: GO:0036218

nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: dTTP + H2O = dTMP + H+ + diphosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0004028

nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: 3-chloroallyl aldehyde + H2O = 2 H+ + 2 e- + 3-chloroacrylic acid.

nodes.label: GO:1990003
nodes.Name: IDP phosphatase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: IDP + H2O = IMP + H+ + phosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0047265

nodes.label: GO:0016003
nodes.Name: carbon-nitrogen ligase activity, with glutamine as amido-N-donor
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the transfer of the amide nitrogen of glutamine to a substrate. Usually composed of two subunits or domains, one that first hydrolyzes glutamine, and then transfers the resulting ammonia to the second subunit (or domain), where it acts as a source of nitrogen.

nodes.label: GO:0044155
nodes.Name: host caveola
nodes.Definition: A small pit, depression, or invagination, such as any of the minute pits or incuppings of the host cell membrane formed during pinocytosis, that communicates with the outside of a host cell and extends inward, indenting the host cytoplasm and the host cell membrane. Such caveolae may be pinched off to form free vesicles within the host cytoplasm. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.

nodes.label: GO:0033735
nodes.Name: aspartate dehydrogenase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: L-aspartate + H2O + NAD(P)+ = oxaloacetate + NH3 + NAD(P)H + H+.

nodes.label: GO:0005607
nodes.Name: laminin-2 complex
nodes.Definition: A laminin complex composed of alpha2, beta1 and gamma1 polypeptide chains.

nodes.label: GO:0036217
nodes.Name: dGTP diphosphatase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the reaction: dGTP + H2O = dGMP + H+ + diphosphate.

nodes.label: GO:0008843
nodes.Name: endochitinase activity
nodes.Definition: Catalysis of the hydrolysis of nonterminal (1->4)-beta linkages of N-acetyl-D-glucosamine (GlcNAc) polymers of chitin and chitodextrins. Typically, endochitinases cleave randomly within the chitin chain.
